(36, 11, '2026-03-16 11:13:55', 'A3 Medical Billing Services LLC', '', '', 'Chief Executive Officer', 'ammar@a3medicalbilling.com', '', 'NO', 25, 'Hard disqualified as a medical billing services company, which falls under excluded consulting/services category rather than direct patient care', 'A3 Medical Billing Services LLC appears to be a medical billing service provider rather than a healthcare practice, offering revenue cycle management services to healthcare providers.', 'mid-size', 'high', 'As a medical billing service provider, they likely struggle with manual payer portal management and lack of automated tools to efficiently handle high claim volumes across multiple client practices.', 'billing service provider, multiple client practices, high claim volume management, manual payer portal workflows', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Managing eligibility checks across dozens of client practices likely creates bottlenecks when your billing team hits payer portals manually.', 'billing staff overload', 'eligibility bottlenecks slowing billing', 'Managing eligibility checks across dozens of client practices creates interesting operational challenges. Most billing services hit the same wall around 15-20 practices, where manual payer portal work starts eating into margins. The verification bottleneck becomes the constraint that limits how many new clients can realistically be onboarded.', 'why we built calyxr', 'Built Calyxr specifically for billing services drowning in manual payer portal work. The platform handles eligibility verification across all major payers automatically, so your team can focus on complex cases instead of routine checks. One billing service reduced verification time by 78% in their first month.', 'Manual eligibility checks typically cost billing services $2.50 per verification when factoring staff time and portal fees. Most services process 800-1200 verifications monthly per practice. Calyxr goes live in 3 days with no long contracts. Curious what your current verification volume looks like?', 'Noticed A3 manages multiple client practices. Manual eligibility verification across dozens of payer portals seems like it would create some interesting bottlenecks for scaling. Worth exploring how other billing services handle this?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(37, 12, '2026-03-16 11:26:11', 'Presbyterian Healthcare Services', 'http://www.phs.org', 'Sheri Leger', 'Manager Clinical Operations Presbyterian Health Plan', 'nan', 'nan', 'NO', 15, 'Presbyterian Healthcare Services is a large hospital system with 14,000 employees, far exceeding Calyxr\'s target market of 10-500 employee healthcare practices.', 'Presbyterian Healthcare Services is a large integrated health system in New Mexico operating hospitals, health insurance plans, and medical group practices with extensive virtual care capabilities.', 'large', 'high', 'Massive scale with 14,000 employees across hospitals, insurance plans, and medical groups creates enormous claim volume, staff coordination challenges, and manual payer portal workload that\'s impossible to manage efficiently', 'large integrated health system, 14000 employees, multiple service lines, hospitals and medical groups, insurance plan operations, high claim volume, complex staff coordination', 'high', 'Influencer', 'medium', 'Managing claim status across 14,000 employees while coordinating between your hospitals, health plan, and medical groups must create massive payer portal workload.', 'staff coordination challenges with massive claim volume', '14,000 employees worth of claims', 'Managing claim status across 14,000 employees while coordinating between hospitals, health plans, and medical groups creates an impossible payer portal workload. Most large healthcare systems find their staff spending 6-8 hours daily just logging into different portals to check claim statuses. The manual coordination between departments becomes the bottleneck that slows everything down.', 'why I\'m reaching out', 'I\'m writing because Calyxr helps large healthcare systems like Presbyterian eliminate the manual payer portal work that\'s crushing your teams. Instead of staff logging into dozens of portals daily, our platform pulls all claim statuses automatically and coordinates updates across departments. One 12,000-employee health system cut their portal time from 40 hours to 3 hours per week.', 'Quick math: if your team spends 40 hours weekly on payer portals at $25/hour, that\'s $52,000 annually just in labor costs. Most systems see this drop to under 5 hours within their first month, with no long contracts or lengthy implementations. Would it make sense to see how this works for a system your size?', 'Managing claim coordination across 14,000 employees and multiple business units must create massive payer portal workload for your teams. I work with large healthcare systems on exactly this challenge, would be worth a brief conversation?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(38, 13, '2026-03-16 11:30:59', 'Associates of Internal Medicine', '', '', 'Practice Manager', 'boreilly@drwiddows.com', '', 'YES', 75, 'Strong fit as a 24-employee internal medicine practice within ideal size range, though lacks specific high-fit signals like multi-location or EMR details.', 'Associates of Internal Medicine is likely a multi-physician internal medicine practice providing comprehensive adult primary care services. Without website data, this appears to be a traditional internal medicine group practice serving adult patients with routine and chronic care needs.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'Multi-physician internal medicine practice with 24 employees likely struggles with high-volume insurance eligibility verification and prior authorization coordination across multiple providers.', 'multi-physician practice, internal medicine specialty, 24 employees suggesting significant patient volume, likely Medicare/Medicaid heavy patient mix, chronic care management requiring frequent prior auths', 'high', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'With 24 staff supporting multiple internists, your team likely spends significant time daily on insurance eligibility checks and prior auth coordination.', 'billing staff overload', 'insurance verification bottleneck', 'Multi-physician internal medicine practices often hit the same wall around 20+ employees. The insurance eligibility verification workload starts consuming entire mornings for multiple staff members. Prior authorization coordination becomes a full-time juggling act across different providers and patient schedules. What used to take minutes per patient now stretches into hours, with teams constantly switching between verification calls and patient care.', 'why I\'m writing', 'I\'m reaching out because Calyxr helps internal medicine practices eliminate the insurance verification bottleneck. Instead of your team spending hours on eligibility checks and prior auth coordination, our platform handles these tasks instantly in the background. One practice with 6 internists reduced their daily verification time from 4 hours to 15 minutes. The same staff who used to juggle insurance calls now focus entirely on patient care and scheduling.', 'Quick math on verification time: if your team saves even 15 minutes daily per provider on insurance tasks, that\'s roughly $12,000 annually in recovered productivity. Most practices see results within days of setup, no long contracts required. Would it make sense to show you exactly how this works for a practice your size?', 'Saw Associates of Internal Medicine online. Multi-physician practices often hit verification bottlenecks around your staff size. Worth a quick conversation about how others solve this?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(39, 14, '2026-03-16 11:47:32', 'Cross Timbers Health Clinic', '', '', 'Patient Services Coordinator', 'tlopez@crosstimbersinc.org', '', 'YES', 85, 'FQHC with 32 employees fits perfectly in target size range and healthcare industry focus, likely handling high patient volumes requiring administrative automation.', 'Cross Timbers Health Clinic appears to be a community-based healthcare facility, likely providing primary care or family medicine services in a rural or suburban area based on the geographic naming convention.', 'small', 'medium', 'Primary care clinic with 32 employees likely struggling with high patient communication volume and manual scheduling workflows across multiple providers', 'community-based primary care, 32 employees suggesting multi-provider practice, likely high patient volume, rural/suburban location may have communication challenges', 'medium', 'Influencer', 'low', 'With 32 staff members handling patient communications, your coordinators are probably drowning in appointment confirmations and insurance verification calls.', 'staff overload from manual patient communication tasks', '32 staff, endless phone tag', 'Most primary care clinics with 30+ staff find their patient services teams spending 60% of their day on appointment confirmations and insurance verifications. The phone tag cycle never ends. Coordinators become reactive instead of proactive, and patient experience suffers despite everyone working harder.', 'why we built calyxr', 'That endless phone tag problem is exactly why we built Calyxr. Our healthcare operations platform handles appointment confirmations and insurance verifications automatically, so your coordinators can focus on complex patient needs instead of repetitive calls. One clinic with similar staffing cut their daily call volume by 70% in the first month.', 'Quick math: if your coordinators spend 3 hours daily on confirmation calls, that\'s roughly $45,000 annually in just labor costs for repetitive tasks. Calyxr typically pays for itself within 60 days, no long contracts required. Worth exploring what those savings could look like for Cross Timbers?', 'Hey! Noticed Cross Timbers has a substantial patient services team. Most clinics your size tell us their coordinators are drowning in confirmation calls and insurance verifications. Curious if that rings true for your team?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(40, 14, '2026-03-16 11:48:12', 'Paoli Family Medicine', '', '', 'Office Manager', 'connie.legge@paolifamilymedicine.com', '', 'YES', 75, 'Mid-size family medicine practice with 27 employees fits core ICP criteria for employee count and healthcare focus, though lacks specific high-fit signals like multi-location or specialty mentions.', 'Paoli Family Medicine is likely a primary care family medicine practice serving patients across all age groups with comprehensive healthcare services.', 'small', 'medium', 'Primary care practice with 27 employees likely struggles with high patient volume, constant insurance eligibility verification, and managing mixed payer types including Medicare/Medicaid patients', 'family medicine specialty, 27 employees indicating significant patient volume, primary care accepting all insurance types, likely high Medicare/Medicaid mix, comprehensive services requiring frequent eligibility checks', 'medium', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'With 27 staff members, your team is probably spending hours daily on insurance eligibility checks for your mixed Medicare/commercial patient base.', 'staff productivity drain from manual verification workflows', '27 staff, endless eligibility checks', 'Primary care practices with mixed Medicare and commercial patients face a familiar pattern. Staff members spend 2-3 hours daily calling insurance companies to verify coverage before appointments. With 27 team members, that\'s potentially 15+ hours of productive clinical time lost to phone calls every single day. The larger the practice, the more this administrative burden multiplies.', 'why I\'m reaching out', 'Healthcare operations is exactly why I\'m writing. Calyxr handles real-time insurance eligibility verification across all payer types, including Medicare and Medicaid. Instead of your staff making dozens of calls, coverage gets verified instantly in your EMR. One practice similar to yours recovered 18 hours per day of clinical time within their first month.', 'If each eligibility call takes 8 minutes and costs $25 in staff time, a practice like yours spends roughly $3,000 weekly just on verification calls. Calyxr typically pays for itself within 30 days, and practices go live within a week with no long-term contracts. How much clinical time is your team currently losing to insurance calls each day?', 'Primary care practices with mixed payer types usually have staff spending hours daily on eligibility verification calls. Calyxr handles this automatically in real-time. Worth a quick conversation about how much time your 27-person team spends on insurance calls?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(41, 14, '2026-03-16 11:48:49', 'Executive Healthcare Services - Concierge Primary Care', '', '', 'Front Desk Coordinator', 'lia@ehsdocs.com', '', 'YES', 75, 'Mid-size concierge primary care practice with 15 employees fits healthcare focus and size parameters, though concierge model may have different operational needs than typical primary care practices.', 'Executive Healthcare Services is a concierge primary care practice serving high-net-worth patients with personalized medical services and enhanced access to physicians.', 'small', 'medium', 'High-touch concierge patients expect immediate communication and seamless scheduling coordination across a small staff of 15', 'concierge model requires premium service levels, high-net-worth patients expect immediate responsiveness, small team managing high-touch relationships, personalized service expectations', 'low', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Managing immediate communication expectations from high-net-worth concierge patients with just 15 staff creates constant interruption cycles that pull coordinators away from scheduling.', 'staff interruption overload', 'concierge patient interruptions', 'Most concierge practices with smaller teams face the same challenge: high-net-worth patients expect immediate responses, but every interruption pulls coordinators away from scheduling tasks. The result is a constant cycle where urgent communication requests create scheduling delays, which then generates more urgent follow-ups. It\'s especially tough with a lean team of 15 where each person wears multiple hats.', 'why we built calyxr', 'The interruption cycle at concierge practices is exactly why we built Calyxr. Instead of coordinators juggling phones and scheduling systems separately, everything flows through one platform that handles patient communication while protecting focused scheduling time. One practice reduced coordinator interruptions by 60% in their first month while maintaining their signature white-glove service standards.', 'Every 15 minutes of coordinator interruptions typically costs about 45 minutes in lost scheduling productivity due to task-switching. For practices with 15 staff, that adds up to significant operational drag. Would a quick 10-minute conversation about how similar concierge practices solved this be worth exploring?', 'Hi there, noticed Executive Healthcare Services focuses on concierge care. Managing immediate communication expectations from high-net-worth patients with a smaller team creates unique coordination challenges. Worth a brief conversation about how similar practices handle this?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(42, 14, '2026-03-16 11:49:28', 'MEDCARE ASSOCIATES P.A.', '', '', 'Practice Manager', 'bmercado@cardiologyclinic.org', '', 'YES', 75, 'Small medical practice with 19 employees fits core ICP criteria, though limited information about specialty, EMR systems, or specific pain points prevents a higher score.', 'MEDCARE ASSOCIATES P.A. appears to be a multi-provider medical practice, likely offering primary care or multi-specialty services based on the \'Associates\' designation suggesting multiple physicians.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'Multi-provider practice with 19 employees likely struggling with coordinating patient communication and scheduling workflows across multiple providers and staff members', 'multi-provider practice, 19 employees suggesting moderate size, Associates designation indicating multiple physicians, likely primary care or multi-specialty', 'medium', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'Managing patient scheduling across multiple providers with 19 staff members creates coordination bottlenecks that ripple through your entire patient flow.', 'multi-provider scheduling coordination chaos', 'scheduling coordination bottlenecks', 'Most multi-provider practices with 15+ staff hit the same wall. Patient scheduling becomes a coordination nightmare when multiple providers, front desk, and clinical staff all need to stay in sync. What starts as simple appointment booking turns into a game of telephone, with double bookings, missed communications, and patients falling through cracks. The bigger the team, the more moving parts that can break down.', 'why calyxr built this', 'That coordination chaos is exactly why Calyxr exists. Instead of juggling separate systems and manual handoffs, everything flows through one platform that keeps your entire team synchronized. Patient communications, scheduling updates, and workflow coordination happen automatically across all 19 of your staff members. One practice manager told us it eliminated their daily \'scheduling emergency meetings\' within the first week.', 'Practices typically lose 2-4 hours daily to scheduling coordination issues, plus the revenue hit from no-shows caused by communication gaps. Calyxr goes live in days, not months, with no long-term contracts required. Would a brief walkthrough of how the coordination piece works make sense for your situation?', 'Managing patient flow across 19 staff members at MEDCARE ASSOCIATES must create some interesting coordination challenges. Been working with similar multi-provider practices on streamlining these workflows. Worth a quick conversation about what you\'re seeing on your end?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(43, 14, '2026-03-16 11:50:04', 'THRIVE Internal Medicine', '', '', 'Practice Manager', 'clouis@thriveinternalmed.com', '', 'YES', 65, 'Small internal medicine practice with 4 employees fits core ICP criteria but lacks specific high-fit signals like multi-location structure or mentioned pain points.', 'THRIVE Internal Medicine appears to be an internal medicine practice focusing on primary care services. Without website data, this is likely a small to mid-size practice providing comprehensive adult primary care.', 'small', 'medium', 'Small 4-person team likely overwhelmed with manual insurance verification, appointment reminders, and claim follow-up tasks that pull staff away from patient care', 'small team size, internal medicine specialty with high patient volume, likely managing multiple insurance plans, primary care requires frequent eligibility checks', 'medium', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'Running internal medicine with a 4-person team means your staff is probably buried in insurance verifications and claim follow-ups daily.', 'billing staff overload', '4-person teams drowning daily', 'Running internal medicine with a 4-person team means someone is always buried in insurance verifications and claim follow-ups. The same staff who should be focused on patient care spend hours each day on hold with insurance companies, chasing down prior authorizations, and tracking claim denials. Most practices this size lose 15-20 hours per week to these manual tasks alone.', 'why I\'m reaching out', 'That\'s exactly why I\'m writing about Calyxr. We handle insurance verification, claim follow-up, and prior authorization tasks so your 4-person team can focus on what matters, patient care instead of phone calls. One internal medicine practice similar to yours freed up 18 hours per week within their first month. What would your team do with those hours back?', 'If your team spends 18 hours weekly on insurance tasks, that\'s roughly $15,000 monthly in lost productivity. Most practices go live with Calyxr in days, not months, and there are no long-term contracts. Would it be worth a brief conversation to see how this applies to THRIVE specifically?', 'Noticed you\'re managing internal medicine with a lean team. Most 4-person practices lose 15-20 hours weekly to insurance verifications and claim follow-ups. Wondering if this sounds familiar at THRIVE?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(44, 15, '2026-03-16 12:05:11', 'Associates of Internal Medicine', '', '', 'Practice Manager', 'boreilly@drwiddows.com', '', 'YES', 85, 'Internal medicine practice with 24 employees fits perfectly within target size range and represents a high-value primary care specialty that typically handles complex patient communication and insurance workflows.', 'Associates of Internal Medicine is an internal medicine practice providing primary care services to adult patients, likely offering comprehensive medical care including preventive services, chronic disease management, and acute care.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'Managing high-volume insurance eligibility verifications and prior authorizations across 24 staff members for comprehensive internal medicine services', 'internal medicine specialty, 24 employees indicating significant patient volume, primary care with chronic disease management requiring frequent insurance verification, comprehensive services likely requiring prior authorizations', 'high', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'With 24 staff members handling eligibility checks for your comprehensive internal medicine patient base, verification bottlenecks likely create scheduling delays.', 'staff resource drain from manual verification processes', '24 staff doing eligibility checks', 'Many internal medicine practices with large teams find their staff spending hours each day on insurance eligibility verifications. With 24 people involved in the process, even small delays in verification can cascade into scheduling bottlenecks that push patient appointments out days or weeks. The manual back-and-forth with insurance companies becomes a full-time job for multiple team members, leaving less time for patient care.', 'why I\'m reaching out', 'I\'m writing because Calyxr helps internal medicine practices eliminate eligibility verification bottlenecks. Instead of your 24 staff members manually checking insurance, our platform handles real-time verifications automatically before appointments are scheduled. One practice similar to yours reduced their eligibility verification time by 80% in the first month. This freed up their team to focus on patient care instead of insurance paperwork.', 'Every delayed appointment due to eligibility issues represents lost revenue, typically $200-400 per slot that sits empty. With your patient volume, verification delays could cost thousands weekly. Calyxr goes live in days with no long-term contracts required. Would you be curious to see how this works for a practice your size?', 'Managing eligibility verifications with 24 staff must create some interesting scheduling challenges. I work with internal medicine practices to eliminate these bottlenecks completely. Worth a quick conversation about how this works?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(45, 16, '2026-03-16 12:09:46', 'Associates of Internal Medicine', 'http://www.drwiddows.com', 'Brooke O\'Reilly', 'Practice Manager', 'nan', 'nan', 'YES', 75, 'Good fit as a 24-employee medical practice likely handling internal medicine with typical healthcare admin challenges, though lacks specialty or high-volume insurance indicators for premium scoring.', 'Associates of Internal Medicine is a primary care practice in Delray Beach, FL led by Dr. Joanna Widdows, focusing on comprehensive preventative healthcare for adult patients.', 'small', 'medium', 'High patient communication overhead with missed appointments and manual scheduling coordination across 24 staff members for comprehensive adult primary care', '24 employees, primary care specialty, comprehensive preventative care, adult patient population, Florida location with high Medicare population', 'medium', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'Managing preventative care coordination for adult patients across 24 staff members likely creates significant appointment reminder and follow-up communication bottlenecks.', 'staff coordination overhead', 'missed appointments eating revenue', 'Managing appointment reminders across 24 staff members creates a perfect storm for missed appointments. Many practices find their front desk spending hours daily on manual calls and coordination, only to watch 15-20% of slots go unfilled anyway. The bigger the team, the more communication falls through the cracks, especially with preventative care follow-ups that patients easily forget about.', 'why we built calyxr', 'The missed appointment problem is exactly why we created Calyxr for practices like Associates of Internal Medicine. Our patient communication system handles appointment reminders, confirmations, and rescheduling automatically, so your 24 staff members can focus on patient care instead of phone tag. One similar practice reduced no-shows by 40% in their first month while cutting communication overhead in half.', 'A typical primary