(51, 21, '2026-03-17 08:13:30', 'Paoli Family Medicine', '', '', 'Office Manager', 'connie.legge@paolifamilymedicine.com', '', 'YES', 75, 'Mid-size family medicine practice with 27 employees fits core ICP criteria for healthcare practices needing patient communication and scheduling automation solutions.', 'Paoli Family Medicine is a primary care practice providing comprehensive family medicine services to patients of all ages in the Paoli area.', 'small', 'medium', 'Managing high patient volume communication and appointment scheduling with limited administrative staff across comprehensive family medicine services', 'primary care specialty, 27 employees indicating moderate size, comprehensive family services, all-age patients requiring frequent communication', 'medium', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'Primary care practices handling all-age patients typically see 30-40% more scheduling conflicts than specialists due to urgent sick visits disrupting routine appointments.', 'scheduling chaos from urgent care disruptions', 'scheduling chaos at paoli', 'Family medicine practices are drowning in appointment conflicts. When urgent sick visits bump routine checkups, the ripple effect creates hours of rescheduling calls. Most practices lose 6-8 hours weekly just managing the chaos that comes with serving all-age patients. The administrative burden keeps growing while staff stays the same.', 'why i\'m reaching out', 'The scheduling conflicts at family practices like Paoli Family Medicine caught my attention. That\'s exactly why we built Calyxr, a platform that automatically handles appointment reshuffling when urgent visits disrupt your schedule. One practice reduced their weekly rescheduling time from 8 hours to under 2. The system learns your patient flow patterns and manages conflicts without staff intervention.', 'Quick math: if your team spends 8 hours weekly on scheduling conflicts, that\'s $12,000+ in annual labor costs just managing appointment chaos. Most practices see the