(66, 24, '2026-03-17 12:08:04', 'Presbyterian Healthcare Services', 'http://www.phs.org', 'Samuel Hinton', 'Director of Operations', 'shinton@phs.org', '', 'NO', 0, 'Large health system with 14,000 employees and $3B revenue exceeds ICP parameters and requires enterprise sales motion outside current GTM capability.', 'Presbyterian Healthcare Services is a major not-for-profit healthcare system serving one in three New Mexicans with nine hospitals, comprehensive services, and integrated health plans. Founded in 1908, they operate as both healthcare provider and insurer with 14,000+ employees and $3B revenue.', 'large', 'high', 'Managing insurance verification and claims processing across nine hospitals with 14,000+ employees creates massive coordination challenges and billing inefficiencies', '14000+ employees, 9 hospitals across 7 communities, $3B revenue, dual provider-insurer model, multi-location complexity, massive claim volume', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'Managing eligibility verification across nine hospitals while also operating as an insurer creates unique dual-sided coordination headaches most health systems don\'t face.', 'dual provider-insurer operational complexity', 'nine hospitals, one nightmare', 'Managing insurance verification across nine different hospitals while also operating as an insurer creates a coordination puzzle most health systems never face. Each facility runs its own eligibility checks, yet everything needs to sync with your insurance operations. The dual-sided complexity means verification delays at any hospital ripple through both your provider network and insurance claims processing. Most 14,000-person organizations struggle with basic coordination, but Presbyterian faces the rare challenge of being both payer and provider simultaneously.', 'why calyxr built for this', 'Healthcare operations platforms typically handle either provider workflows or payer processes, never both. That\'s why I\'m reaching out about Calyxr. We built our verification system specifically for health systems that operate insurance plans alongside multiple facilities. Instead of nine separate verification processes, you get unified eligibility management that speaks to both your hospital systems and insurance operations. One of our health system clients reduced verification time by 60% across their multi-facility network within the first quarter.', 'Presbyterian\'s verification delays likely cost around $2.1M annually in denied claims and administrative overhead across nine facilities. Most health systems see 20-30% of that back in the first six months with streamlined verification. We can show you exactly how this works with your dual payer-provider setup in a 15-minute screen share, no long contracts or complex implementations required. Would seeing the verification workflow for a similar nine-hospital system be worth a quick look?', 'Hi Samuel, noticed Presbyterian operates both as a health system and insurer across nine hospitals. That dual-sided verification coordination challenge caught my attention. Mind if I connect to share how other health systems handle this unique setup?', 'the 14,000 employee math', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (http://www.phs.org) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Presbyterian Healthcare Services', '3B', '14000', '', '', 'New Mexico', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (http://www.phs.org) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/presbyterian-healthcare-services', '+1 505-923-5256', '', '', '', 'phs.org', 'hospital & health care', 'health insurance, health care, hospitals, hospitals & health care, community health programs, services, clinical alerting, healthcare cost reduction, healthcare financing, community engagement, medical network, hospital care', 'Presbyterian Healthcare Services (PHS) is a private, not-for-profit healthcare system based in Albuquerque, New Mexico. Founded in 1908 as a tuberculosis sanatorium, PHS has evolved into a comprehensive healthcare provider serving approximately one in three New Mexicans. The organization operates nine hospitals across seven communities and offers a wide range of services, including acute, preventive, and specialty care. PHS employs over 10,000 people, making it the second-largest private employe', 'Albuquerque', '1908', '1', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
