(67, 24, '2026-03-17 12:08:46', 'Smile Brands Inc.', 'https://smilebrands.com', 'Stephanie Daleiden', 'Manager of People Operations', 'sdaleiden@midwest-dental.com', '', 'NO', 0, 'Large dental service organization with 7,500 employees falls outside medical practice ICP focus and exceeds preferred size range for current GTM motion.', 'Smile Brands Inc. is one of the largest dental service organizations (DSOs) in the United States, providing comprehensive business support to nearly 700 affiliated dental offices across 29 states with $1.5B in revenue.', 'large', 'high', 'Managing insurance eligibility verification and claim status across 700 dental offices creates massive administrative overhead and revenue cycle bottlenecks', '700+ locations, $1.5B revenue scale, 7500 employees, DSO model requires standardized processes, dental insurance complexity, multi-state operations, massive claim volume', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With 700+ affiliated offices processing thousands of dental insurance verifications daily, your revenue cycle teams are likely drowning in manual eligibility checks.', 'billing staff overload', '700 offices, endless eligibility checks', 'Managing insurance eligibility verification across 700+ dental offices means your revenue cycle teams are processing thousands of manual checks daily. Each verification takes 3-5 minutes, and incomplete or delayed eligibility data creates claim denials that ripple through your entire revenue cycle. With 7,500 employees across the network, even small inefficiencies in verification processes compound into massive administrative overhead.', 'why dental groups choose calyxr', 'That\'s exactly why I\'m reaching out about Calyxr. Our platform automates insurance eligibility verification in real-time, eliminating the manual work that\'s bottlenecking your revenue cycle across all 700 offices. One multi-location dental group reduced their eligibility verification time by 80% within the first month. Your teams get instant, accurate insurance data without the phone calls and portal logins.', 'Quick math: if each office saves 15 hours weekly on eligibility verification, that\'s 10,500 hours saved across your network every week. At $25/hour, you\'re looking at potential savings of over $13 million annually. We can have Calyxr live in your offices within days, no long contracts required. Worth exploring what those time savings could mean for your revenue cycle teams?', 'Hi Stephanie, noticed Smile Brands manages eligibility verification across 700+ offices. That\'s a massive administrative lift. I work with dental groups on streamlining their revenue cycle processes. Would love to connect and share what we\'re seeing in the market.', '15 hours saved per office weekly', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://smilebrands.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Smile Brands Inc.', '1.5B', '7500', '', '', 'California', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://smilebrands.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/smile-brands-inc.', '+1 714-668-1300', '', '', '', 'smilebrands.com', 'hospital & health care', 'dental practice transitions, dental assistants, dental careers, general dentistry, dental students, dentist recruiting, dentistry, dental hygienists, general dentists, hospitals & health care, dental practice support solutions, dental practice transition', 'Smile Brands Inc. is one of the largest providers of dental support services in the United States. Founded in 1998 and based in Costa Mesa, California, the company operates as a dental service organization (DSO) that offers comprehensive business support to affiliated dental groups nationwide. With around 7,500 employees and nearly 700 affiliated dental offices, Smile Brands generates approximately $1.1 billion in revenue.\n\nThe company provides essential support services that allow dentists to c', 'Costa Mesa', '1998', '3', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(68, 24, '2026-03-17 12:09:33', 'InterDent Service Corporation', 'https://interdent.com', 'Shane McCarthy', 'Chief Operating Officer', 'mccarthys@interdent.com', '', 'NO', 0, 'InterDent is a Dental Service Organization (DSO) with 2,100 employees and $113.1M revenue, which falls outside Calyxr\'s core medical practice focus and exceeds the ideal employee range.', 'InterDent is a large Dental Service Organization (DSO) providing business and administrative support to nearly 400 dentists across 175 independently owned dental practice locations in 8 states. With 2,100 employees and $113.1M revenue, they focus on enabling dentists to concentrate on clinical care while handling back-office operations.', 'large', 'high', 'Managing insurance eligibility verification and claim status across 175 locations with 400 dentists creates massive administrative burden and billing inefficiencies', 'DSO with 175 locations, 400 dentists, $113M revenue, dental specialty with high insurance complexity, massive scale coordination needs, clinical operations focus', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'Supporting 400 dentists across 175 locations means your billing teams are drowning in eligibility verification rework and claim status calls.', 'billing staff overload', '400 dentists, endless verification calls', 'Most multi-location dental groups hit the same wall around 150+ locations. Billing teams spend half their day on eligibility verification calls and claim status updates. The math gets brutal, 400 providers across 175 locations means thousands of manual touchpoints every week. Administrative overhead starts eating profit margins, especially when you\'re processing the volume that comes with $113M in revenue.', 'why calyxr built for dental groups', 'Built Calyxr specifically for this problem, multi-location dental groups drowning in verification and claim management. Our platform handles real-time eligibility checks and automated claim status updates across all your locations from one dashboard. One of our dental groups cut their verification workload by 78% in the first month, freeing up their billing staff for higher-value tasks.', 'Quick math, if each location averages 15 verification calls daily, that\'s 2,625 calls across your 175 locations. At $25/hour for billing staff, you\'re looking at roughly $65K monthly just on verification labor. Most groups see payback in 90 days, no long implementation timeline. Would eliminating most of those verification calls be worth a brief conversation?', 'Supporting 400 dentists across 175 locations creates a verification nightmare. Built Calyxr to solve exactly this problem for multi-location dental groups. Worth a quick chat about how we\'re cutting verification workload by 70%+ for similar operations?', 'the verification math problem', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://interdent.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'InterDent Service Corporation', '113.1M', '2100', '', '', 'California', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://interdent.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/interdent-service-corporation', '+1 800-436-8531', '', '', '', 'interdent.com', 'hospital & health care', 'speciality dentistry, healthcare, clinical operations, dentistry, dso, practice support, dental, hospitals & health care, dental care, patient satisfaction, time management, dental practice support', 'InterDent Service Corporation is a Dental Service Organization (DSO) that provides essential non-clinical business support and administrative services to around 175 independently owned dental practices across eight states, including Arizona, California, and Washington. Founded over 30 years ago, InterDent originated from Gentle Dental and has grown through mergers, including a significant partnership with Dental Care Alliance in 1999. The company operates under several brands, such as Gentle Den', 'Inglewood', '1978', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(69, 24, '2026-03-17 12:10:16', 'American Oncology Network', 'https://aoncology.com', 'Ashley Gerber', 'Project Manager, Pharmacy Operations', 'ashley.gerber@aoncology.com', '', 'NO', 0, 'Disqualified due to 2,000 employees exceeding the maximum threshold of 1,001-5,000 range and $1.8B revenue far exceeding the $100M maximum, indicating enterprise-level organization requiring different sales motion than Calyxr\'s current GTM approach.', 'American Oncology Network is a large physician-led alliance of community oncology practices with over 2000 employees and $1.8B revenue, providing integrated care and technology platforms to help independent oncology practices navigate administrative complexity while maintaining autonomy.', 'large', 'high', 'Managing insurance eligibility verification and prior authorizations across 2000+ employees and multiple oncology practices creates massive administrative burden and delays in critical cancer treatments', 'oncology specialty, 2000+ employees, $1.8B revenue, multi-location network, practice management focus, administrative complexity mentioned, hematology/medical oncology keywords', 'high', 'Influencer', 'low', 'With 2000+ employees across your network, your pharmacy operations team likely processes hundreds of daily eligibility verifications for high-cost oncology treatments.', 'eligibility verification bottleneck', '2000+ employees, endless verifications', 'With 2000+ employees across your oncology network, pharmacy operations teams often find themselves drowning in hundreds of daily eligibility verifications. Each high-cost cancer treatment requires multiple authorization checks, creating bottlenecks that can delay critical care for patients who can\'t afford to wait. The administrative burden compounds when dealing with complex oncology protocols across multiple practice locations.', 'why calyxr built this', 'Large oncology networks like yours are exactly why Calyxr exists. Instead of your pharmacy team manually processing hundreds of eligibility checks daily, our platform handles the verification workflow automatically, clearing authorizations in minutes rather than hours. One 1500-employee cancer center reduced their prior auth processing time by 78% in the first month.', 'Every day of delayed authorization can mean delayed treatment for cancer patients, plus your team burning hours on manual verifications that could be automated. Most oncology networks see ROI within 60 days, with no long-term contracts required. Would it help to see how this works with a network your size?', 'Ashley, noticed American Oncology Network\'s scale across 2000+ employees. Pharmacy operations at that size likely means constant eligibility verification bottlenecks. Built something specifically for large oncology networks that might interest you.', 'cost of delayed treatments', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://aoncology.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'American Oncology Network', '1.8B', '2000', '', '', 'Florida', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://aoncology.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/american-oncology-network', '+1 866-266-0555', '', '', '', 'aoncology.com', 'medical practice', 'hematology, medical oncology, medical oncology & hematology, medical practices, clinical research, clinical services, practice management, practice transformation, practice autonomy, practice efficiency, offices of physicians, practice support', 'American Oncology Network (AON) is a physician-led alliance of oncologists and healthcare leaders, established in 2017. Based in Fort Myers, Florida, AON focuses on supporting community-based oncology practices through an integrated care and technology platform. The company employs approximately 1,525 people and reported revenue of $1.6 billion. AON is publicly traded under the stock symbol AONC.\n\nAON provides management services that allow physicians to maintain their independence while accessi', 'Fort Myers', '2017', '3', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(70, 24, '2026-03-17 12:11:06', 'American Oncology Network', 'https://aoncology.com', 'Melody Chang', 'Vice President of Pharmacy Operations', 'melody.chang@aoncology.com', '', 'NO', 0, 'Disqualified due to large enterprise size (2000 employees) which exceeds the maximum threshold of 5,000 but more importantly represents a complex enterprise sales motion that doesn\'t fit Calyxr\'s current GTM strategy for mid-market healthcare practices.', 'American Oncology Network is a large physician-led alliance supporting community oncology practices with over $1.6B revenue and 1,525+ employees, focusing on practice management and reducing administrative burden for oncologists.', 'large', 'high', 'Managing insurance authorization workflows and claim denials across 2000+ employees serving complex oncology patients requires massive administrative coordination that\'s overwhelming billing staff', 'oncology specialty, 2000+ employees, $1.8B revenue, practice management focus, administrative burden reduction mission, complex cancer treatments requiring prior auth, high-cost procedures prone to denials', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'Managing prior auths across 270+ community oncology locations while preserving physician autonomy creates massive coordination overhead for your billing teams.', 'billing staff overload', '270 locations, one authorization nightmare', 'Most community oncology networks with 270+ locations face the same coordination nightmare. Prior authorization workflows become exponentially more complex when each location operates with physician autonomy, yet billing teams need centralized oversight. The administrative burden multiplies across thousands of complex cancer treatment protocols, creating bottlenecks that delay patient care and overwhelm staff.', 'why calyxr built for networks like yours', 'Large oncology networks like yours are exactly why we built Calyxr. Our platform handles prior authorization coordination across multiple locations while preserving physician autonomy at each site. One 200-location network reduced their authorization processing time by 60% within the first month. The system manages complex oncology protocols automatically, so your billing teams focus on exceptions rather than routine coordination.', 'Networks your size typically waste $2M+ annually on authorization inefficiencies. The cost of delayed treatments and administrative overhead compounds quickly across 270 locations. Calyxr goes live in days, not months, with no long-term contracts required. Would you be curious to see how similar networks handle prior auth coordination without adding staff?', 'Saw your network spans 270+ locations. Most VP-level pharmacy ops leaders tell us prior authorization coordination across that many sites is their biggest headache. Curious if you\'re seeing the same coordination challenges?', '2000 employees, massive auth savings', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://aoncology.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'American Oncology Network', '1.8B', '2000', '', '', 'Florida', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://aoncology.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-