(71, 24, '2026-03-17 12:11:52', 'Femwell Group Health', 'https://femwell.com', 'Trent Hathaway', 'Vice President, Revenue Cycle', 'thathaway@femwell.com', '', 'NO', 0, 'This is a management services organization (MSO) supporting hundreds of physicians rather than a direct healthcare practice, which falls outside our direct practice ICP and requires an enterprise sales motion.', 'Femwell Group Health is a large management services organization (MSO) based in Florida that provides comprehensive business and operational support to hundreds of physician practices across the state, helping them run efficiently and profitably.', 'large', 'high', 'Managing insurance eligibility verification, claim status tracking, and denial management across hundreds of physician practices creates massive administrative overhead and coordination challenges.', 'large MSO serving hundreds of practices, 310+ employees indicating high administrative overhead, revenue cycle management across multiple specialties, compliance focus suggests heavy insurance requirements, practice optimization keywords indicate current inefficiencies', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'Supporting 300+ physician practices across Florida means your team handles thousands of eligibility verifications and claim inquiries daily.', 'billing staff overload', '300 practices, endless verifications', 'Managing eligibility verification across 300+ physician practices means your team is drowning in thousands of daily verification requests. Each practice calls with urgent patient eligibility questions, claim status updates, and denial appeals that need immediate attention. The coordination overhead alone consumes entire days, and practices still wait hours for responses on time-sensitive patient care decisions.', 'why I\'m writing about Femwell', 'Writing because Calyxr helps revenue cycle teams like yours eliminate the verification bottleneck entirely. Instead of your staff manually handling thousands of eligibility checks, the platform processes them automatically and delivers results directly to each practice in real-time. One Florida health system cut their verification workload by 78% in the first month.', 'With 310 employees handling revenue cycle operations, every hour saved on manual verifications translates to significant cost savings and faster patient care. Most teams see dramatic workload reduction within the first week, no long implementation timelines required. Worth exploring how this might work specifically for your 300+ practice network?', 'Saw Femwell supports 300+ practices across Florida. That verification workload must be intense with thousands of daily eligibility requests. Worth a quick conversation about how similar groups are handling this differently?', '78% less verification work', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://femwell.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Femwell Group Health', '120.2M', '310', '', '', 'Florida', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://femwell.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/femwell-group-health', '+1 305-273-4641', '', '', '', 'femwell.com', 'hospital & health care', 'hospitals & health care, legal advice, practice formation, compliance, practice compliance solutions, private practice support, practice management data services, practice support for florida physicians, practice management technology platforms, practice marketing support, quality assurance, practice optimization', 'Femwell Group Health is a management services organization based in Miami, Florida. Founded in 1997, the company supports hundreds of physicians across the state, from Miami to Jacksonville. With approximately 384 employees and annual revenue of $36.3 million, Femwell focuses on helping medical practices operate more efficiently and profitably.\n\nThe company offers a wide range of practice management services, including managed care support, accounting and finance, compliance and data services, e', 'Miami', '1997', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(72, 24, '2026-03-17 12:12:36', 'Dartmouth Hitchcock Medical Center and Clinics', 'https://dartmouth-hitchcock.org', 'Pat Sorento', 'Operations Manager', 'pat.sorento@hitchcock.org', '', 'NO', 0, 'Large academic medical center with 7,700 employees and $3.6B revenue falls outside Calyxr\'s SMB/mid-market focus. Enterprise health systems require different sales motions than our current GTM approach.', 'Dartmouth Hitchcock Medical Center is New Hampshire\'s only academic medical center with 7,700 employees and $3.6B revenue, providing comprehensive specialized care across multiple locations in New Hampshire and eastern Vermont.', 'large', 'high', 'Managing massive claim volumes and insurance verifications across 12+ specialties with 7,700 employees creates overwhelming administrative burden and revenue cycle bottlenecks', '7700 employees, $3.6B revenue, academic medical center, 12+ specialties including high-complexity cardiology/oncology/neurosurgery, multi-location system, comprehensive specialized care, Medicare/Medicaid academic mission', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 7,700 employees processing eligibility checks across cardiology, oncology, neurosurgery, and 9+ other specialties, your revenue cycle team likely burns hours daily on manual insurance verifications.', 'billing staff overload', '7,700 employees, endless verifications', 'Most large health systems with 12+ specialties face the same challenge. Revenue cycle teams spend countless hours manually verifying insurance eligibility across cardiology, oncology, neurosurgery, and other departments. The bigger the organization, the more verification requests pile up. Staff gets overwhelmed, claims get delayed, and revenue suffers while administrative costs keep climbing.', 'why I\'m reaching out', 'Healthcare operations platforms like Calyxr handle insurance verifications automatically across multiple specialties. Instead of your team manually checking eligibility for thousands of patients, the system processes verifications in real-time and flags issues before claims go out. One 8,000-employee health system cut their verification workload by 80% in the first month.', 'If your revenue cycle team spends even 3 hours daily on manual verifications, that\'s roughly $45,000 annually in staff time per person doing this work. Most large health systems see ROI within 60 days, no long-term contracts required. Would a 15-minute conversation about streamlining verifications across your specialties be worth exploring?', 'Hi Pat, noticed Dartmouth Hitchcock manages verifications across 12+ specialties with 7,700 employees. Most health systems this size struggle with verification bottlenecks. Curious if this impacts your revenue cycle operations?', 'quick math on verification costs', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dartmouth-hitchcock.org) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Dartmouth Hitchcock Medical Center and Clinics', '3.6B', '7700', '', '', 'New Hampshire', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dartmouth-hitchcock.org) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/dartmouthhitchcock', '+1 603-650-5000', '', '', '', 'dartmouth-hitchcock.org', 'hospital & health care', 'emergency, primary care, rheumatology, cardiology heart surgery, cancer, orthopedics, neurology neurosurgery, gynecology, pulmonology, urology, nephrology, gastroenterology', 'Dartmouth Hitchcock Medical Center and Clinics (DHMC and Clinics) is New Hampshire\'s only academic medical center and a key part of the Dartmouth-Hitchcock Health system. It provides specialized services, research, and patient care across New Hampshire and eastern Vermont. The center has its roots in the Mary Hitchcock Memorial Hospital, founded in 1893, and has grown into a comprehensive facility since relocating to a modern campus in Lebanon in 1991.\n\nDHMC offers a wide range of advanced medic', 'Lebanon', '1893', '1', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(73, 24, '2026-03-17 12:13:18', 'MyMichigan Health', 'https://mymichigan.org', 'Brad Choi-Deyoung', 'Director, IT Enterprise Services & Analytics', 'brad.choi-deyoung@mymichigan.org', '', 'NO', 0, 'Large health system with 3,300 employees and $1.5B revenue exceeds ICP parameters. Enterprise-grade organization requires different sales motion than current GTM strategy.', 'MyMichigan Health is a large non-profit health system serving over one million residents across 26 counties in Michigan, with $1.5B revenue and 3,300+ employees operating multiple hospitals and medical centers.', 'large', 'high', 'Managing insurance verification and prior authorization workflows across 26 counties with 3,300+ staff creates massive administrative burden and coordination challenges', 'large health system, 26-county coverage area, 3300+ employees, multiple hospitals and medical centers, managed care involvement, community health focus', 'high', 'Influencer', 'low', 'Coordinating insurance eligibility across 26 counties with 3,300+ staff likely creates verification bottlenecks that delay patient access at your tertiary centers.', 'eligibility verification bottlenecks', 'verification bottlenecks across 26 counties', 'Managing insurance verification across 26 counties with 3,300+ staff creates inevitable coordination gaps. When eligibility checks get stuck between locations, patient access to tertiary care gets delayed. Most health systems this size see verification bottlenecks become the hidden constraint on patient flow, especially when staff across counties work different processes.', 'why MyMichigan caught my attention', 'Your 26-county footprint is exactly why Calyxr caught my attention. Most health systems your size lose 2-3 days per patient on insurance verification coordination between locations. Calyxr connects verification workflows across all sites so eligibility gets confirmed faster. OSF HealthCare cut their verification time by 60% after implementing across their multi-county