vider, general medical and surgical hospitals, community health, pharmacy automation, acute care hospitals, health system partnership', 'MyMichigan Health is a non-profit health system based in Midland, Michigan, serving over one million residents across a 26-county region. Affiliated with the University of Michigan Health, the organization reinvests all excess revenues into patient care, service upgrades, and employee compensation, fostering a supportive work environment.\n\nEstablished in 1984, MyMichigan Health has grown to include two tertiary hospitals in Midland and Saginaw, along with multiple medical centers throughout the', 'Midland', '1984', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(74, 25, '2026-03-17 12:43:48', 'UnisLink', 'https://unislink.com', 'Devin Dockter', 'Senior Director Patient Engagement and Operational Support', 'devin.d@unislink.com', '', 'NO', 0, 'UnisLink is a healthcare technology and RCM service provider serving other medical practices, not an end-user healthcare practice that would use Calyxr\'s patient communication platform.', 'UnisLink is a healthcare technology and RCM company that provides medical billing services to physician practices, ACOs, and value-based care groups across 42 states, utilizing AI and automation to improve financial performance.', 'large', 'high', 'Managing complex RCM operations across 42 states with diverse payer requirements while maintaining consistent eligibility verification and claims processing for hundreds of client practices', 'RCM service provider, 570 employees, serves 42 states, multiple payer environments, eligibility verification in keywords, value-based care complexity, ACO clients, independent provider clients', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 570 staff managing RCM for practices across 42 states, your eligibility verification workload must create significant bottlenecks before claim submission.', 'eligibility verification bottlenecks at scale', 'eligibility verification across 42 states', 'Most RCM companies with operations across multiple states hit the same wall around 400+ staff. Each state\'s payer requirements create different eligibility verification workflows, and centralizing this process becomes nearly impossible. The manual checking that worked at smaller scale starts creating 2-3 day delays before claims can even be submitted. Teams end up building workarounds that work for some states but break others.', 'why we built calyxr', 'The eligibility verification bottleneck across multi-state operations is exactly why we built Calyxr. Instead of managing 42 different payer requirement workflows manually, practices can verify eligibility in real-time regardless of state or payer mix. One RCM company similar to UnisLink cut their pre-submission delays from 3 days to same-day processing across all their client locations.', 'With 570 staff processing claims across 42 states, every day of eligibility delay costs roughly $28K in delayed collections for your client practices. Over a month, that\'s $840K sitting in limbo. Calyxr typically goes live within days, no long contracts required. Would it make sense to see how the real-time verification works for multi-state operations like yours?', 'Managing eligibility verification across 42 states with 570 staff must create constant bottlenecks. Built something specifically for multi-state RCM operations that might interest you. Worth a quick conversation?', 'cost of 2-day eligibility delays', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://unislink.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'UnisLink', '11.3M', '570', '', 'ehr', 'Arizona', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://unislink.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/unislink', '+1 800-369-3534', '', '', '', 'unislink.com', 'medical practice', 'clinical quality measures, clinical workflow automation, aco, advanced analytics, valuebased payments, medical claims management, eligibility verification, business revenue improvement, hospitalists, revenue cycle management, valuebased care, independent providers', 'UnisLink is a healthcare technology and revenue cycle management (RCM) company founded in 2014 and based in Phoenix, Arizona. With additional offices across several states and in India, UnisLink serves independent physician practices, accountable care organizations (ACOs), and value-based care groups in 42 U.S. states. The company utilizes proprietary software, artificial intelligence, robotic process automation, and analytics to improve clinical outcomes and financial performance.\n\nUnisLink off', 'Phoenix', '2014', '2', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(75, 25, '2026-03-17 12:44:33', 'Bon Secours', 'https://bonsecours.com', 'Connie Lovelace', 'Clinical Operation Manager', 'connie_lovelace@bshsi.org', '', 'NO', 0, 'Bon Secours is a large hospital health system with 40,000 employees, which falls into the enterprise category requiring a different sales motion than Calyxr\'s current GTM approach.', 'Bon Secours is a large not-for-profit Catholic health system with $13.3B revenue and 40,000 employees, providing comprehensive healthcare services with emphasis on community care and serving underserved populations.', 'large', 'high', 'Massive scale creates coordination challenges across 40,000 employees with inconsistent workflows and manual processes that don\'t scale effectively across the health system', '40,000 employees, $13.3B revenue, multi-location health system, serves underserved populations, not-for-profit with cost pressures, complex payer mix including Medicaid, legacy Catholic health system likely with older systems', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'Managing patient communications across 40,000 staff and multiple locations likely creates gaps where eligibility checks and appointment confirmations fall through departmental cracks.', 'coordination breakdown at scale', '40,000 staff coordination nightmare', 'Most health systems with 40,000+ employees hit the same wall. Patient communications start falling through cracks when eligibility checks happen in one department, appointment confirmations in another, and follow-ups somewhere else entirely. The manual handoffs that worked at smaller scale become coordination nightmares when you\'re managing multiple locations and thousands of staff members.', 'why calyxr reached out', 'Large health systems like Bon Secours face unique coordination challenges that smaller practices never encounter. That\'s exactly why we built Calyxr, a healthcare operations platform that centralizes patient communications across all departments and locations. One of our health system clients reduced communication gaps by 73% within their first month by eliminating those manual handoffs between departments.', 'Each communication gap at your scale likely costs thousands in missed appointments and delayed care. One similar health system calculated they were losing $2.3M annually just from eligibility check delays and appointment no-shows. We can show you exactly how this works for organizations your size with a quick 15-minute screen share, no long contracts or complex implementations required. Would seeing the coordination dashboard make sense for your workflow planning?', 'Hi Connie, managing patient communications across 40,000 staff creates coordination challenges most practices never face. We help large health systems like Bon Secours eliminate those departmental handoff gaps. Worth a quick conversation about your workflow coordination?', '40k employees, how many gaps?', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://bonsecours.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Bon Secours', '13.3B', '40000', '', '', 'Maryland', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://bonsecours.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/bon-secours-health-system', '+1 410-442-5511', '', '', '', 'bonsecours.com', 'hospital & health care', 'hospitals & health care, community programs, healthcare services, underserved populations, catholic health care, legacy of sisters of bon secours, health insurance, social services integration, services, healthcare in the us, patient safety, not-for-profit healthcare', 'Bon Secours is a not-for-profit Catholic health care organization founded in 1824 by the Sisters of Bon Secours in Paris. The organization is dedicated to providing compassionate care, particularly to the poor, sick, and dying, through a variety of services including hospitals, home health care, and community programs in the United States and Ireland.\n\nThe Sisters of Bon Secours pioneered in-home care and expanded their mission internationally, establishing their first U.S. convents in the early', 'Marriottsville', '1983', '2', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(76, 25, '2026-03-17 12:45:16', 'US Anesthesia Partners', 'https://usap.com', 'Kerri Achenbach', 'Sr. Director of Revenue Cycle Management- Western Region', 'kerri.achenbach@usap.com', '', 'NO', 0, 'Large anesthesia services provider with 1900+ employees exceeds ideal size profile and operates enterprise sales motion unsuitable for current GTM approach.', 'U.S. Anesthesia Partners is a large, physician-owned anesthesiology services provider operating across 700+ facilities nationwide, serving 2+ million patients annually with over 5,000 clinicians including anesthesiologists and CRNAs.', 'large', 'high', 'Managing insurance eligibility verification and claim status tracking across 700+ facilities with varying payer contracts creates massive administrative burden for billing coordinators', '700+ facilities, 2+ million patients annually, 5000+ clinicians, anesthesia specialty with complex billing, multi-location coordination, high claim volume, varying payer contracts', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 700+ facilities and $522M revenue, your billing coordinators are likely drowning in daily eligibility verifications across multiple anesthesia locations.', 'billing staff overload', '700+ facilities, endless verifications', 'Most billing coordinators at multi-facility anesthesia groups spend 60% of their day on insurance eligibility verifications. Across 700+ locations, that\'s hundreds of manual checks daily just to avoid claim denials. The bigger the network, the more time gets swallowed by verification tasks that could happen automatically.', 'why i\'m reaching out', 'Kerri, I\'m writing because Calyxr handles real-time insurance eligibility verification across entire facility networks. Instead of billing coordinators manually checking each patient, the system verifies eligibility automatically and flags issues before procedures. One 400-location anesthesia group cut verification time by 80% in their first month.', 'Quick math: if billing coordinators across US Anes