(84, 27, '2026-03-17 13:49:41', 'Urgent Care of Texas', '', 'Aman Khan', 'ASST. Practice Manager', '', '', 'YES', 16, 'Texas-based urgent care with assistant practice manager title suggests operational oversight role, but lacks firmographic data and technology signals to demonstrate strong ICP alignment.', 'Urgent Care of Texas appears to be a multi-location urgent care network providing walk-in medical services for non-emergency conditions across Texas markets.', 'large', 'high', 'High patient volume urgent care with walk-in scheduling creates massive patient communication challenges with missed appointments and no-shows impacting revenue', 'urgent care specialty, multi-location network, walk-in patient model, high patient turnover, Texas market coverage', 'high', 'Gatekeeper', 'low', 'Multi-location urgent care networks like yours typically see 20-30% no-show rates without proactive patient communication workflows.', 'no-show revenue loss', 'walk-in scheduling chaos', 'Multi-location urgent care networks face a brutal challenge. Walk-in patients expect immediate care, but without confirmed appointments, practices can\'t predict daily volume. The result is either overstaffed shifts with idle providers or understaffed shifts with angry patients waiting hours. Meanwhile, 20-30% of scheduled slots go unused because patients simply don\'t show up or communicate changes.', 'why we built calyxr', 'That communication chaos is exactly why we built Calyxr for urgent care operations. Our platform automatically reaches patients before their visit with smart reminders and real-time updates, then fills last-minute cancellations instantly. One Texas urgent care network reduced no-shows by 40% in their first month, turning empty slots into revenue.', 'A 100-patient daily volume with 25% no-shows costs roughly $180K annually in lost revenue. Most urgent care groups see ROI within 60 days with our system, and we go live in under a week with no long contracts. Would it help to see how similar networks are filling those empty chairs?', 'Hi Aman, noticed Urgent Care of Texas manages high walk-in volumes across locations. Most urgent care networks struggle with 20-30% no-show rates without proactive patient communication. Quick question, how are you currently handling last-minute cancellations and open slots?', 'cost of empty chairs', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, specialty) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, specialty) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
