(88, 28, '2026-03-17 13:54:02', 'Collier Urgent Care', 'http://www.collierurgentcare.com', 'Christine Murphy-Jones', 'Office Manager', 'cmurphy@collierurgentcare.com', '', 'YES', 62, 'Strong urgency care fit in high-value Florida market with solid revenue scale. Office Manager role suggests operational pain but lacks senior decision-making authority for immediate priority.', 'Collier Urgent Care operates 3 walk-in urgent care locations in Naples, Florida, staffed by board-certified physicians and serving patients 7 days a week with on-site lab and x-ray services.', 'mid-size', 'high', 'High daily patient volume across 3 locations with walk-in scheduling creates massive insurance eligibility verification bottlenecks and staff overwhelm', 'urgent care specialty, 3 locations, walk-in model, 7 days/week operations, 28 employees serving high patient volume, on-site services requiring pre-authorization', 'high', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'Managing insurance eligibility for walk-ins across 3 Naples locations with 28 staff likely creates verification delays that slow your 7-day operation.', 'eligibility verification bottlenecks', 'walk-ins hitting verification walls', 'Walk-in patients expect fast service, but insurance eligibility checks create bottlenecks that slow everything down. Most urgent care practices with multiple locations find their staff spending 15-20 minutes per patient just verifying coverage before treatment can begin. The bigger the operation, the more these delays compound across locations, creating frustrated patients and overwhelmed staff.', 'why calyxr built this', 'Christine, insurance verification bottlenecks across multiple urgent care locations is exactly why we built Calyxr. Our platform handles real-time eligibility verification so walk-in patients get processed in under 2 minutes instead of 15-20. Gulf Coast Medical reduced their verification time by 85% after switching from their manual process.', 'If each of your 28 staff members saves just 30 m