(89, 28, '2026-03-17 13:55:06', 'FAST TRACK URGENT CARE', 'http://www.urgentcaredcmd.com', 'Elly Strait', 'Chief Operating Officer', '', '', 'YES', 56, 'Maryland-based urgent care with COO decision-maker in ideal persona, but small size (19 employees) limits growth potential. Strong industry and title fit offset by scale constraints.', 'Fast Track Urgent Care is a walk-in clinic serving Silver Spring, Kensington, and Montgomery County, MD with 19 employees, providing immediate care services for non-emergency medical needs.', 'small', 'medium', 'High patient volume walk-in clinic with unpredictable scheduling and insurance verification needs overwhelming a small 19-person staff', 'walk-in clinic model, unpredictable patient flow, 19 employees for multi-location operation, urgent care specialty with high insurance complexity', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'Managing walk-in eligibility checks with 19 staff across three Montgomery County locations likely creates bottlenecks when patient volume spikes unexpectedly.', 'eligibility verification bottlenecks during volume spikes', '19 staff, three locations', 'Walk-in clinics with multiple locations hit a wall when patient volume spikes unexpectedly. Staff gets pulled in different directions between eligibility checks, patient flow, and insurance verification. The 19-person teams that run smoothly on Tuesday mornings suddenly feel understaffed when Friday afternoon brings double the usual walk-ins. Many urgent care operators notice this pattern but haven\'t found a way to handle the unpredictable surge without overwhelming their teams.', 'eligibility bottlenecks solved', 'Calyxr handles real-time insurance verification so your Montgomery County teams can focus on patient care instead of eligibility checks. When volume spikes hit, our platform processes the verification work in the background while your staff stays focused on what matters. One 15-location urgent care group saw their staff stress drop significantly once eligibility verification moved off their plates. What\'s your biggest challenge when patient volume suddenly doubles on busy days?', 'A typical 19-person urgent care team spends roughly 4 hours daily on insurance verification across all locations. That\'s over $75,000 annually in labor costs just for eligibility checks. Calyxr clients typically see verification time drop to under 30 minutes per day, with no long contracts required and most go live within days. Would it help to see exactly how this works for multi-location urgent care setups like yours?', 'Hi Elly, noticed Fast Track operates three Montgomery County locations with walk-in volume. Managing insurance verification with 19 staff across multiple sites during surge times seems challenging. Worth a quick conversation about streamlining this?', '4 hours per day saved', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (http://www.urgentcaredcmd.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'FAST TRACK URGENT CARE', '', '19', '', '', 'Maryland', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (http://www.urgentcaredcmd.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/fast-track-