(90, 28, '2026-03-17 13:55:56', 'The MediCentral', 'http://www.themedicentral.com', 'Thyana Jannah', 'Director of Telemedicine Operations', '', '', 'YES', 52, 'Strong healthcare industry match with telemedicine focus and Director-level IT persona, but small team size (10 employees) and recent founding (2021) suggest limited scale and maturity for immediate deployment.', 'The MediCentral is a modern healthcare provider focused on accessible, technology-driven care with telemedicine capabilities and walk-in clinic services. They emphasize efficiency and affordability while combining traditional care with cutting-edge medical technology.', 'small', 'medium', 'Managing high-volume walk-in patients and telemedicine appointments with limited staff creates scheduling chaos and missed revenue opportunities', 'walk-in clinic model, telemedicine capabilities, only 10 employees, technology-focused but likely manual processes, high patient turnover from convenient access model', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 10 staff juggling both walk-ins and telemedicine flows, your scheduling bottlenecks are likely costing you same-day appointment revenue.', 'scheduling chaos and missed revenue opportunities', 'walk-ins vs telemedicine chaos', 'Most practices with 10 staff find themselves stuck between two worlds. Walk-in patients expect immediate care, while telemedicine slots need advance scheduling. The result? Staff constantly juggling between front desk chaos and virtual appointment prep, with same-day revenue slipping through the cracks when scheduling conflicts arise.', 'why we built calyxr', 'That scheduling chaos between walk-ins and telemedicine is exactly why we built Calyxr. It automatically manages both patient flows without your staff having to choose between immediate care and virtual appointments. One practice similar to yours recovered $180K in annual same-day appointment revenue within 90 days.', 'Quick math: if scheduling conflicts cost you just 3 same-day appointmen