(100, 29, '2026-03-17 14:33:11', 'A PLUS FAMILY URGENT CARE', 'https://aplusfamilyuc.com', 'Kim Arena', 'Practice Administrator', 'kim.arena@aplusfamilyuc.com', '', 'YES', 62, 'Strong fit urgent care practice in Florida with Practice Administrator decision-maker and 14 employees in sweet spot range. Missing EHR data and revenue signals limit higher scoring.', 'A+ Family Urgent Care is a single-location walk-in clinic in South Tampa providing urgent care services for families, operating 7 days a week with 14 employees and accepting most insurance plans.', 'small', 'medium', 'Walk-in urgent care clinic with \'most insurances accepted\' likely struggling with real-time insurance eligibility verification and high denial rates from insurance mix complexity', 'walk-in clinic model, most insurances accepted, urgent care specialty, small 14-person team, single location with high patient turnover', 'high', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'Walk-in model with 14 staff accepting \'most insurances\' means your front desk is constantly calling to verify coverage before treatment.', 'staff overload from manual eligibility verification', 'insurance verification calls', 'Walk-in urgent care creates a unique challenge most practices don\'t face. Patients show up expecting immediate care, but verifying their insurance eligibility in real-time often means your front desk is tied up on hold with insurance companies. The alternative is treating first and hoping coverage is valid, which creates its own risks. Many urgent care clinics with diverse insurance acceptance find their staff spending more time on verification calls than patient care.', 'why I\'m reaching out', 'I\'m writing because Calyxr helps urgent care clinics verify insurance eligibility in seconds, not minutes. Instead of your front desk calling insurance companies, our system checks coverage instantly while patients are still at reception. One urgent care group reduced their verification time from 8 minutes per patient to under 30 seconds. Does real-time eligibility verification sound like it could help A Plus Family Urgent Care streamline your walk-in process?', 'If your 14-person team is spending even 5 minutes per patient on insurance verification, that\'s over 40 hours weekly that could be spent on patient care instead. Most urgent care clinics see immediate ROI within their first month, no long contracts required. Would you be open to a brief conversation about how real-time verification might work for your walk-in model?', 'Hi Kim, I work with urgent care clinics struggling with insurance verification delays for walk-in patients. Most find their front desk spends more time on hold with insurance companies than helping patients. Is this something A Plus Family deals with regularly?', '30 seconds vs 8 minutes', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://aplusfamilyuc.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'A+ Family Urgent Care', '', '14', '', '', 'Florida', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://aplusfamilyuc.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/a-family-urgent-care', '+1 813-234-0100', '', '', ''