(102, 29, '2026-03-17 14:34:37', 'BONA DEA GYNECOLOGY', 'https://bonadeagynecology.com', 'Elease Emporellis', 'Practice Manager', 'elease.emporellis@bonadeagynecology.com', '', 'YES', 52, 'Small 7-employee women\'s health practice in NJ with functional medicine focus shows decent firmographic fit and specialty alignment, but lacks clear pain signals and senior decision-maker access.', 'Bona Dea Gynecology is an integrative women\'s health practice blending functional and conventional medicine, led by Dr. Tracy Verrico serving Bergen County, NJ and offering virtual consultations nationwide. The practice focuses on root-cause analysis with extended appointment times and personalized care approaches.', 'small', 'high', 'Complex insurance verification and prior authorization requirements for specialized hormone therapy and functional medicine treatments that many insurers don\'t readily cover', 'functional medicine specialty, hormone therapy focus, extended appointment times, virtual consultations across states, small 7-person team, specialized treatments requiring prior auth', 'high', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'Functional medicine practices like yours typically spend 40% more time on insurance eligibility calls for hormone therapy coverage than conventional gynecology offices.', 'billing staff overload from complex prior authorizations', 'hormone therapy authorization maze', 'Functional medicine practices are drowning in insurance verification calls. Hormone therapy coverage requires multiple rounds of prior auth documentation that conventional gynecology never deals with. The average eligibility verification for bioidentical hormones takes 3x longer than standard prescriptions. Many practices are spending entire mornings just navigating insurer requirements for treatments that should be straightforward approvals.', 'why I\'m writing about calyxr', 'I\'m reaching out because Calyxr specializes in insurance verification for functional medicine practices like BONA DEA GYNE