(112, 30, '2026-03-18 14:45:06', 'Langdon Prairie Health', 'https://lph.hospital', 'Darla Roder', 'Chief Operating and Compliance Officer', 'darla.roder@lph.hospital', '', 'YES', 42, 'Small hospital with strong ops leadership fit (COO title scores well) but limited firmographic signals and no clear technology or pain indicators to drive higher qualification.', 'Langdon Prairie Health is a critical access hospital and clinic serving rural communities since 1939, providing comprehensive healthcare from emergency services to primary care across multiple locations in Langdon and Walhalla.', 'small', 'high', 'Critical access hospital with multiple locations likely struggling with insurance eligibility verification and claim processing across different service lines with limited billing staff', 'critical access hospital, multiple locations, rural healthcare, comprehensive services, small staff relative to service scope, emergency services complexity', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'Managing eligibility verification across emergency, primary care, and specialty services with a 32-person staff at multiple rural locations creates serious billing bottlenecks.', 'billing staff overload', '32 staff, multiple locations', 'Critical access hospitals with multiple service lines face an impossible math problem. Emergency, primary care, and specialty services each generate different eligibility requirements, but most rural facilities run with the same small billing team they had five years ago. The result is a growing backlog of unverified claims that creates cash flow gaps no hospital can afford.', 'why I\'m writing to Langdon Prairie', 'Darla, I\'m reaching out because Calyxr helps critical access hospitals solve the eligibility verification bottleneck across multiple locations and service lines. Instead of your billing staff manually checking each patient, our platform handles verification in real-time before services are rendered. One 28-bed hospital in Montana cut their claim deni