(129, 30, '2026-03-18 14:57:08', 'DOC-AID Urgent Care', 'https://doc-aid.com', 'Marisa Smithwick', 'Director of Operations', 'msmithwick@doc-aid.com', '', 'YES', 42, 'Director-level Operations contact at healthcare urgent care facility with 18 employees falls into viable size range. Limited data prevents higher scoring but core fit elements present.', 'DOC-AID Urgent Care operates three walk-in urgent care clinics in Laredo, TX, providing same-day treatment for minor illnesses and injuries with on-site labs and X-rays. They serve patients of all ages with no appointment required, open daily 10 AM - 8 PM.', 'small', 'medium', 'Three walk-in urgent care locations with no-appointment model likely struggling with unpredictable patient flow, insurance verification bottlenecks, and manual coordination across sites', 'multi-location operations, walk-in no-appointment model, urgent care specialty, small staff relative to three locations, daily 10-8 operations, on-site diagnostics requiring workflow coordination', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'Managing insurance eligibility across three walk-in locations with 18 staff probably means your front desk spends hours daily on hold with payers.', 'staff time waste on insurance verification', '18 staff, endless hold music', 'Most urgent care directors notice their front desk staff spending 2-3 hours daily on hold with insurance companies. Three locations with walk-in patients makes it worse since eligibility checks can\'t wait. The hold music becomes a soundtrack to mounting patient wait times and frustrated staff.', 'why I\'m writing about eligibility', 'Calyxr handles real-time insurance verification so your front desk stops playing phone tag with payers. Instead of 18 staff members juggling hold times across three locations, eligibility gets verified instantly when patients walk in. One urgent care group cut their verification time from 45 minutes to under 2 minutes per patient.', 'If your team verifies 50 patients daily across three sites, that\'s 37.5 hours saved per day on hold times alone. At $20/hour front desk wages, you\'re looking at $195,000 annually in just labor costs. Most practices see this working within days, no long contracts required. Worth exploring what those savings could look like for DOC-AID?', 'Hey Marisa, managing insurance verification across three urgent care walk-ins with 18 staff sounds like a daily coordination challenge. Curious how you\'re handling the patient flow bottlenecks when front desk gets stuck on hold with payers?', '45 minutes vs 2 minutes', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://doc-aid.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '18', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://doc-aid.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'msmithwick@doc-aid.com', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Director of Operations', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(130, 30, '2026-03-18 14:57:47', 'Emergence Health Holdings', 'https://emergencehealth.com', 'Joseph Sicard', 'Director of Operations', 'jsicard@ccmdcenters.com', '', 'YES', 39, 'Strong persona match with Director of Operations and healthcare industry fit, but small size (24 employees) and lack of technology/pain signals limit scoring potential.', 'Emergence Health Holdings is a parent company operating two urgent care brands (CareWell and ClearChoiceMD) across New England with 50+ locations providing walk-in care 12 hours daily, 7 days a week.', 'large', 'high', 'Managing patient communication and scheduling across 50+ urgent care locations with only 24 employees creates massive operational inefficiency and missed revenue opportunities', 'multi-location operator, urgent care specialty, high patient volume, lean staffing model, walk-in scheduling complexity, extended hours operation', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'Running 50+ urgent care locations with just 24 employees means your front desk teams are drowning in eligibility checks and appointment confirmations.', 'staff overload from manual processes', '24 people, 50+ locations', 'Most urgent care networks with 50+ locations have 200+ administrative staff. Running that many sites with just 24 people means your front desk teams are probably buried in eligibility checks, appointment confirmations, and patient callbacks. The math just doesn\'t add up for sustainable operations.', 'why I\'m writing', 'I\'m reaching out because Calyxr helps urgent care networks like yours handle patient communication and scheduling without adding headcount. We automate eligibility verification and appointment confirmations so your 24-person team can focus on higher-value work. One network reduced their administrative workload by 60% in the first month.', 'Every missed appointment or delayed eligibility check costs urgent care centers roughly $200 in lost revenue. Across 50+ locations, that adds up fast. Calyxr typically pays for itself within 30 days, no long contracts required. Would it help to see how this works for a network your size?', 'Joseph, noticed you\'re managing operations across 50+ urgent care locations with a lean 24-person team. That\'s impressive but probably overwhelming for patient scheduling and communication. Mind if I share how similar networks handle this without adding staff?', 'the revenue math', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://emergencehealth.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '24', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://emergencehealth.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'jsicard@ccmdcenters.com', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Director of Operations', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(131, 30, '2026-03-18 14:58:24', 'Inpatient Physician Associates, PLLC', 'https://inpatientdocs.com', 'April Wyant', 'Director of Operations', 'awyant@inpatientdocs.com', '', 'YES', 43, 'Hospital-based physician group with Director of Operations shows good persona fit, but small size (25 employees) and lack of clear pain signals limit the score to partial fit territory.', 'Inpatient Physician Associates is a hospitalist group providing inpatient medical care services with 25 employees, focusing on hospital-based patient management and coordination.', 'mid-size', 'high', 'Managing high-volume insurance verifications and claims for frequent hospital admissions with complex payer mix across 25 staff members', 'hospitalist specialty, hospital-based care, high admission volume, complex insurance mix, 25-person team coordination, frequent eligibility checks needed', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'Managing eligibility verification for frequent hospital admissions across 25 hospitalists creates constant insurance rework cycles that pull staff from patient care.', 'eligibility rework', 'insurance rework cycles', 'Hospital medicine practices with 25+ providers face a constant cycle of insurance verification failures. Each admission triggers eligibility checks that often come back incomplete or outdated, forcing staff to restart the verification process while patients wait. The frequent readmissions and complex payer mix in hospital settings makes this even worse, creating a bottleneck that pulls administrative staff away from supporting patient care.', 'why calyxr reached out', 'The insurance verification bottlenecks at practices like yours are exactly why we built Calyxr. Instead of manual eligibility checks that fail and require rework, our platform handles real-time verification for hospital admissions automatically, even with complex payer arrangements. One 30-provider hospitalist group reduced their insurance rework by 78% in the first month. Does this sound like something that could help your team focus more on patient care?', 'A practice your size typically spends 15-20 hours weekly on insurance rework cycles, which costs roughly $180k annually in staff time alone. Calyxr eliminates most of this rework and goes live in days, not months, with no long-term contracts required. Would it make sense to see how this works for a hospitalist practice like yours?', 'Hi April, noticed Inpatient Physician Associates manages a complex payer mix across 25 hospitalists. The insurance verification rework cycles in hospital medicine are brutal. Worth a quick conversation about how similar practices are eliminating most of this administrative burden?', 'cost of verification rework', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://inpatientdocs.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '25', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://inpatientdocs.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'awyant@inpatientdocs.com', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Director of Operati