(138, 30, '2026-03-18 15:03:04', 'Urgent Care Clinic, PLLC', 'https://uccsouth.com', 'Yuliya Neymer', 'Director of Operations', 'yneymer@uccsouth.com', '', 'YES', 42, 'Perfect industry match (urgent care) with ideal operations persona (Director of Operations), but limited by missing geographic, revenue, and technology signals. Employee count of 29 fits viable range.', 'Urgent Care Clinic PLLC is a walk-in urgent care facility in Southampton, PA serving children and adults with injury care, diagnostic services, and comprehensive urgent care without appointments. They emphasize faster, more affordable care than emergency rooms with on-site lab work, X-rays, and radiology services.', 'small', 'medium', 'High patient volume with walk-in scheduling creates communication chaos with missed callbacks, no-show follow-ups, and manual appointment reminders overwhelming your 29-person team', 'walk-in urgent care model, no appointments needed, high patient turnover, 29 employees managing unpredictable volume, injury care requiring follow-up', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'Managing 29 staff across walk-in urgent care with on-site diagnostics means your team is constantly juggling callback queues and follow-up communications.', 'staff overwhelm from communication chaos', 'callback chaos with walkins', 'Most urgent care practices with high walk-in volume hit the same wall around 25-30 staff members. The callback queues start backing up, no-show follow-ups get missed, and manual appointment reminders eat up hours of admin time daily. When you\'re managing diagnostics on top of patient flow, communication tasks become the bottleneck that slows everything down. The bigger question becomes whether this scales without burning out the team.', 'why calyxr built this', 'That callback chaos is exactly why we built Calyxr for practices like Urgent Care Clinic. Instead of your 29-person team manually managing follow-ups and reminders, our platform handles the entire communication workflow au