(139, 30, '2026-03-18 15:03:47', 'Visiting Docs', 'https://myvisitingdocs.com', 'Jason King', 'Director of Operations', 'jking@myvisitingdocs.com', '', 'YES', 39, 'Strong persona match with Director of Operations and healthcare industry fit, but very small team size (14 employees) limits growth potential and contract value.', 'Visiting Docs is a family medicine practice in Rockland County providing comprehensive primary care services to patients of all ages with 14 employees and expansion plans.', 'small', 'medium', 'With only 14 employees serving comprehensive primary care across all ages, staff are likely overwhelmed with manual patient communication, appointment scheduling, and insurance verification tasks', 'small staff size relative to comprehensive services, family medicine high patient volume, all-age demographics requiring frequent scheduling, expansion plans with current staffing constraints', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 14 staff managing comprehensive primary care across all age groups, your team probably spends hours daily on insurance eligibility checks and appointment confirmations.', 'small staff operational overload', '14 staff, endless phone calls', 'Most primary care practices with small teams face the same daily grind. Staff spend 3-4 hours on insurance eligibility checks and appointment confirmations instead of patient care. The phone never stops ringing, and manual verification processes eat up entire mornings. When you\'re covering all age groups with 14 people, every hour counts.', 'why visiting docs caught our attention', 'Your team at Visiting Docs likely knows this pain well, which is why Calyxr exists. We handle insurance verification and patient communication automatically, so your 14 staff members can focus on what matters. One practice with a similar setup freed up 20 hours weekly within their first month. How much time does your team currently spend on these manual tasks each day?', 'Quick math: if insurance checks and appointme