(143, 30, '2026-03-18 15:06:25', 'MercyCare Community Physicians', '', 'Kathy Keane', 'Director, Clinic Operations', 'kkeane@mercydesmoines.org', '', 'YES', 44, 'Strong persona match with Director of Clinic Operations at healthcare practice with 45 employees (ideal size range). Limited by missing geography, revenue, and technology signals.', 'MercyCare Community Physicians is a mid-sized healthcare organization with 45 employees serving community-based patients across multiple specialties and primary care services.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'With 45 employees across multiple specialties, MercyCare likely struggles with coordinating patient communication and workflow automation across different departments and care teams', '45 employees, multi-specialty practice, community-based patients, mid-sized organization coordination complexity', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 45 staff across multiple specialties, your teams probably spend hours daily on eligibility verifications that could be handled automatically.', 'staff time inefficiency / verification bottlenecks', '45 staff, endless verifications', 'Multi-specialty practices with 45+ staff typically burn 3-4 hours daily on manual insurance eligibility checks. Each verification takes 8-12 minutes per patient, and with multiple departments handling their own checks, the same patient often gets verified twice. The math adds up quickly when you\'re coordinating across different care teams.', 'why I\'m writing today', 'Reaching out because Calyxr handles real-time insurance eligibility verification automatically, so your teams across specialties can focus on patient care instead of phone calls to payers. One practice with 50+ staff cut their verification time by 85% in the first month. Does this sound like something worth exploring for MercyCare\'s operations?', 'Quick math: 3 hours of staff time daily on verifications costs most practices $75,000+ annually in labor alone. Calyxr typically pays for itself in 60-90 days, with no long-term contracts required. Would a brief conversation about how this could work for your multi-specialty setup be worthwhile?', 'Hi Kathy, noticed MercyCare has multiple specialties with 45 staff. Most practices your size spend hours daily on manual insurance verifications. Built something that handles this automatically, curious if this resonates with your current operations?', '3 hours daily adds up', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '45', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'kkeane@mercydesmoines.org', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Director, Clinic Operations', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(144, 30, '2026-03-18 15:07:06', 'Complete Care Management Services', 'https://ccmsus.com', 'Aristides Legra', 'Executive Director of Operations', 'aristidesl@ccmsus.com', '', 'YES', 44, 'Strong operations leadership persona with Executive Director title, healthcare industry match, and appropriate employee size (22), but lacks technology signals, pain indicators, and geographic/revenue data to reach higher scoring tiers.', 'Complete Care Management Services (CCMS) provides in-home healthcare and care coordination services focused on reducing hospital readmissions and managing transitions of care. They work with hospitals, SNFs, and primary care providers to deliver coordinated care management for high-need patients.', 'small', 'high', 'Managing care transitions and patient follow-up across multiple healthcare facilities requires extensive manual coordination and communication that\'s prone to gaps and delays', 'care coordination specialty, hospital readmission focus, multiple provider relationships, transitions of care management, 22 employees managing complex workflows', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'Coordinating discharge follow-ups across 22 staff members while tracking patient compliance between hospitals and SNFs creates serious communication bottlenecks.', 'care coordination workflow overload', '22 staff, endless follow-ups', 'Most care management services with 20+ staff hit the same wall around discharge coordination. Patient follow-ups between hospitals and SNFs become a daily game of phone tag, spreadsheet updates, and hoping nothing slips through the cracks. The bigger the team, the more gaps appear in the handoffs. Even the most organized operations teams find themselves manually tracking compliance across facilities while staff juggle competing priorities.', 'why calyxr built this', 'The coordination bottleneck you\'re managing across 22 staff members is exactly why we built Calyxr. Instead of manual follow-up tracking between facilities, care teams get automated patient transition workflows that keep everyone synchronized in real-time. Heritage Healthcare reduced their discharge coordination time by 60% within the first month. Worth exploring how this might work for Complete Care Management Services?', 'Care management services typically lose 15-20 hours per week to manual coordination delays, which compounds when you\'re managing transitions across multiple facilities. That\'s roughly $40K annually just in coordination inefficiency, not counting readmission risks. Calyxr goes live in days, no long contracts required. What does your current follow-up workflow look like between hospitals and SNFs?', 'Saw Complete Care Management Services manages transitions across multiple facilities with 22 staff. The manual coordination bottlenecks you\'re probably dealing with are exactly what we solve at Calyxr. Worth a quick conversation about streamlined care transitions?', 'cost of missed handoffs', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://ccmsus.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '22', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://ccmsus.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top