(147, 30, '2026-03-18 15:09:08', 'Emergicare of Harrisonburg, Inc.', 'https://emergicares.com', 'Taeahn Cherry', 'Medical Office Manager', 'taeahn.cherry@emergicares.com', '', 'YES', 34, 'Small urgent care with 10 employees fits healthcare industry but scores poorly due to minimal size, missing technology signals, and lack of clear pain indicators. Medical Office Manager suggests operational focus but limited scaling potential.', 'Emergicare of Harrisonburg is a 20-year-established urgent care center offering walk-in services, occupational health, and diagnostic testing in Harrisonburg, VA. They provide comprehensive urgent care including on-site X-rays, lab work, and workplace health services with a team of nurse practitioners.', 'small', 'high', 'High patient volume urgent care with walk-ins creates scheduling chaos and missed patient communications leading to operational inefficiencies', 'urgent care specialty, walk-in services, small 10-person team, 20-year established practice, comprehensive services including X-rays and labs', 'medium', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'With 20 years of walk-in volume and only 10 staff, your front desk is probably drowning in eligibility checks for urgent visits.', 'billing staff overload', 'urgent care scheduling chaos', 'Many urgent care practices with high walk-in volume hit the same wall around year 20. The front desk staff who used to handle 50 patients a day are now processing 100+ with the same manual scheduling systems. Patient communications slip through cracks, eligibility checks pile up, and what used to be organized chaos becomes actual chaos. The volume growth that should be celebrated becomes the thing that breaks operations.', 'why we built calyxr', 'This scheduling chaos at high-volume urgent care practices is exactly why we created Calyxr. We handle the patient communication workflows and eligibility verification that bog down your front desk staff. One practice with similar walk-in volume freed up 15 hours per week of staff time within their first month. Your 10-person team shouldn\'t be drowning in administrative tasks when patients need care.', 'A practice your size typically loses $8,000 monthly from missed patient communications and delayed eligibility checks. Calyxr goes live in days, not months, with no long-term contracts required. Would it help to see how we\'ve streamlined operations for other urgent care practices with similar walk-in volume?', 'Hi Taeahn, noticed Emergicare has been handling high walk-in volume for 20 years with a lean team. Many urgent care practices hit operational bottlenecks around scheduling and patient communications at that scale. Worth a quick conversation about streamlining those workflows?', 'cost of missed communications', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://emergicares.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '10', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://emergicares.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'taeahn.cherry@emergicares.com', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Medical Office Manager', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(148, 31, '2026-03-19 11:50:42', 'Emergency Medicine Physicians', 'https://emp.com', 'Tim Bowman', 'CFO', 'tbowman@emp.com', '', 'YES', 45, 'Emergency Medicine practice with 830 employees indicates significant scale and billing volume, but lacks specific billing pain signals and technology stack visibility.', 'Emergency Medicine Physicians (EMP) is a large emergency medicine group practice and USACS co-founder operating across 23+ states with 830+ employees, providing comprehensive emergency department management and related hospital-based services.', 'large', 'high', 'Managing massive claim volumes across 23+ states with complex emergency billing requirements, multiple insurance networks, and high denial rates typical of emergency medicine', 'multi-state operations, emergency medicine specialty, 830+ employees, hospital-based services, complex emergency billing codes, likely high claim volumes, multi-location coordination challenges', 'high', 'Economic Buyer', 'high', 'Managing emergency billing compliance across 23 states means your team is juggling dozens of different payer portals for claim status updates daily.', 'manual portal time', '23 states of payer portals', 'Managing emergency billing compliance across 23 states means your team is juggling dozens of different payer portals for claim status updates daily. Each state has different networks, different portal layouts, different login requirements. Emergency Medicine Physicians with 830+ employees likely has billing staff spending hours each day just checking claim status across multiple systems. The manual portal-hopping for 276/277 inquiries becomes a full-time job when you\'re processing emergency claims at this volume.', 'why calyxr reached out', 'The reason Calyxr is writing is because emergency medicine groups tell us payer portal management is killing their billing efficiency. Calyxr automates claim status checking across all major payers, eliminating the need for your team to log into dozens of differ