(159, 33, '2026-03-19 13:40:39', 'Collier Urgent Care Centers', 'https://collierurgentcare.com', 'Christine Murphy-Jones', 'Office Manager', 'cmurphy@collierurgentcare.com', '', 'YES', 32, 'Strong industry fit (urgent care) with 28 employees in sweet spot range, but Office Manager persona has limited decision-making authority and lacks clear technology/pain signals for higher scoring.', 'Collier Urgent Care Centers operates 3 walk-in urgent care locations in Naples, Florida, staffed by board-certified physicians, advanced practitioners, and registered nurses, serving patients 7 days a week with on-site diagnostic services.', 'mid-size', 'high', 'High walk-in volume across 3 locations creates massive patient communication chaos with missed callbacks, appointment confusion, and no-show coordination challenges', 'urgent care specialty, 3 locations, walk-in model, 7-day operations, 28 employees managing high patient turnover', 'medium', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'Managing callback queues and appointment coordination across three Naples locations with 28 staff must create constant communication bottlenecks.', 'multi-location communication chaos', '3 locations, endless callbacks', 'Managing callback queues across three Naples locations with 28 staff creates communication bottlenecks that never seem to end. High walk-in volume means patients get mixed messages about appointments, callbacks fall through cracks, and no-shows happen because coordination breaks down between locations. Many urgent care operations with multiple sites face this same challenge, where growth actually makes patient communication harder instead of smoother.', 'why we built calyxr', 'The communication chaos across multiple urgent care locations is exactly why we built Calyxr. Our platform centralizes patient communication so callbacks, appointments, and no-show coordination work seamlessly across all your locations with one unified system. One 4-location urgent care group in Texas reduced missed callbacks by 89% in their first month using our centralized queue management.', 'Each missed callback costs urgent care centers an average of $247 in lost revenue, and coordination failures between locations multiply that impact. With your 28 staff across three Naples locations, even small communication improvements add up quickly. Would it make sense to see how other multi-location urgent cares handle this without long contracts or complex implementations?', 'Christine, noticed Collier Urgent Care\'s growth to 3 locations. Managing patient callbacks and appointment coordination across multiple sites with 28 staff must create daily communication challenges. Mind if I connect to share how other urgent care groups solve this?', '28 staff, 3 locations', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://collierurgentcare.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '28', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://collierurgentcare.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'cmurphy@collierurgentcare.com', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Office Manager', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(160, 33, '2026-03-19 13:41:20', 'Immediate Medical Care MD', '', 'Juan Arbelaez', 'Office Manager', 'jarbelaez@immediatemedicalcaremd.com', '', 'YES', 23, 'Small urgent care practice with 6 employees fits healthcare industry but lacks decision-maker seniority and key firmographic signals. Office Manager role suggests operational focus but limited authority for software purchasing decisions.', 'Immediate Medical Care MD is a small urgent care practice with 6 employees providing immediate medical services for non-emergency conditions. The practice likely handles walk-in patients with acute but non-critical medical needs.', 'small', 'medium', 'High walk-in patient volume with only 6 staff creates scheduling chaos and missed appointment opportunities while patients wait for immediate care.', 'urgent care walk-ins, small 6-person staff, immediate service model, non-emergency acute care', 'medium', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'Six-person urgent care handling walk-ins means your front desk is constantly juggling phone calls while patients are standing right there waiting.', 'staff overwhelm / missed revenue opportunities', '6 staff, endless walk-ins', 'Most urgent care practices with small teams face the same impossible choice. Answer the ringing phone and risk losing the walk-in patient standing at your desk, or help the person in front of you and miss potential appointments. Six staff members trying to manage both streams means someone always gets overlooked. The phone rings, patients wait longer, and scheduling opportunities slip through the cracks daily.', 'why we built calyxr', 'That scheduling chaos at Immediate Medical Care MD is exactly why we built Calyxr. Our platform handles walk-in flow and phone scheduling simultaneously, so your front desk never has to choose between the patient at the counter and the caller on hold. One practice with similar staffing saw their missed appointment opportunities drop 67% in the first month after going live.', 'Quick math on those missed scheduling opportunities: if your team misses just 3 appointments daily at $200 average, that\'s $156,000 in lost revenue yearly. Calyxr typically pays for itself within 60 days, no long contracts required, and practices go live within a week. Worth exploring how this might work for a 6-person operation like yours?', 'Hey Juan, noticed Immediate Medical Care MD is handling high walk-in volume with a lean team. That front desk juggling act between walk-ins and phone calls is brutal. Mind if I share how similar practices solved this?', 'cost of missed appointments', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '6', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'jarbelaez@immediatemedicalcaremd.com', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Office Manager', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(161, 33, '2026-03-19 13:41:57', 'MEDSAVE CLINIC', 'https://medsaveclinics.com', 'Briar Qadir', 'Office Manager', 'briar.q@medsaveclinics.com', '', 'YES', 20, 'Small healthcare clinic with 18 employees fits industry requirements but has limited decision-making authority with Office Manager contact and missing key fit signals.', 'MEDSAVE CLINIC appears to be a healthcare practice with 18 employees in the hospital & health care industry, though specific operational details are limited due to website access restrictions.', 'small', 'medium', 'With 18 employees and limited operational visibility, likely struggling with manual insurance eligibility verification and claim status tracking across multiple staff members', 'mid-sized practice, healthcare industry, limited operational transparency, likely multi-provider setup', 'medium', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'With 18 staff members, your eligibility verification workload likely creates bottlenecks when multiple team members are checking the same patient benefits.', 'staff coordination inefficiency', '18 staff checking eligibility', 'Most clinics with 18+ staff members hit the same operational bottleneck. Multiple team members end up checking eligibility for the same patients, creating duplicate work and coverage gaps. The larger the team, the more coordination breaks down. Even with good intentions, someone always ends up re-verifying benefits that were already checked an hour earlier.', 'why I\'m reaching out', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr eliminates duplicate eligibility work across your entire team. Instead of 18 people manually checking benefits, our platform centralizes verification so everyone sees real-time status updates. One of our clients with 22 staff cut their eligibility workload by 60% in the first month.', 'If each of your 18 team members spends just 10 minutes daily on redundant eligibility checks, that\'s 3 hours of wasted labor every day. Over a year, you\'re looking at nearly $25,000 in duplicate work costs. Would it make sense to see how other practices with similar team sizes handle this coordination challenge?', 'Noticed MEDSAVE has 18 team members. Most practices that size struggle with duplicate eligibility verification work across staff. Mind if I share how similar clinics solved this coordination issue?', '18 people, 18x the waste', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://medsaveclinics.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '18', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://medsaveclinics.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'briar.q@medsaveclinics.com', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Office Manager', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(162, 33, '2026-03-19 13:42:29', 'MercyCare Community Physicians', '', 'Heather Bonner', 'Office Manager', 'hbonner@mercycare.org', '', 'YES', 22, 'Strong industry match with proper employee size, but Office Manager title lacks decision-making authority and missing geographic/technology signals significantly limit the score.', 'MercyCare Community Physicians is a mid-size healthcare organization with 45 employees serving community-based patients across multiple service lines. As a community-focused practice, they likely handle diverse patient populations with varying insurance coverage and administrative complexity.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'Managing complex insurance verification and claims processing across multiple specialties with limited billing staff relative to patient volume', 'multi-specialty practice, community-focused diverse patient mix, 45 employees suggesting high patient-to-staff ratio, varied insurance coverage complexity', 'high', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'With 45 staff managing multiple specialties, your billing team is probably drowning in insurance eligibility checks across different payer networks.', 'billing staff overload', 'eligibility checks drowning teams', 'Most multi-specialty practices with 45+ staff hit a breaking point where insurance eligibility checks consume entire days. Different payer networks, varying requirements per specialty, and limited billing staff create a perfect storm. The manual verification process that worked at smaller volumes becomes impossible to sustain as patient loads grow.', 'why I\'m writing today', 'Writing because Calyxr helps practices like MercyCare streamline insurance verification across multiple specialties and payer networks. Instead of your billing team spending hours on manual eligibility checks, our platform handles the verification process automatically. One of our multi-specialty clients reduced their verification time by 80% in the first month.', 'Every hour spent on manual insurance verification c