(164, 33, '2026-03-19 13:43:50', 'Paoli Family Medicine', 'https://paolifamilymedicine.com', 'Connie Legge', 'Office Manager', 'connie.legge@paolifamilymedicine.com', '', 'YES', 44, 'Small practice with 27 employees matches target size range and healthcare industry. Office Manager indicates operational focus but lacks senior decision-making authority typical for larger deals.', 'Paoli Family Medicine is a single-location family practice with 7 physicians and 4 nurse practitioners serving families in Paoli, PA. The practice has 27 employees and explicitly does not accept Medicaid, suggesting they focus on commercial insurance patients.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'With 27 employees managing a busy 11-provider family practice, your billing team is likely overwhelmed with manual insurance eligibility checks and payer portal logins across multiple commercial insurers', 'large provider-to-staff ratio (11 providers, 27 total staff), family medicine high-volume scheduling, commercial insurance focus requires constant eligibility verification, single location with high patient throughput', 'high', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'With 11 providers and zero Medicaid patients, your team is juggling eligibility checks across dozens of commercial payer portals daily.', 'billing staff overload', '11 providers, dozens of portals', 'Managing eligibility checks across dozens of commercial payer portals with 11 providers must feel like a full-time job in itself. Most practices with your patient volume find their billing team spending 3-4 hours daily just logging into different portals to verify coverage. The constant portal switching, password resets, and manual data entry creates a bottleneck that pushes collections further out.', 'why I\'m writing about eligibility', 'Writing because Calyxr eliminates the portal juggling act for busy family practices. Instead of your team logging into dozens of payer portals, our platform checks eligibility across all major commercial insurers from one dashbo