(184, 33, '2026-03-19 13:56:31', 'Agenacare Urgent Care', 'https://agenacare.com', 'Amanda Belcher', 'Practice Manager', 'amanda@agenacare.com', '', 'YES', 36, 'Small urgent care practice (10 employees) with Practice Manager contact fits industry but lacks scale indicators. Missing location, revenue, and technology signals limit scoring potential.', 'Agenacare Urgent Care is a walk-in urgent care clinic providing treatment for low to moderately acute injuries and illnesses, with a new Salem location opening soon and specialized wound care services.', 'small', 'medium', 'High patient volume walk-in urgent care with only 10 employees likely struggling with patient communication, scheduling coordination, and insurance verification for immediate care needs', 'walk-in urgent care model, high patient turnover, small staff size relative to patient volume, immediate care requirements, expanding to new location', 'high', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'With walk-in volumes at your Salem expansion, your 10-person team is likely spending significant time on insurance eligibility checks for urgent visits.', 'staff overload on real-time insurance verification', 'salem walk-ins and insurance delays', 'Most urgent care practices with high walk-in volumes hit the same bottleneck. Patients arrive needing immediate care, but insurance verification takes 15-20 minutes per visit. With only 10 staff members handling everything from check-in to clinical support, those verification delays create waiting room backup and patient frustration. The busier the location gets, the worse this cycle becomes.', 'why calyxr built instant verification', 'Amanda, this insurance verification bottleneck is exactly why we built Calyxr for urgent care practices. Our platform verifies patient eligibility in under 30 seconds, even for walk-ins, so your front desk can focus on patient flow instead of phone calls with insurance companies. One urgent care group reduced their average check-in time from 18 minutes to 4 