(194, 33, '2026-03-19 14:03:59', 'Valley Urgent Care & Occupational Medicine', 'https://valleyurgentcareva.com', 'Anna Williams', 'Practice Manager', 'anna.williams@valleyurgentcareva.com', '', 'YES', 42, 'Strong industry fit (urgent care) with 21 employees in target range, but lack of senior decision-maker and missing technology/pain signals limit the score to partial fit tier.', 'Valley Urgent Care & Occupational Medicine appears to be a mid-sized urgent care practice with occupational medicine services, employing 21 staff members in the healthcare sector.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'High patient volume urgent care with occupational medicine complexity creates scheduling chaos and insurance verification bottlenecks with limited staff resources', 'urgent care specialty, occupational medicine complexity, mid-size practice 21 employees, high patient turnover, workers comp insurance challenges, scheduling demands', 'high', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'With 21 staff handling both walk-in urgent care and scheduled occupational medicine, your insurance verification team is likely drowning in workers comp pre-auths.', 'insurance verification bottlenecks with workers comp complexity', 'insurance verification chaos', 'Most urgent care practices handling occupational medicine hit the same wall around 20+ staff. Walk-ins need immediate attention, but workers comp pre-auths pile up behind scheduled occ med appointments. The insurance verification team ends up playing constant catch-up, and patient flow suffers on both sides.', 'why i\'m writing', 'Anna, I\'m reaching out because Calyxr helps urgent care practices like Valley handle mixed patient types without the verification bottlenecks. Our platform separates urgent care flow from occupational medicine scheduling, so your team can verify workers comp coverage in advance instead of scrambling during patient visits. One practice in Virginia cut their verification delays by 60% in the first month.', 'When verification delays stack up, each hour of staff overtime costs more than most practices realize. One 25-person urgent care calculated they were losing $180k annually just from verification inefficiencies. Calyxr deploys in days, no long contracts required. Worth exploring how this would look at Valley?', 'Anna, noticed Valley handles both urgent care and occ med with your current team size. The insurance verification juggling act between walk-ins and workers comp is brutal. Mind if I share how similar practices solved this?', 'the real cost', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://valleyurgentcareva.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '21', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://valleyurgentcareva.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'anna.williams@valleyurgentcareva.com', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Practice Manager', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(195, 33, '2026-03-19 14:04:49', 'Walking Urgent Care', 'https://walkinmedicine.com', 'Stephanie Reid', 'Practice Manager', 'stephanie-reid@walkinmedicine.com', '', 'YES', 27, 'Small urgent care practice with 14 employees shows strong industry fit but limited scale. Practice Manager is a viable persona for operational decisions in smaller practices.', 'Walking Urgent Care is a single-location urgent care clinic in Coral Springs, FL serving patients of all ages with walk-in services, minor injuries, illnesses, and routine care. The practice operates 7 days a week and accepts a wide variety of insurance plans.', 'small', 'high', 'High patient volume with walk-in model creates constant phone interruptions, no-shows for follow-ups, and missed communication with patients about results or care instructions', 'walk-in urgent care model, open 7 days a week, accepts wide variety of insurance plans, single location with 14 staff, serves all ages', 'medium', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'With 14 staff handling daily walk-ins plus follow-up coordination, your front desk is probably fielding dozens of lab result and care instruction calls.', 'staff communication overload', '14 staff, endless phone calls', 'Most walk-in clinics with 14+ staff see the same pattern. High patient volume means constant phone interruptions about lab results, care instructions, and follow-up questions. The front desk becomes a bottleneck, and important patient communications get delayed or missed entirely. Many practices find their staff spending more time answering phones than helping patients in front of them.', 'why I\'m writing about Walking Urgent Care', 'Stephanie, I\'m reaching out because Calyxr helps urgent care practices reduce phone volume by automatically handling patient result notifications and care instructions. Instead of your 14 staff fielding dozens of these calls daily, patients get secure, instant access to their information. One similar walk-in clinic cut their phone interruptions by 60% in the first month.', 'Quick math: if your front desk spends just 2 hours daily on result and instruction calls, that\'s 10+ hours weekly that could go toward patient care. Most practices see immediate relief within days of setup, no long contracts required. Worth exploring what those reclaimed hours could mean for Walking Urgent Care?', 'Hi Stephanie, I help urgent care practices like Walking Urgent Care reduce constant phone interruptions about lab results and care instructions. Worth a quick conversation about what this could mean for your 14-person team?', 'cost of those phone interruptions', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://walkinmedicine.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '14', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://walkinmedicine.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'stephanie-reid@walkinmedicine.com', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Practice Manager', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(196, 33, '2026-03-19 14:05:31', 'Winfield Family Medicine', 'https://winfieldfamilymedicine.com', 'Debbie Aguilera', 'Practice Manager', 'daguilera@winfieldfamilymedicine.com', '', 'YES', 49, 'Small family medicine practice with Practice Manager as decision-maker shows operational fit, but missing key data on geography, EHR usage, and pain signals limits scoring potential.', 'Winfield Family Medicine is a family practice with 16 employees, indicating a mid-size operation that likely serves a broad patient population with primary care services.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'With 16 staff managing diverse family medicine patients across all ages and insurance types, manual scheduling coordination and insurance verification creates daily bottlenecks', 'family medicine practice, 16-person team size, broad patient demographics, multiple insurance types, primary care complexity', 'medium', 'Gatekeeper', 'medium', 'With 16 staff coordinating care across pediatric through geriatric patients, your team likely spends hours daily on insurance eligibility calls.', 'staff time drain on verification tasks', '16 staff, endless insurance calls', 'Family medicine practices with 16+ staff often find themselves in a daily cycle of insurance verification calls. Pediatric visits need different authorizations than geriatric care, and each insurance plan has its own maze of requirements. Many practice managers report their teams spend 3-4 hours daily just confirming patient eligibility before appointments. The larger the staff, the more coordination headaches multiply.', 'why I\'m reaching out', 'Debbie, I\'m writing because Calyxr helps family medicine practices eliminate those daily insurance verification bottlenecks. Our platform handles real-time eligibility checks across all insurance types, from pediatric to geriatric patients, so your 16 staff members can focus on patient care instead of phone calls. One practice manager told us it freed up 20 hours per week across her team.', 'If your