(202, 33, '2026-03-19 14:10:20', 'Emergicare of Harrisonburg', 'https://emergicares.com', 'Stephen Valentine', 'Vice President of Operations & Marketing', 'stephen.valentine@emergicares.com', '', 'YES', 44, 'Strong persona fit with VP of Operations title (14 pts) and healthcare industry match (8 pts), but limited by small size (10 employees) and lack of technology/pain signals.', 'Emergicare of Harrisonburg is a 20-year established urgent care clinic offering walk-in medical services, diagnostic testing, occupational health services, and wellness/beauty treatments in Virginia.', 'small', 'medium', 'Urgent care\'s high patient volume with unpredictable walk-in flow creates missed calls, scheduling chaos, and manual patient intake bottlenecks with only 10 staff members', 'urgent care specialty, walk-in patients, small 10-person team, high patient turnover, unpredictable volume, manual intake processes', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 10 staff handling unpredictable walk-in volumes over 20 years, your front desk likely drowns in eligibility checks during peak hours.', 'billing staff overload', '10 staff, unpredictable walk-ins', 'Most urgent care centers with 10 staff face the same pattern during peak hours. Walk-ins surge unpredictably, phones ring nonstop, and front desk staff get buried juggling eligibility checks while patients wait. The bottleneck always happens at intake when volume spikes hit small teams hardest. Many practices watch revenue walk out the door during these rushes.', 'why I\'m reaching out', 'Stephen, I\'m writing because Calyxr helps urgent care centers handle unpredictable walk-in surges without drowning small teams in manual work. Instead of staff juggling phones and eligibility checks during peak hours, our platform streamlines patient intake so your 10-person team can focus on care. Genesis Healthcare reduced their front desk workload by 60% in the first month.', 'Quick question Stephen. If peak hour chaos causes your team to miss just 5 patient calls daily, that\'s roughly $180,000 in lost annual revenue for urgent care. Most practices see results within days of going live, no long contracts required. Worth exploring what streamlined intake could mean for Emergicare\'s walk-in flow?', 'Stephen, noticed Emergicare\'s been growing over 20 years. Curious how you handle those unpredictable walk-in surges with your current team size. Most urgent care centers struggle with the intake bottleneck during peak hours.', 'the math on missed revenue', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://emergicares.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '10', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://emergicares.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'stephen.valentine@emergicares.com', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Vice President of Operations & Marketing', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(203, 33, '2026-03-19 14:11:02', 'Protocol', 'https://protocol.us', 'Susanna Wiborg', 'Vice President Operations', 'susanna@protocol.us', '', 'YES', 34, 'VP Operations title is strong persona fit, but very small team size (13 employees) and lack of technology/pain signals significantly limit the opportunity.', 'Protocol is a boutique longevity-focused primary care practice targeting high-performing individuals with comprehensive health optimization services including advanced testing, personalized care plans, and ongoing health advisory services.', 'small', 'medium', 'Manual patient communication and workflow coordination across comprehensive longevity services is overwhelming a small 13-person team managing high-touch, personalized care for demanding clientele.', 'boutique practice with high-touch services, small team managing comprehensive care plans, advanced testing coordination, ongoing advisory services, high-performing demanding clientele', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'Managing comprehensive longevity protocols for high-performing clients with just 13 staff likely means your ops team spends hours coordinating multi-step testing sequences and follow-ups.', 'small team operational overload', '13 people, endless coordination', 'Most longevity practices with small teams hit the same wall around patient volume. Managing comprehensive testing sequences and follow-ups starts consuming entire days when every client expects white-glove service. The coordination alone between multi-step protocols becomes a full-time job for multiple people.', 'why I\'m writing', 'I\'m reaching out because Calyxr handles the workflow coordination that\'s eating up your team\'s time. Instead of manually tracking testing sequences and follow-ups, everything runs automatically while maintaining that personalized touch your clients expect. One longevity practice cut their coordination time by 70% in the first month.', 'If your 13-person team spends even 2 hours daily on manual coordination, that\'s $150K+ annually in lost productivity. Most practices see immediate relief within days of setup, no long contracts required. Would it help to see how this looks for a practice your size?', 'Noticed Protocol\'s comprehensive longevity approach. Managing multi-step testing protocols with a lean team creates some unique coordination challenges. Mind if I connect and share how similar practices handle this?', 'the math on coordination time', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://protocol.us) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '13', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://protocol.us) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'susanna@protocol.us', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Vice President Operations', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
