(216, 34, '2026-03-20 09:29:03', 'Watchung Pediatrics', 'Watchung Pediatrics', 'Sandy Shamy', 'Billing Specialist', 'sshamy@watchungpediatrics.com', '', 'NO', 23, 'Pediatric specialty match is strong, but Billing Specialist lacks decision-making authority and 7-person practice likely falls below minimum viable contract threshold.', 'Watchung Pediatrics appears to be a small general pediatric practice with 7 employees, likely serving families in the Watchung, NJ area with standard pediatric services and facing typical small practice billing challenges.', 'small', 'medium', 'Small 7-person pediatric practice likely has 1-2 billing staff managing high-volume well-child visits and Medicaid claims, creating severe bandwidth constraints for timely claim status follow-up', '7 total employees, general pediatrics specialty, small practice size relative to pediatric visit volume, likely high Medicaid/CHIP mix typical for pediatrics', 'high', 'Influencer', 'low', 'With 7 total staff, your billing specialist is probably spending 2+ hours daily on Medicaid hold times for well-child claim statuses.', 'billing staff to patient volume ratio creating Medicaid follow-up bottleneck', 'medicaid hold times at pediatric practices', 'Sandy, many pediatric billing teams are spending 2+ hours daily on Medicaid and CHIP hold times just to track claim statuses for routine well-child visits. With smaller practice teams, that means one person carrying most of the manual claim follow-up workload. The hold times for pediatric payers seem to get longer every quarter, but the reimbursement timelines stay the same.', 'claim status without phone calls', 'Sandy, that\'s actually why I\'m writing about Calyxr\'s Claim Status Agent. It automates 276/277 claim status requests for pediatric practices, so your team gets real-time claim updates without ever logging into payer portals or sitting on hold. When denials happen, they surface automatically in your system. One of our pediatric practices reduced manual billing tasks by 70% within the first month.', 'Sandy, if your billing team is spending 2+ hours daily on Medicaid hold times, that\'s roughly 520 hours per year just chasing claim statuses. At $25/hour, that\'s over $13k in labor costs for something that could happen automatically. Would be happy to show you how the Claim Status Agent works for pediatric practices. No long contracts, live in days, no IT lift required. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at Watchung Pediatrics?', 'Sandy, noticed Watchung Pediatrics has a smaller team managing high-volume Medicaid claims. Many pediatric billing specialists are spending hours daily on payer hold times just for claim status. Is that still a manual process at your practice?', '2 hours daily on hold', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (Watchung Pediatrics) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '7', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (Watchung Pediatrics) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'sshamy@watchungpediatrics.com', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Billing Specialist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
