(218, 34, '2026-03-20 09:29:12', 'SperoMD', 'SperoMD', 'Sarah Gueho', 'Certified Medical Coder', 'sgueho@speromd.com', '', 'Skipped', 8, 'ICP score 8 is below the threshold of 15. General hospital & health care organization with 25 employees but no pediatric specialty indicators and contact is a certified medical coder with no decision-making authority for RCM purchases.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(219, 34, '2026-03-20 09:29:46', 'Spark Pediatrics', 'Spark Pediatrics', 'Denise Ling', 'Sr Director of Revenue Cycle', 'denisel@sparkpediatrics.com', '', 'YES', 53, 'Strong persona fit with Sr Director of Revenue Cycle at pediatric practice with optimal size (49 employees). Missing geography and technology signals limit tier placement despite excellent decision-maker alignment.', 'Spark Pediatrics appears to be a mid-size pediatric practice with 49 employees, suggesting multiple providers and locations with significant billing volume requiring structured claim status management.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'With 49 employees across multiple locations, their billing team likely lacks centralized visibility into claim status across all sites, leading to inconsistent follow-up and delayed collections.', '49 employees indicating multi-location practice, high pediatric visit volume requiring structured claim management, lack of centralized claim visibility across sites', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 49 employees across multiple locations, your billing team probably burns hours each week logging into different Medicaid portals per site.', 'multi-location Medicaid portal management inefficiency', 'medicaid portals per location', 'Multi-location pediatric practices face a unique billing challenge that single-site practices never see. Each location often requires separate Medicaid and CHIP portal access for claim status checks. Many billing teams at practices like Spark Pediatrics end up with different staff managing different portals, or one person juggling multiple logins daily. The result is inconsistent follow-up timing and claims that slip through the cracks between locations.', 'centralized claim tracking', 'The reason for reaching out is Calyxr\'s Claim Status Agent, which handles 276/277 inquiries automatically across all your locations from a single dashboard. Instead of logging into separate Medicaid portals per site, your billing team gets real-time claim status updates centrally. One pediatric practice reduced manual billing tasks by 70% within their first month. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process across your locations?', 'Quick math on multi-location claim status follow-up: if your billing staff spend 2 hours per day across different Medicaid portals, that\'s 10 hours weekly at roughly $25/hour, or $13,000 annually in labor costs just for claim status checks. Worth seeing how automated 276/277 inquiries work across multiple locations with no long contracts, live in days, and no IT lift required. Is centralized claim tracking something you\'d want to see in action?', 'Hi Denise, noticed Spark Pediatrics has multiple locations. Multi-site pediatric billing teams often juggle different Medicaid portals for claim status, burning hours daily. Worth a quick conversation about centralized claim tracking?', 'hours lost to portal juggling', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (Spark Pediatrics) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '49', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (Spark Pediatrics) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'denisel@sparkpediatrics.com', '', '', '', 'individual & family services', '', '', '', '', '', 'Sr Director of Revenue Cycle', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
