(227, 34, '2026-03-20 09:30:22', 'Bellaire ER', 'Bellaire ER', 'Branddi Chaney', 'Medical Billing and Collection Specialist', 'b.chaney@bellaireer.com', '', 'Skipped', 0, 'ICP score 0 is below the threshold of 15. Bellaire ER is an emergency room facility, not a pediatric practice, making it outside our target specialty for claim status automation in pediatric billing workflows.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(228, 34, '2026-03-20 09:30:56', 'New England Pediatrics', 'New England Pediatrics', 'Michelle Isla', 'Medical Biller', 'isla@nepeds.com', '', 'YES', 41, 'Small New England pediatric practice with Medical Biller indicates active insurance billing operations and likely Medicaid volume. Limited data but pediatric specialty is strong match for claim status automation.', 'New England Pediatrics is a mid-size general pediatric practice with 14 employees serving the New England region, likely handling standard pediatric services with mixed payer complexity including Medicaid programs common in northeastern states.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'Small billing team is overwhelmed managing claim status across multiple northeastern state Medicaid programs with varying requirements and high hold times', '14-person practice indicates 2-3 billing staff maximum, northeastern region has complex multi-state Medicaid landscape, general pediatrics means high Medicaid/CHIP volume, mid-size practice lacks economies of scale for dedicated payer specialists', 'high', 'Influencer', 'low', 'With 14 staff managing multiple northeastern state Medicaid programs, your billing team likely spends hours daily on hold with different state systems.', 'Multi-state Medicaid complexity with small team bandwidth', 'northeastern state medicaid hold times', 'Many pediatric billing teams across New England are spending hours daily on hold with different state Medicaid programs, each with their own claim status requirements. Massachusetts MassHealth, Vermont Medicaid, New Hampshire DHHS, each system operates differently with varying hold times that can stretch 20-45 minutes per call. For practices managing multiple northeastern states, billing staff often spend more time waiting on hold than actually processing claims.', 'automated claim status tracking', 'Michelle, I\'m writing because Calyxr built something specifically for this problem. Our Claim Status Agent automatically pulls 276/277 transaction data from all northeastern state Medicaid programs without any manual portal logins or phone calls. One pediatric practice in Massachusetts saw their billing team reduce manual claim status tasks by 70% within the first month. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at New England Pediatrics?', 'If your billing team spends 3 hours daily on Medicaid hold time across northeastern states, that\'s roughly $45,000 annually in lost productivity for a 14-person practice. Those hours could be spent on higher-value revenue cycle work instead of waiting for claim status updates. I\'d like to show you how our system eliminates payer hold time entirely, no long contracts required and you\'re live in days with no IT lift. Worth a quick look?', 'Hi Michelle, noticed New England Pediatrics works across multiple northeastern Medicaid programs. Many pediatric billing teams tell us they spend hours daily on hold with different state systems just for claim status. Is that still a manual process at your practice?', 'cost of payer hold time', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (New England Pediatrics) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '14', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (New England Pediatrics) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'isla@nepeds.com', '', '', '', 'hospital & health care', '', '', '', '', '', 'Medical Biller', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
