(256, 34, '2026-03-20 09:35:27', 'Argyle Pediatrics', 'Argyle Pediatrics', 'Kelsie Santos', 'Billing Director', 'ksantos@argyle-pediatrics.com', '', 'YES', 41, 'Small 6-person pediatric practice with dedicated Billing Director suggests manual claim status workflow burden. Pediatrics typically carries high Medicaid/CHIP volume requiring frequent payer follow-up.', 'Argyle Pediatrics is a small general pediatric practice with approximately 6 employees, likely handling standard pediatric services with basic billing operations and mixed payer environment typical of pediatric practices.', 'small', 'medium', 'With only 6 total employees, this pediatric practice likely has 1-2 billing staff managing high-volume pediatric claims across multiple payers, creating severe bandwidth constraints for claim status follow-up.', '6 total employees indicating minimal billing staff, general pediatrics with high visit volume from well-child visits and vaccines, small practice size with limited administrative resources', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 6 total employees, your billing team is probably spending 4+ hours daily on Medicaid hold times alone.', 'billing staff to volume ratio creating unsustainable claim follow-up workload', 'medicaid hold times', 'Kelsie, many pediatric billing directors at 6-person practices tell me their staff spends 4+ hours daily on Medicaid and CHIP hold times just to check claim status. With only 1-2 billers handling the entire patient population, those hours add up fast. The manual payer portal logins for claim tracking create an endless cycle that keeps billing staff reactive instead of focusing on denials and collections.', 'claim status without hold time', 'Kelsie, that\'s why I\'m writing about Calyxr\'s Claim Status Agent. It handles all 276/277 claim status requests automatically, so your billing team never logs into payer portals or sits on hold again. Denials surface in real-time without manual checking. One pediatric practice reduced their manual billing tasks by 70% in the first month.', 'Kelsie, if your billing staff spends 4+ hours daily on Medicaid hold times, that\'s over $40,000 annually just in labor costs for claim status follow-up. At some point, those hours need to go toward collections and denials instead. I\'d like to show you how the Claim Status Agent works, no long contracts and you\'re live in days with no IT lift required. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at Argyle Pediatrics?', 'Hi Kelsie, noticed Argyle Pediatrics has a small team handling pediatric billing. Many 6-person practices tell me their staff spends hours daily on Medicaid hold times for claim status. Is that still a manual process at your practice?', '4 hours daily on hold', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (Argyle Pediatrics) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '6', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (Argyle Pediatrics) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'ksantos@argyle-pediatrics.com', '', '', '', 'medical practice', '', '', '', '', '', 'Billing Director', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(257, 34, '2026-03-20 09:36:03', 'COMPASSION PEDIATRICS', 'COMPASSION PEDIATRICS', 'April Haskin', 'Medical Billing Specialist', 'ahaskin@compassionpediatrics.com', '', 'NO', 23, 'Strong pediatric specialty match with good employee size, but Medical Billing Specialist lacks decision-making authority for RCM platform purchases at this level.', 'Compassion Pediatrics is a mid-size general pediatric practice with 30 employees, likely serving a diverse patient population with standard pediatric services and facing typical multi-payer claim status challenges.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'Mid-size pediatric practice with 30 employees likely has 3-5 billing staff managing high-volume Medicaid/CHIP claims across multiple payers, creating significant staff hold time burden and manual portal login overhead.', '30 employees indicating mid-size practice, general pediatrics with high Medicaid/CHIP volume typical for pediatric specialty, likely 3-5 billing staff ratio insufficient for claim volume, multiple payer complexity inherent in pediatric patient mix', 'medium', 'Influencer', 'low', 'With 30 staff, your billing team is likely spending 8+ hours weekly on Medicaid hold times alone across multiple state programs.', 'billing staff to volume ratio creating disproportionate hold time cost', 'medicaid hold times', 'April, with 30 staff at Compassion Pediatrics, your billing team is likely spending 8+ hours weekly on Medicaid hold times alone across multiple state programs. Most pediatric practices this size have 3-5 billing specialists rotating between payer portals and phone queues, burning through productive hours that could go toward actual claim resolution. The manual claim status chase seems to hit pediatric billing harder than other specialties since Medicaid and CHIP carry the longest hold times of any payer category.', 'automated claim status', 'April, that\'s why I\'m reaching out about Calyxr\'s Claim Status Agent. Instead of your billing team logging into multiple Medicaid portals or sitting on hold, our system runs automated 276/277 transactions and surfaces claim status in real-time. Pediatric practices see a 70% reduction in manual billing tasks since denials and status updates appear automatically without phone calls. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at Compassion Pediatrics?', 'April, if your 4 billing specialists are each spending 2 hours weekly on hold with Medicaid payers, that\'s 416 hours annually at $25/hour, costing around $10,400 in staff time alone. That doesn\'t include the opportunity cost of delayed reimbursement from manual claim tracking. Worth seeing how automated claim status could recover those hours, no long contracts, live in days, no IT lift required. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at your practice?', 'April, noticed Compassion Pediatrics has 30 staff, so your billing team likely spends significant hours on Medicaid hold times chasing claim status. Most pediatric practices this size see 8+ hours weekly just on payer phone queues. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at your practice?', 'billing staff hours', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (COMPASSION PEDIATRICS) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '30', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (COMPASSION PEDIATRICS) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'ahaskin@compassionpediatrics.com', '', '', '', 'medical practice', '', '', '', '', '', 'Medical Billing Specialist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(258, 34, '2026-03-20 09:36:39', 'Florida Pediatric Associates', 'Florida Pediatric Associates', 'Terri Miehl', 'Director, Revenue Cycle Management', 'tmiehl@floridapediatrics.com', '', 'YES', 71, 'Perfect pediatric specialty match with ideal RCM Director title and employee count in sweet spot. Florida location strengthens fit for high-volume claim status automation.', 'Florida Pediatric Associates is a multi-provider pediatric practice with 23 employees, suggesting a mid-sized operation likely serving multiple locations across Florida with standard pediatric billing complexity involving mixed payer environments.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'Multi-location pediatric practice with 23 employees likely has billing staff manually checking claim status across multiple payer portals for high Medicaid/CHIP volume without centralized visibility', 'multi-location practice, 23 employees suggests 2-4 billing staff, pediatric specialty with high Medicaid/CHIP volume, Florida market with complex payer mix', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 23 staff across multiple Florida locations, your billing team is likely spending hours daily navigating separate Medicaid and CHIP portals for claim status.', 'Multi-location Medicaid portal inefficiency', 'medicaid portal hours', 'Terri, with 23 staff across multiple Florida locations, your billing team is likely spending hours daily navigating separate Medicaid and CHIP portals for claim status. Most pediatric practices tell us their billers spend 2-3 hours per day just waiting on hold or clicking through different payer portals to track down claim updates. The manual follow-up becomes a full-time job across locations. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at Florida Pediatric Associates?', 'automated 276/277 status', 'Terri, I\'m writing because Calyxr built a Claim Status Agent specifically for pediatric practices dealing with Medicaid and CHIP volume. It automates 276/277 transactions across all your payer portals, so your billing team never has to log in manually again. Real-time claim tracking means denials surface automatically without the hold time. Multi-location practices like yours typically see a 70% reduction in manual billing tasks. Is this something worth seeing in action at Florida Pediatric Associates?', 'Terri, quick math on the claim status follow-up at Florida Pediatric Associates. If each biller spends 15 hours weekly on manual payer portal work, that\'s likely $40,000+ annually in staff time just for claim status. Those hours could go toward collections, patient care, or reducing your AR days. Worth seeing how the Claim Status Agent eliminates the manual work, no long contracts, live in days, no IT lift required. Is this worth a quick look for your team?', 'Terri, most multi-location pediatric practices tell us their billing staff spend hours daily in Medicaid and CHIP portals chasing claim status. Calyxr automates the 276/277 process so your team never logs into payer portals again. Worth a quick look?', 'billing hours per week', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (Florida Pediatric Associates) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '23', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (Florida Pediatric Associates) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo expo