(262, 35, '2026-03-20 09:53:46', 'Capital Area Pediatrics', 'https://capitalareapediatrics.com', 'Irina Reus', 'Billing Specialist', 'ireus@capitalareapediatrics.com', '', 'YES', 35, 'Capital Area Pediatrics is a 14-employee pediatric practice with potential for high Medicaid volume, but contact is billing specialist level rather than decision-maker, limiting immediate opportunity.', 'Capital Area Pediatrics is a general pediatrics practice serving Northern Virginia with multiple locations in Ashburn and Falls Church, handling routine pediatric care including forms processing for camps/sports/schools. With 14 employees and multi-location operations, they likely manage moderate billing complexity across various payers in the VA market.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'Multi-location pediatric practice with 14 employees likely has billing staff manually logging into multiple payer portals across VA Medicaid, CHIP, and commercial payers without centralized claim status visibility', 'multi-location practice, 14 employees suggesting small billing team, Northern Virginia market with high Medicaid/CHIP volume, routine pediatric care generating high claim volume, forms processing indicating administrative burden', 'medium', 'Influencer', 'low', 'With 14 staff across Ashburn and Falls Church locations, your billing team probably burns hours daily juggling VA Medicaid portal logins for claim status checks.', 'Multi-location billing staff portal management inefficiency', 'va medicaid portal logins', 'Most billing teams at multi-location pediatric practices spend 2-3 hours daily logging into separate payer portals just to check claim status. VA Medicaid and CHIP portals are particularly time-consuming, especially when you\'re coordinating between Ashburn and Falls Church locations. That\'s before any actual follow-up work even begins.', 'claim status without portal logins', 'Irina, that\'s exactly why I\'m reaching out about Calyxr\'s Claim Status Agent. Instead of your team logging into VA Medicaid, CHIP, and commercial payer portals, our system runs automated 276/277 queries and surfaces claim status in real-time. Pediatric practices see denials automatically without any manual portal work.', 'Quick math on your current process: if your billing staff spends 15 hours weekly on payer hold time and portal logins, that\'s roughly $18,000 annually in labor costs just for claim status checks. Worth seeing how other pediatric practices eliminated that entirely? No long contracts, live in days, no IT lift required. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at Capital Area Pediatrics?', 'Hi Irina, noticed Capital Area Pediatrics has locations in Ashburn and Falls Church. Most multi-location pediatric billing teams tell us they spend hours daily in VA Medicaid and CHIP portals just checking claim status. Is that still a manual process at your practice?', '3 hours daily on hold', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://capitalareapediatrics.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '14', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://capitalareapediatrics.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (co