(263, 35, '2026-03-20 09:54:23', 'Hanover Pediatrics', 'https://hanoverpediatrics.com', 'Laura Topper', 'Billing', 'laura.topper@hanoverpediatrics.com', '', 'YES', 41, 'Hanover Pediatrics is a 13-person pediatric practice with billing personnel, indicating operational pediatric billing needs. Small team size suggests manual processes and potential for claim status automation efficiency gains.', 'Hanover Pediatrics is a single-location general pediatric practice in Wilmington, NC led by Dr. Hoke Pollock, serving families with comprehensive pediatric services including weekend availability. With 13 employees, they appear to be a well-established practice with strong local reputation but likely face typical small practice billing challenges.', 'small', 'medium', '13-person pediatric practice likely has 2-3 billing staff managing high-volume Medicaid/CHIP claims with weekend availability creating additional claim follow-up burden.', '13 total employees suggests 2-3 billing staff, single-location pediatric practice, weekend availability increases visit volume, North Carolina has high Medicaid pediatric enrollment', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 13 staff and weekend hours, your billing team is probably drowning in Monday morning Medicaid status calls from weekend visits.', 'Weekend availability creates claim follow-up bottleneck for small billing teams', 'monday morning medicaid calls', 'Many pediatric practices with weekend availability face the same Monday morning reality. Billing teams spend hours on hold with Medicaid and CHIP trying to track claim status from weekend visits while new patients keep coming through the door. The larger the practice, the more weekend volume creates this Monday bottleneck. Is this pattern familiar at Hanover Pediatrics?', 're: those medicaid hold times', 'The reason for my note about Monday morning Medicaid calls is Calyxr\'s Claim Status Agent. Instead of your billing team spending hours on payer portals and hold queues, our system