(264, 35, '2026-03-20 09:55:02', 'Excell for Life Family Care & Pediatrics', 'https://excellforlife.com', 'Susan Lackey', 'Billing Manager', 'slackey@excellforlife.com', '', 'YES', 51, 'Family Care & Pediatrics practice with dedicated Billing Manager suggests pediatric claim volume and manual billing processes that could benefit from claim status automation.', 'Excell for Life is a functional medicine practice serving Indianapolis area since 2011, offering integrative healthcare with some pediatric services but primarily focused on chronic care, anti-aging, and wellness for all ages.', 'small', 'high', 'Functional medicine billing complexities combined with mixed adult-pediatric services likely creates claim status confusion across different payer requirements and coding scenarios.', 'functional medicine specialty, mixed adult-pediatric services, integrative healthcare billing complexity, 15-person team suggests limited dedicated billing staff', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'With functional medicine codes mixed into your pediatric claims, tracking status across different payer approval timelines probably creates daily bottlenecks for your billing team.', 'Functional medicine + pediatric coding complexity creating claim status workflow confusion', 'functional medicine pediatric claims', 'Many billing teams at mixed practices find themselves caught between functional medicine\'s complex approval timelines and standard pediatric claim processing. When you\'re managing both integrative codes and routine childhood visits, claim status becomes a daily guessing game. Medicaid and CHIP already have the longest hold times in healthcare, and adding functional medicine\'s prior auth complexity means your team probably spends hours each week just trying to figure out where claims stand.', 'automated claim status tracking', 'Susan, I\'m writing because Calyxr\'s Claim Status Agent handles exactly this mixed-practice scenario. Our system automatically pulls 276/277 status updates for both your functional medicine and pediatric claims, so your team never has to log into payer portals or sit on hold. One practice similar to yours saw a 70% reduction in manual billing tasks within their first month. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at Excell for Life?', 'Quick math on what claim status follow-up costs your 15-person practice: if your billing staff spends even 5 hours per week on payer hold time, that\'s roughly $12,000 annually just in wages for status checking. The functional medicine complexity probably makes it worse. I can show you how practices eliminate those hours entirely with automated claim tracking, no long contracts, live in days, no IT lift required. Worth a quick look at how this would work for your mixed practice setup?', 'Hi Susan, many billing managers at mixed functional medicine and pediatric practices tell me claim status tracking across different payer timelines creates daily bottlenecks. Is this still a manual process at Excell for Life?', 'billing staff hold time costs', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://excellforlife.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '15', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://excellforlife.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo ex