(265, 35, '2026-03-20 09:55:43', 'Spark Pediatrics', 'https://sparkpediatrics.com', 'Kyle Peterson', 'Chief Financial Officer', 'kylep@sparkpediatrics.com', '', 'YES', 43, 'Spark Pediatrics with 49 employees fits size profile and pediatric specialty, but CFO persona is lower priority than Revenue Cycle leaders for claim status automation.', 'Spark Pediatrics operates specialized medical daycare centers (PPEC/PPECC) across Florida and Texas, serving children with complex medical conditions requiring continuous nursing care. With 14 locations and serving hundreds of children daily, they likely handle high-volume, complex Medicaid billing for medically fragile pediatric patients.', 'large', 'high', 'High-volume complex Medicaid billing across 14 locations for medically fragile children creates massive claim status tracking burden for specialized PPEC services that often face delays and denials', 'specialized PPEC/PPECC services, 14 multi-state locations, complex medical conditions requiring continuous nursing care, hundreds of daily patients, Florida and Texas Medicaid complexity, medically fragile population with high-value claims', 'high', 'Economic Buyer', 'high', 'With 14 PPEC locations serving medically fragile children, your billing team is likely drowning in Medicaid claim status calls for complex nursing services.', 'Multi-location PPEC Medicaid complexity burden', '14 ppec locations claim status', 'Medicaid claim status tracking for PPEC nursing services across multiple locations is brutal. Many pediatric billing teams at larger PPEC organizations spend 8+ hours per week per biller just waiting on hold with Medicaid portals that don\'t show real-time status for complex nursing claims. The specialized nature of medically fragile care billing makes these calls even longer, and denials often surface weeks late.', 'automated medicaid claim tracking', 'Kyle, this is exactly why we built Calyxr\'s Claim Status Agent for pediatric practices like Spark Pediatrics. Our system runs automated 276/277 queries directly with Medicaid payers, so your billing team never touches another payer portal for claim status. PPEC practices using our platform see denials surface automatically within hours instead of weeks, which is critical for complex nursing service reimbursement.', 'Quick math on what Medicaid hold time costs across 14 PPEC locations: if each biller spends 8 hours weekly chasing claim status at $25/hour, that\'s $41,600 annually per biller in lost productivity. We have something specific to show you about how PPEC practices eliminate these hours entirely with automated claim tracking, no long contracts, live in days, no IT lift required. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at Spark Pediatrics?', 'Kyle, noticed Spark Pediatrics operates 14 PPEC locations serving medically fragile children. Many multi-location PPEC practices tell us their billing teams spend hours daily on Medicaid claim status calls for complex nursing services. Is automated claim tracking something that might help at Spark?', 'claim status hold time costs', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://sparkpediatrics.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '49', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://sparkpediatrics.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Age