(287, 35, '2026-03-20 09:59:09', 'Steeplechase Pediatric Center', 'https://steeplechasepedi.com', 'Shahla Habib', 'Medical Billing Specialist', 'shabib@steeplechasepedi.com', '', 'YES', 48, '33-employee pediatric center with billing specialist indicates operational complexity and manual claim status workflows typical of pediatric practices handling high Medicaid/CHIP volumes.', 'Steeplechase Pediatric Center is a mid-sized general pediatric practice with 33 employees, suggesting a substantial patient volume and complex billing operations that likely involve significant claim status follow-up activities.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'With 33 employees serving a high-volume pediatric patient base, the billing team is likely overwhelmed chasing claim status updates across multiple Medicaid, CHIP, and commercial payers daily.', '33 employees indicating high patient volume, general pediatrics with heavy well-child and vaccination visits, mid-sized practice complexity requiring significant claim follow-up bandwidth', 'high', 'Influencer', 'low', 'With 33 staff members handling high-volume pediatric billing, your team is probably spending hours daily calling Medicaid and CHIP for claim updates.', 'Staff-to-volume ratio inefficiency with Medicaid/CHIP hold times', 'medicaid hold times', 'Many pediatric billing teams at practices with 30+ staff are finding themselves stuck on hold with Medicaid and CHIP for 20-30 minutes per claim status inquiry. With high patient volume, billing specialists often spend entire mornings just waiting for payer representatives to pick up. The manual claim tracking process eats up hours that could be spent on higher-value billing tasks. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at your practice?', 'automated claim tracking', 'Shahla, I\'m reaching out because Calyxr\'s Claim Status Agent eliminates those long Medicaid hold times entirely. Our system runs automated 276/277 transactions in real-time, so your billing team never has to log into payer portals or make phone calls for claim updates. One pediatric practice reduced manual billing tasks by 70% within their first month. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at your practice?', 'If your billing specialists are spending even 2 hours daily on Medicaid hold time, that\'s 10 hours weekly per person just waiting for claim updates. At Steeplechase\'s size, those lost hours add up to thousands in staff costs monthly. I\'d like to show you how our Claim Status Agent works, no long contracts and live in days with no IT lift required. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at your practice?', 'Hi Shahla, many pediatric billing specialists are spending hours daily on Medicaid hold time for claim status updates. With Steeplechase\'s patient volume, I imagine your team faces the same challenge. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at your practice?', 'billing hours lost weekly', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://steeplechasepedi.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '33', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://steeplechasepedi.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain +