(302, 35, '2026-03-20 10:01:40', 'Pediatric Associates Inc. of Central Ohio', 'https://kidzdoc.com', 'Jessica Lee', 'Revenue Cycle Manage/Site Manager', 'jessica.lee@kidzdoc.com', '', 'YES', 58, 'Perfect pediatric specialty match with Revenue Cycle Manager title, but very small team size (7 employees) creates capacity constraints for contract minimums.', 'Pediatric Associates Inc. is an established large pediatric practice serving central Ohio since 1960 with 5 locations and a team of pediatricians and nurse practitioners caring for children birth through age 21. With multiple locations and likely high patient volume, they face significant claim status management complexity across various payers.', 'large', 'high', 'Multi-location pediatric practice with only 7 total employees likely has 1-2 billers managing claim status across 5 locations, creating severe bottlenecks in Medicaid/CHIP follow-up and payer portal management.', '5 locations with only 7 total employees, established since 1960 indicating high patient volume, pediatric specialty with heavy Medicaid/CHIP mix, multi-location complexity without centralized visibility', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 7 staff covering 5 locations since 1960, your billers are likely drowning in Medicaid hold times across multiple Ohio counties.', 'billing staff to location ratio bottleneck', '5 locations, 2 billers', 'Most multi-location pediatric practices with 5+ sites end up with 1-2 billers managing claim status across all locations. When those billers are chasing Medicaid and CHIP claims across multiple Ohio counties, the hold times alone can consume 15+ hours per week. The bottleneck gets worse when payer portals are down or claims get stuck in processing limbo.', 'automated 276/277 for pediatric', 'Jessica, writing because Calyxr built a Claim Status Agent specifically for practices like Pediatric Associates. Instead of your billers logging into multiple payer portals or sitting on hold, our system sends automated 276/277 requests and surfaces claim status in real-time. One pediatric practice with 4 locations saw a 70% reduction in manual billing tasks within the first month.', 'If your billers spend 15 hours weekly on Medicaid hold times across 5 locations, that\'s roughly $18,000 annually in staff time just waiting for payer responses. Worth seeing how other multi-location pediatric practices eliminated payer hold time entirely. No long contracts, live in days, no IT lift required. Is claim status follow-up still a manual process at Pediatric Associates?', 'Jessica, noticed Pediatric Associates manages 5 locations with a small team. Most pediatric practices that size have billers spending hours weekly on Medicaid hold times across multiple counties. Is claim status follow-up still manual at your practice?', '15 hours weekly on hold', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://kidzdoc.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '7', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://kidzdoc.com) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (Apollo export, pre-enriched) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '