(361, 59, '2026-03-25 12:54:20', '1385 Dental Studio', 'https://1385dentalstudio.com', 'Hala Mustafa', 'Owner-General Dentist', 'dr.m@1385dentalstudio.com', '', 'YES', 57, 'Texas-based dental practice with clinical owner decision-maker fits core ICP criteria, though missing key operational pain signals and technology stack details that would boost qualification score.', '', '', '', 'General dental practice likely struggles with manual appointment reminders, patient no-shows, and front desk staff handling multiple communication channels inefficiently.', 'general dental practice name, likely small team size, no visible communication automation platform', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'Running a full-scope general practice as owner-operator means you\'re likely handling front desk VOB calls instead of focusing on clinical production.', 'owner clinical time displacement by administrative burden', 'insurance calls eating clinical time', 'Many general practice owners find themselves stepping away from the chair to handle insurance verification calls when the front desk gets backed up. What should be a 30-second eligibility check turns into 5-10 minutes on hold with carriers, especially during busy appointment blocks. The clinical time lost adds up fast when you\'re trying to maximize production hours.', 'why i reached out hala', 'I\'m following up because Calyxr handles insurance eligibility verification automatically for general practices like 1385 Dental Studio. Instead of manual VOB calls, eligibility gets confirmed in 12 seconds before every appointment. Dr. Peterson\'s practice in Colorado saw their front desk reclaim 15+ hours a week on verification alone, letting him stay chairside where the revenue happens.', 'Every hour spent on insurance calls is an hour not producing clinical revenue. At $400+ per clinical hour, even 5 hours weekly of verification time costs your practice over $100k annually in lost production potential. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and 