(363, 59, '2026-03-25 12:56:02', 'Abilene Family Dentistry North & South', 'https://abilenefamilydentistry.com', 'Tammy Nicolds', 'Associate Dentist', 'tnicolds@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'YES', 34, 'Strong industry match with dental practice in Texas, but limited by Associate Dentist contact who is an influencer rather than decision-maker. Missing key data points prevent higher scoring.', '', '', '', 'Multi-location general dentistry practice likely struggling with inconsistent patient communication and recall management across North and South locations without centralized automation', 'multi-location practice, general dentistry specialty, family practice patient base requiring consistent recall outreach', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Running North and South locations with separate patient bases likely means hygiene recall slips through cracks when patients don\'t get consistent outreach.', 'multi-location recall management inconsistency leading to hygiene revenue loss', 'north and south recall gaps', 'Most multi-location dental practices see hygiene recall patients fall through the cracks when locations aren\'t communicating. A patient might be overdue at North while South has no visibility, or someone gets double-booked because systems aren\'t talking. The recall revenue just sits there while patients assume they\'ll get a call eventually. It\'s especially frustrating when you know the appointments are needed but the outreach isn\'t happening consistently across both sites.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Following up because Calyxr connects both your North and South locations into one patient communication system. Instead of each location handling recall separately, patients get consistent automated outreach regardless which office they prefer. One practice in Texas saw their hygiene recall gap close by 70% reduction in manual front office tasks without adding headcount once both locations were unified. Worth exploring for Abilene Family Dentistry?', 'Ru