(364, 59, '2026-03-25 12:56:50', 'Abilene Family Dentistry North & South', 'https://abilenefamilydentistry.com', 'Mercedes Cody', 'Dental Assistant', 'mcody@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'YES', 42, 'Strong dental industry match in Texas with named practice suggesting multi-location operations, but contact is clinical staff (influencer role) rather than decision-maker, limiting immediate sales potential.', '', '', '', 'Family dentistry practice with multiple locations likely struggles with coordinating patient communication and recall management across North and South offices without a unified platform', 'multi-location family practice, likely high recall volume for routine cleanings, coordination challenges between offices, family dentistry typically sees high no-show rates', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Running North and South locations with separate patient bases likely means double the manual recall calls and missed coordination when patients switch between offices.', 'multi-location patient communication coordination inefficiency', 'two locations, double work', 'Mercedes, most multi-location dental practices end up with their team doing recall calls and patient outreach twice. North office calling their patients, South office calling theirs, and when someone moves between locations the coordination gets messy. The front desk team basically runs two separate recall systems instead of one unified approach. Have you noticed this pattern with your North and South locations?', 'why i\'m following up', 'Mercedes, I\'m following up because of Calyxr. We help multi-location dental practices like Abilene Family Dentistry coordinate patient communication from one system instead of managing separate recall processes at each office. One practice similar to yours saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone after switching from location-specific outreach to unified patient communication. Does this type of coordination challenge sound familiar?', 'Mercedes, running separate recall systems at North and South locations probably costs your team 20+ hours weekly in duplicated effort, plus patients fall through cracks when they switch between offices. Each month without unified communication means more missed recalls and your team working harder instead of smarter. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week. Would it help to see how other multi-location practices handle this coordination challenge?', 'Mercedes, I noticed Abilene Family Dentistry runs both North and South locations. Most practices with multiple offices end up with their teams doing double the recall work instead of coordinating from one system. Is this something you\'ve experienced with your locations?', 'cost of separate systems', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'mcody@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'http://www.