(365, 59, '2026-03-25 12:57:41', 'Abilene Family Dentistry North & South', 'https://abilenefamilydentistry.com', 'Kali Beauchamp', 'Dental Office Manager', 'kbeauchamp@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'YES', 64, 'Strong dental industry match in Texas with operational decision-maker as contact. Family dentistry practice suggests multi-doctor setup with patient volume needs, though limited visibility into specific pain signals or technology stack.', '', '', '', 'Multi-location family dental practice likely struggles with coordinating patient communication and recall management across two offices without centralized automation', 'multi-location practice, family dentistry specialty, no centralized communication platform visible', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'Running patient recalls across North and South locations manually creates inconsistent follow-up timing and likely leaves hygiene revenue on the table.', 'multi-location recall coordination inefficiency leading to hygiene revenue loss', 'two locations, different recall timing', 'Kali, many family practices with multiple locations find their recall systems running on completely different schedules. North location might be reaching out to overdue patients every 6 months, while South location does it quarterly, or one office calls while the other sends postcards. Patients get confused about which location they prefer, and hygiene chairs sit empty because there\'s no unified way to track who\'s due where. The manual coordination between locations means some patients slip through entirely.', 'why I\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We built unified recall management specifically for multi-location dental practices like Abilene Family Dentistry. Instead of each office running separate recall systems, both North and South locations operate from the same patient communication platform. One practice we work with saw their hygiene recall gap close by 40% within 60 days because patients finally received consistent, coordinated outreach regardless of their preferred location.', 'Running separate recall systems across your two locations probably costs Abilene Family Dentistry 15-20 hygiene appointments monthly, patients who fall through coordination gaps or get confused by mixed messaging. That\'s roughly $3,000 in lost hygiene revenue every month. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system and goes live in under a week with no IT setup required. Would it make sense to see how unified recall management would look for both your locations?', 'Hi Kali, noticed Abilene Family Dentistry operates North and South locations. Most multi-location practices struggle with coordinating patient recall between offices, leading to hygiene revenue gaps. Are you seeing consistent recall timing across both locations?', 'cost of separate systems', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '