(376, 59, '2026-03-25 13:07:04', 'AFTER HOURS DENTISTRY', 'https://afterhoursdentistry.com', 'Jeffrey Ludlow', 'Owner/CEO', 'holly@afterhoursdentistry.com', '', 'YES', 70, 'Strong fit with dental industry match and Owner/CEO persona in Texas. After-hours specialty suggests high patient volume and communication pain points that Calyxr can solve.', '', '', '', 'After-hours dental practice likely struggles with 24/7 patient communication, emergency appointment scheduling, and managing high-volume urgent care patient flow without adequate staffing coverage.', 'after-hours specialty, emergency dental care, likely high patient volume, 24/7 operational needs, urgent scheduling requirements', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'After-hours emergency model means your front desk handles urgent scheduling calls at all hours without automated patient triage.', '24/7 call volume burden and emergency scheduling chaos', 'urgent calls going unanswered', 'Jeffrey,\n\nNoticed something about after-hours dental practices. Emergency patients call when they\'re in pain, often outside normal business hours. Many practices miss these urgent calls or rely on answering services that can\'t actually schedule appointments.\n\nThe gap seems biggest during evening rushes and weekends when patients need immediate scheduling but can\'t reach anyone who knows the practice\'s availability.\n\nIs this something you\'re seeing with your patient volume?', 'why i\'m following up', 'Jeffrey,\n\nFollowing up because of Calyxr. We handle patient communication for dental practices that can\'t afford to miss emergency calls.\n\nYour patients get connected to someone within 8 seconds, 24/7, who can actually schedule their urgent appointments using your real availability. Zero missed calls, every patient reached within 8 seconds, around the clock.\n\nSpecifically built for practices like yours where timing matters for emergency cases.\n\nWould this type of coverage make sense for After Hours Dentistry?', 'Jeffrey,\n\nEvery missed emergency call at After Hours Dentistry likely represents $300-800 in lost treatment revenue. If you\'re missing even 2-3 urgent calls per week, that\'s potentially $75,000+ annually walking out the door.\n\nPlus your reputation suffers when patients in pain can\'t reach anyone for immediate care.\n\nCalyxr works with your existing systems, no IT setup required, and you could be live within a week.\n\nWorth exploring how this might work for your emergency model?', 'Jeffrey, noticed After Hours Dentistry handles emergency cases. Many practices in your space struggle with patients calling outside hours when they can\'t reach anyone who can actually schedule urgent appointments. Are you seeing this challenge with your patient volume?', 'cost of missed emergencies', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://afterhoursdentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://afterhoursdentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'holly@afterhoursdentistry.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/