(378, 60, '2026-03-25 13:14:30', '161 Dental Studio', 'https://161dentalstudio.com', 'Temitope Adesanya', 'General Dentist', 'drtemi@161dentalstudio.com', '', 'YES', 35, 'Strong dental industry match with 161 Dental Studio name, but contact is clinical staff (General Dentist) rather than owner/decision-maker, and missing critical firmographic data limits scoring potential.', '', '', '', 'Small dental practice likely struggling with manual appointment reminders, missed calls, and basic patient communication workflows without dedicated front desk automation', 'small practice size, general dentistry specialty, likely minimal staffing for administrative tasks', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', '161 Dental Studio\'s boutique setup likely means the doctor handles patient calls personally, missing production time on manual appointment confirmations.', 'doctor time displacement from clinical production to administrative tasks', 'production time vs phone calls', 'Many solo practitioners end up fielding confirmation calls between patients, which pulls time away from what generates revenue. The phone rings during procedures, patients need rescheduling during lunch breaks, and evening calls about tomorrow\'s appointments become routine. It\'s one of those necessary evils that comes with running a boutique practice, but it quietly chips away at productive chair time.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We handle all patient communication so doctors stay focused on dentistry instead of phone management. One of our solo practitioners saw their front desk call volume drop by 70% while no-shows went from 28% to under 12% in 90 days. The system reaches every patient automatically and only escalates to your team when someone actually needs to reschedule.', 'A doctor spending even 30 minutes daily on patient calls is losing roughly $2,400 in monthly production time. That adds up to nearly $29,000 annually in opportunity cost, not counting the procedure interruptions. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system and goes live in under a week. Would it be worth exploring if it could give you back those 30 minutes every day?', 'I noticed 161 Dental Studio likely handles patient communication in-house. Most solo docs end up taking calls between patients, which cuts into chair time. Are you finding the phone interruptions during procedures becoming a bigger issue lately?', 'cost of missed chair time', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://161dentalstudio.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://161dentalstudio.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'drtemi@161dentalstudio.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/temitope-adesanya-b1832097', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'General Dentist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(379, 60, '2026-03-25 13:15:50', 'Abilene Family Dentistry North & South', 'https://abilenefamilydentistry.com', 'Tammy Nicolds', 'Associate Dentist', 'tnicolds@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'YES', 47, 'Strong industry match (dental practice) and favorable Texas location, but Associate Dentist is an influencer rather than decision-maker. No technology or pain signals present to boost score.', '', '', '', 'Multi-location dental practice likely struggling with inconsistent patient communication and scheduling coordination between North and South locations without unified workflow automation', 'multi-location practice, family dentistry specialty, likely high recall volume, potential staff coordination challenges between locations', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Running North and South locations probably means your front desk teams are duplicating reminder calls and insurance checks across both offices.', 'multi-location operational inefficiency and duplicate administrative work', 'north and south office workflows', 'Most multi-location dental practices end up with each office handling patient reminders, confirmations, and insurance checks completely differently. The North location might use one system while the South location does everything manually, or both teams are making the same reminder calls without knowing what the other office already handled. What usually happens is patients get double-contacted or fall through the cracks entirely when they switch between locations.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is because Calyxr handles patient communication across multiple dental locations from one unified system. Instead of your North and South teams duplicating reminder calls and insurance verification, everything runs automatically with full visibility between both offices. One practice group saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone after switching from location-by-location manual processes. Does this sound like something worth exploring for Abilene Family Dentistry?', 'Running separate patient communication workflows at North and South is probably costing you 20+ staff hours weekly in duplicated reminder calls, insurance checks, and coordination gaps. That\'s roughly $800 in labor costs per week, plus whatever revenue walks away when patients get confused about which location to call. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system and goes live in under a week. What would reclaiming those hours mean for your patient care focus?', 'Most multi-location dental practices I talk to mention their North and South offices handle patient communication completely differently, with lots of duplicated work between front desk teams. Does that match what you see at Abilene Family Dentistry?', 'cost of duplicate workflows', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'tnicolds@abil