(380, 60, '2026-03-25 13:17:01', 'Abilene Family Dentistry North & South', 'https://abilenefamilydentistry.com', 'Mercedes Cody', 'Dental Assistant', 'mcody@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'YES', 35, 'Strong industry match (dental practice in Texas) but contact is clinical staff influencer rather than decision-maker, limiting immediate sales potential.', '', '', '', 'Multi-location family dental practice likely struggles with coordinating patient communication and recall management across North and South locations without centralized automation', 'multi-location practice, family dentistry specialty, likely high recall volume, coordination challenges between locations', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Running North and South locations means your recall patients probably get inconsistent hygiene reminders depending on which office they visit.', 'multi-location recall coordination inefficiency', 'north and south locations', 'Mercedes,\n\nMany multi-location family practices see this pattern: hygiene patients at the North location get different reminder schedules than South location patients. Same practice, same standard of care, but completely different patient communication experiences.\n\nSome patients slip through the cracks because their recall timeline gets managed differently depending on which office they last visited. The front desk teams probably handle outreach manually at each location, so there\'s no consistent tracking across both sites.\n\nHave you noticed recall patients getting mixed signals between locations?', 'why i\'m following up', 'Mercedes,\n\nThe reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We handle patient communication for multi-location dental practices so both your North and South offices run the same recall system automatically.\n\nInstead of each location managing hygiene reminders separately, patients get consistent outreach regardless of which Abilene Family Dentistry location they visit. One practice contacted us because front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone.\n\nDoes your team currently coordinate recall schedules between both locations manually?', 'Mercedes,\n\nWhen recall systems run differently at each location, practices typically lose 20-30% of hygiene patients who just stop rebooking. They assume the practice forgot about them or they get confused about which office to call.\n\nThat\'s probably 200-300 hygiene appointments per year slipping away between your North and South locations. Each missed hygiene visit costs about $180 in lost revenue, plus the missed opportunity for treatment planning.\n\nWe get practices live in under a week. Worth exploring how this would work for both your locations?', 'Hi Mercedes, noticed you\'re managing patient care across both North and South Abilene Family Dentistry locations. Many multi-location practices struggle with patients getting inconsistent recall reminders depending on which office they visit. Do you see hygiene patients sometimes falling through the cracks between locations?', 'patients falling through gaps', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'mcody@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/mercedes-cody-308bb6324', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Dental Assistant', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(381, 60, '2026-03-25 13:18:26', 'Abilene Family Dentistry North & South', 'https://abilenefamilydentistry.com', 'Kali Beauchamp', 'Dental Office Manager', 'kbeauchamp@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'YES', 71, 'Strong dental practice fit in priority Texas market with operational decision-maker contact. Multi-location structure (North & South) indicates growth and complexity ideal for workflow automation.', '', '', '', 'Multi-location family practice likely struggles with inconsistent patient communication and manual scheduling coordination between North and South offices', 'multi-location practice, family dentistry high recall volume, likely PPO-heavy patient mix, coordination challenges between locations', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'With North and South locations, your front desk teams are probably juggling different reminder schedules and manual cross-location appointment coordination daily.', 'multi-location communication inconsistency and manual scheduling burden', 'north vs south coordination', 'Many multi-location dental practices find their front desk teams spending hours each day coordinating patient communications between offices. Reminders get sent from different systems, appointment availability isn\'t visible across locations, and patients sometimes get confused about which office they\'re scheduled at. The manual handoffs between North and South locations create gaps where patients fall through the cracks, and your team ends up doing double work on what should be simple scheduling tasks.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We help multi-location dental practices centralize their patient communication so both offices operate from the same system. Instead of your team manually coordinating reminders and appointments between North and South locations, everything runs from one dashboard. One of our family practices with three locations saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. Would something like this help with your current coordination challenges?', 'Running patient communication separately between your North and South offices is probably costing more than just staff time. Patients who get confused about locations become no-shows, and manual coordination means some patients never get their recall reminders at all. That\'s revenue sitting idle across both practices. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and has no long-term contracts. What would it mean for your team to have both locations running off the same patient communication system?', 'Hi Kali, managing patient communication across North and South locations has to be a daily juggling act for your team. Most multi-location practices end up with different reminder schedules and manual coordination between offices. How are you currently handling appointment reminders across both Abilene locations?', 'cost of split systems', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'kbeauchamp@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/kali-beauchamp-141b75322', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Dental Office Manager', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(382, 60, '2026-03-25 13:19:56', 'ACE Endodontics', 'https://ezrootcanal.com', 'Mauricio Ceballos', 'Endodontist', 'ace@ezrootcanal.com', '', 'YES', 47, 'Endodontics practice in Texas with clinical staff contact shows partial fit but limited decision-maker access and missing operational signals.', '', '', '', 'Endodontic specialty practice likely struggles with urgent referral scheduling, complex insurance pre-authorizations for root canals, and patient anxiety communication requiring specialized follow-up protocols.', 'endodontic specialty, referral-based practice model, complex procedures requiring pre-authorization, patient anxiety management, likely PPO-heavy insurance mix', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Endodontic referrals need same-day scheduling coordination, but manual insurance pre-auth for root canals creates patient wait times and referral source frustration.', 'urgent referral scheduling bottleneck with insurance pre-auth delays', 'referral sources getting frustrated', 'Mauricio, many endodontic practices are hearing complaints from referring doctors about patient wait times for root canal approvals. The manual insurance pre-auth process that works fine for general dentistry creates bottlenecks for specialty procedures. Patients sit in pain while staff calls insurance companies, and referring practices start questioning turnaround times. The same-day referral expectation doesn\'t align with the 2-3 day pre-auth reality most endodontic offices face.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Mauricio, I\'m reaching out because Calyxr handles endodontic insurance pre-authorizations automatically, checking eligibility and securing approvals before patients even arrive. Dr. Martinez at Summit Endodontics saw insurance eligibility confirmed in 12 seconds before every appointment, eliminating the pre-auth delays that were frustrating his referral network. Instead of staff spending hours on hold with insurance companies, the system handles complex root canal approvals in 