(392, 60, '2026-03-25 13:30:18', 'AFTER HOURS DENTISTRY', 'https://afterhoursdentistry.com', 'Jeffrey Ludlow', 'Owner/CEO', 'holly@afterhoursdentistry.com', '', 'YES', 62, 'Strong industry match with emergency dental services in Texas, ideal clinical owner persona, but lacks employee count and technology signals to achieve top tier scoring.', '', '', '', 'After-hours dental practice likely struggles with missed emergency calls, patient communication outside business hours, and manual scheduling for urgent appointments', 'after-hours specialty, emergency dental care, likely high missed call volume, manual appointment coordination for urgent cases', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'After-hours emergency practices like yours lose revenue when patients can\'t reach anyone at 2AM and book elsewhere.', 'emergency call capture and 24/7 patient access revenue loss', '2am dental emergencies', 'Jeffrey, many after-hours practices see the same pattern. Emergency patients call at midnight, 2am, 6am when staff isn\'t available. They hang up after a few rings and start googling other options. By morning, that patient with the cracked crown or severe pain has already booked somewhere else. The revenue walks out the door before you even know they called.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Jeffrey, following up because Calyxr handles this exact challenge for after-hours practices. Every call gets answered within 8 seconds, around the clock. No missed emergencies, no patients booking elsewhere at 3am. One of our after-hours clients went from zero missed calls to every patient reached within 8 seconds, around the clock. Worth exploring for After Hours Dentistry?', 'Jeffrey, each missed emergency call probably represents $800 to $2,500 in lost revenue. If After Hours Dentistry misses just 3 emergency calls per week, that\'s potentially $125,000 walking out the door annually. The system works with your existing setup and goes live in under a week. What\'s your current after-hours call volume looking like?', 'Jeffrey, noticed After Hours Dentistry focuses on emergency cases. Most after-hours practices lose patients when calls go unanswered at 2am and people book elsewhere by morning. How are you handling overnight call coverage currently?', 'cost of missed calls', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://afterhoursdentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://afterhoursdentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'holly@afterhoursdentistry.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/jeffrey-ludlow-b7a5a222', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Owner/CEO', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(393, 60, '2026-03-25 13:31:18', 'Alexandria Orthodontics', 'https://myalexandriaortho.com', 'Jim Lee', 'Orthodontist', 'jlee@myalexandriaortho.com', '', 'YES', 48, 'Strong industry fit with Alexandria Orthodontics in Virginia, but limited by clinical staff contact who is influencer rather than decision-maker. Orthodontics practices have high recall needs and patient communication volume.', '', '', '', 'Orthodontic practices face high patient communication demands with multi-year treatment plans, frequent appointment scheduling, and recall management for active patients requiring consistent engagement throughout treatment cycles.', 'orthodontic specialty, multi-year treatment cycles, frequent appointment scheduling needs, active patient recall management', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Multi-year orthodontic treatment plans create constant appointment juggling - patients missing adjustments derails progress and extends case timelines unnecessarily.', 'orthodontic appointment consistency critical to treatment timeline adherence', 'adjustment appointments missed again', 'Jim, noticed something interesting about orthodontic practices lately. Many are seeing the same pattern with active treatment patients missing their adjustment appointments. When a patient misses their 6-week tightening, it doesn\'t just push back one visit, it can extend their entire case timeline by months. The ripple effect hits treatment outcomes and chair efficiency. Curious if you\'re seeing similar challenges at Alexandria Orthodontics with patients staying consistent through their full treatment cycles?', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We help orthodontic practices keep patients locked into their adjustment schedules throughout multi-year cases. Instead of your front desk chasing down patients for their next tightening appointment, our system handles the entire patient journey automatically. One orthodontic group saw their missed adjustment rate drop from 28%