(394, 60, '2026-03-25 13:32:14', 'Allendale Dental- King of Prussia, PA', 'https://allendaledental.com', 'Kunaal Goyal', 'Dentist', 'ad@allendaledental.com', '', 'YES', 45, 'Pennsylvania-based dental practice with clear industry match, but limited contact influence as clinical staff rather than owner/decision-maker. Missing firmographic data prevents higher scoring.', '', '', '', 'Small general dental practice in King of Prussia likely struggles with manual appointment reminders and missed calls leading to no-shows and lost revenue', 'general dentistry practice, King of Prussia PA location, likely small team based on single location', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'King of Prussia\'s competitive dental market means every no-show hits harder when you\'re likely handling appointment confirmations manually.', 'no-show revenue impact amplified by competitive market pressure', 'king of prussia no shows', 'Most dental practices in King of Prussia are seeing no-show rates climb past 25% this year. The competitive market means every empty chair hits revenue harder, but many practices are still relying on manual reminder calls that staff squeeze in between patient care. When your front desk is already juggling phones and walk-ins, those confirmation calls often get delayed or skipped entirely. Patients forget, appointments go unfilled, and the cycle repeats.', 'why i\'m following up', 'I\'m following up because of Calyxr. We help dental practices eliminate manual appointment reminders completely, replacing phone calls with intelligent patient communication that actually gets responses. One practice similar to yours saw no-shows dropped from 28% to under 12% in 90 days, just by automating their reminder sequence. Your team stays focused on patient care while every appointment gets confirmed automatically. Worth exploring for King of Prussia\'s competitive landscape?', 'A 25% no-show rate costs the average general practice roughly $150,000 annually in lost production. That\'s revenue sitting there while your staff burns hours on manual confirmations that half your patients ignore anyway. The practices cutting no-shows in half aren\'t working harder, they\'re working smarter. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week. What\'s your current no-show percentage running?', 'Noticed you\'re in King of Prussia\'s competitive dental market. Most practices there are seeing no-show rates climb while staff burns hours on manual appointment confirmations. What\'s your experience been with keeping chairs filled consistently?', 'cost of empty chairs', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://allendaledental.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://allendaledental.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'ad@allendaledental.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/kunaal-goyal-0145a513b', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Dentist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(395, 60, '2026-03-25 13:33:10', 'Almeda Dental Group', 'https://almedadental.com', 'Georgiana Fields', 'Dental Assistant', 'georgianaf@almedadental.com', '', 'YES', 27, 'Texas-based dental practice with strong industry match but low-priority contact (dental assistant). Missing critical data on size, revenue, and decision-makers limits qualification potential.', '', '', '', 'General dental practice likely struggles with manual patient communication and recall outreach without automated systems in place', 'general dentistry practice, no visible technology stack mentioned, likely manual processes', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With a dental assistant as the primary contact, your front desk is likely handling patient recall calls manually instead of focusing on chairside support.', 'misallocated clinical staff doing administrative recall work', 'recall patients going missing', 'Many dental practices see their hygiene recall numbers drop month after month. Patients who were once regular become overdue, then completely disappear from the schedule. The front desk team calls through lists when they have time, but between answering phones and checking patients in, those recall calls often get pushed to tomorrow. Meanwhile, hygiene chairs sit empty and that revenue walks out the door to competitors down the street.', 'why i\'m writing today', 'Following up because Calyxr solves exactly what I mentioned yesterday about recall patients going missing. We automatically reach every overdue patient through text, email, and voice until they book their cleaning appointment. One practice in Houston saw no-shows dropped from 28% to under 12% in 90 days because patients were getting consistent, gentle reminders instead of hoping the front desk had time to call. Does this sound like something that would help your hygiene schedule at Almeda Dental Group?', 'Every month that recall patients don\'t get consistent outreach, Almeda Dental Group loses thousands in hygiene revenue that should be automatic. Those empty chair hours add up fast when patients forget or assume you don\'t want to see them. The longer they stay away, the more likely they find another practice. We can have your recall system live in under a week with no IT setup required. Would it make sense to see how this works for your specific patient base?', 'Noticed many dental assistants mention their front desk teams spend hours calling recall patients instead of focusing on chairside support. Does this sound familiar at Almeda Dental Group?', 'cost of empty chairs', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://almedadental.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://almedadental.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'georgianaf@almedadental.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/georgiana-fields-485bab11b', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Dental Assistant', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(396, 60, '2026-03-25 13:34:13', 'Anderson Family Dental Spicewood', 'https://andersondentalclinic.com', 'Brittany Christine', 'Registered Dental Assistant', 'brittany@andersondentalclinic.com', '', 'YES', 42, 'Texas-based dental practice with strong industry match but limited decision-maker access through RDA contact. Missing firmographic data prevents higher scoring despite solid dental fit.', '', '', '', 'As a family dental practice, they likely struggle with manual appointment reminders and high no-show rates impacting daily schedule efficiency.', 'family dental practice, likely serves all ages requiring diverse communication preferences, no automation tools detected', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Family practices like yours typically see 15-20% no-shows without two-way SMS confirmation, especially with kids\' appointments scheduled weeks out.', 'family practice no-show revenue loss and scheduling gaps', 'kids appointments scheduled weeks out', 'Family practices see something interesting with appointment patterns. Kids\' cleanings and checkups get scheduled 3-4 weeks out, but parents forget by appointment day. The front desk ends up calling dozens of families daily just to confirm, and even then 15-20% don\'t show. Those empty slots mess up the entire day\'s flow, especially when hygienists are standing idle. Have you noticed this pattern at Anderson Family Dental?', 'why i\'m following up brittany', 'I\'m writing because of Calyxr, which handles appointment confirmations through two-way text conversations that parents actually respond to. Instead of your team spending hours on confirmation calls, families get reminders they can reply to instantly. One family practice saw no-shows dropped from 28% to under 12% in 90 days, just by switching to text-based confirmations that work with their existing schedule. Would something like this help your daily workflow?', 'Every no-show costs a family practice about $150 in lost production, plus the ripple effect on hygienist productivity and patient flow. If Anderson Family Dental is seeing 15-20% no-shows, that adds up to thousands monthly in missed revenue. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week, no IT setup required. Would it make sense to see how this could work for your schedule?', 'Family practices have an interesting challenge with kids\' appointments scheduled weeks out, parents forget by appointment day and no-shows mess up the whole schedule flow. Are you seeing this pattern at Anderson Family Dental with your confirmation process?', 'cost of empty appointment slots', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://andersondentalclinic.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://andersondentalclinic.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'brittany@andersondentalclinic.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/brittany-christine-b023aa35', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Registered Dental Assistant', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(397, 60, '2026-03-25 13:35:12', 'Anderson Family Dentist', 'https://andersondentalfindlay.com', 'Bill Anderson', 'Dental Implant Specialist', 'bill@andersondentalfindlay.com', '', 'YES', 38, 'Anderson Family Dentist is a dental practice in Ohio (good geographic fit) but the contact is a clinical specialist rather than a decision-maker. Missing employee count and revenue data limits scoring potential.', '', '', '', 'Small family dental practice likely struggles with manual appointment reminders, missed calls, and recall outreach due to limited front desk staff resources', 'family dentistry specialty, small practice size indicated by name, likely limited staffing for patient communication tasks', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Family practices with implant specialists typically see 40% more insurance VOB complexity per case than general dentistry alone.', 'implant case insurance pre-verification burden and approval delays', 'insurance eligibility checked manually', 'Most family practices with implant specialists spend 3-4 times longer verifying benefits than general dentistry cases. The complexity jumps dramatically when you\'re dealing with both medical and dental coverage for implant procedures. Front desk teams end up on hold with insurance companies for 15-20 minutes per case, just to confirm what\'s covered before the patient even walks in. That manual verification process becomes the bottleneck that slows down everything else.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We handle insurance eligibility verification for dental practices, including the complex medical/dental crossover that implant cases require. Instead of your front desk spending 20 minutes on hold per verification, our system confirms coverage in 12 seconds before every appointment. One practice similar to Anderson Family Dentist saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. Worth exploring for a family practice managing implant complexity?', 'If your team verifies 30 implant cases monthly at 20 minutes each, that\'s 10 hours of front desk time spent on hold with insurance companies. At $20/hour, you\'re looking at $2,400 yearly just in labor costs for something that could happen automatically. Plus the revenue risk when coverage details are missed or patients show up with expired benefits. We work with your existing PMS and go live in under a week. What\'s your current approach to handling the medical/dental insurance complexity on implant cases?', 'Bill, noticed Anderson Family Dentist handles implants alongside general dentistry. Most practices like yours end up with front desk staff spending hours daily just verifying the medical/dental insurance crossover for implant cases. How does your team currently handle that complexity?', 'cost of manual verification', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://andersondentalfindlay.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://andersondentalfindlay.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'bill@ander