(400, 60, '2026-03-25 13:38:09', 'Arlington Family Dentistry - Dr. James La', 'https://arlington-dentistry.com', 'James La', 'Dentist', 'drla@afdrla.com', '', 'YES', 50, 'Texas-based dental practice with clear industry match and favorable geography, but limited visibility into practice size, decision-maker level, and operational pain points. Contact is clinical staff (influencer) rather than owner/decision-maker.', '', '', '', 'Small family dental practice likely struggles with manual appointment reminders, missed calls, and patients overdue for routine cleanings without automated recall systems.', 'small family practice, general dentistry, limited staffing capacity, likely phone-dependent operations', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'Arlington Family Dentistry\'s patient base likely has hygiene recall gaps without automated outreach beyond manual phone calls.', 'hygiene recall drop-off revenue loss', 'hygiene revenue sitting idle', 'James,\n\nMany family practices have 400+ patients who are 6+ months overdue for their cleaning appointments. Most of these patients aren\'t avoiding the dentist, they simply forgot or got busy with life.\n\nThe challenge is that manual phone calls to reach overdue patients take hours of front desk time, and even then you might only connect with 20% of them. Meanwhile, that hygiene revenue just sits in the schedule gaps.\n\nPatients want to come back, they just need the right nudge at the right time.', 'why i\'m following up', 'James,\n\nFollowing up because Arlington Family Dentistry likely has that same hygiene recall gap I mentioned yesterday.\n\nCalyxr handles the entire recall process automatically. Text and email sequences go out to overdue patients, and our system handles the back-and-forth to get them scheduled without your team lifting a finger.\n\nOne family practice in Texas saw their hygiene recall rate jump from 42% to 78% in the first 90 days, filling schedule gaps that had been empty for months.\n\nAre you seeing similar recall challenges at Arlington Family Dentistry?', 'James,\n\nIf 400 overdue hygiene patients each represent $180 in revenue, that\'s $72,000 sitting in charts instead of on the schedule.\n\nEvery month you stay with manual recall calls, more patients slip through the cracks and that number grows.\n\nCalyxr works with your existing practice management system and goes live in under a week with no IT setup required.\n\nWould it make sense to see how this would work specifically for Arlington Family Dentistry\'s patient base?', 'Hi James, noticed Arlington Family Dentistry probably has hundreds of patients overdue for cleanings with no automated way to reach them. Most family practices lose significant hygiene revenue this way. Are you seeing similar recall gaps in your patient base?', 'cost of waiting', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://arlington-dentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://arlington-dentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'drla@afdrla.com', '', 'http://www.linkedi