(403, 60, '2026-03-25 13:41:07', 'ATX DENTAL GROUP, PLLC', 'https://atxfamilydental.com', 'Madai Dimas', 'Dental Assistant', 'madai@americanprinters.com', '', 'YES', 29, 'ATX Dental Group is a Texas-based dental practice which meets basic industry requirements, but the contact is a Dental Assistant (influencer only, not decision-maker) and lacks firmographic details like employee count and revenue to establish strong fit signals.', '', '', '', 'Multi-location dental group likely struggling with inconsistent patient communication and recall management across locations without centralized automation', 'multi-location group practice, PLLC structure indicating multiple providers, likely fragmented communication systems across locations', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'ATX Dental Group\'s multi-location structure likely creates recall timing inconsistencies and patient confusion about which location to book follow-ups.', 'multi-location recall coordination gaps leading to hygiene revenue loss', 'recall chaos across locations', 'Most multi-location dental groups see the same pattern. Patients get confused about where their next cleaning is supposed to be. Some locations send recall cards, others rely on phone calls, and a few try text messages. Meanwhile, patients are slipping through the cracks because there\'s no consistent way to track who got reached and when. The front desk teams at each location are working harder but not seeing the recall numbers they want.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We help multi-location dental groups get every location on the same recall system so patients never get mixed messages about where to schedule. ATX Dental Group could have all locations using identical patient outreach, with full visibility into who\'s overdue and which location they prefer. One group saw their hygiene recall gap close by 40% in the first quarter after getting all locations synchronized.', 'Every month that recall stays inconsist