(413, 60, '2026-03-25 13:51:19', 'Authentic Smiles', 'https://authenticsmiles.com', 'Shane Matt', 'Dentist', 'shane@authenticsmiles.com', '', 'YES', 32, 'Strong dental industry match and Texas location, but limited by basic contact persona (Dentist without ownership signals) and lack of operational data to assess pain points or technology stack.', '', '', '', 'Limited practice information suggests potential front desk overload with manual patient communication and scheduling processes typical of smaller dental practices.', 'minimal online presence, likely small team structure, general dentistry practice name suggests basic operational setup', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'With limited front desk staffing typical of smaller practices, your team likely spends significant time on manual appointment reminders and confirmation calls.', 'small practice front desk burden and manual communication overhead', 'your front desk time', 'Shane, most dental practices with smaller front desk teams end up in the same spot. The team spends 3-4 hours daily just on appointment confirmations and reminders, which means less time for the patient experience that actually drives referrals. It\'s one of those necessary tasks that quietly eats up the day, but patients still show up expecting that personal touch when they walk in.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Shane, following up because of Calyxr. We handle all patient confirmations, reminders, and follow-up communication so your front desk can focus on the patients actually in your office. One practice similar to yours saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. Worth exploring if your team is spending too much time on the phone instead of with patients?', 'Shane, if your front desk is spending 20+ hours weekly on manual confirmations, that\'s roughly $400-500 in labor costs just for reminder calls. Meanwhile, patients calling during procedures go to voicemail. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and can be live in under a week. Would it make sense to see how this could work for Authentic Smiles?', 'Shane, noticed most smaller dental practices end up with front desk teams spending hours daily on appointment confirmations instead of focusing on patient experience. Does this sound familiar at Authentic Smiles?', 'cost of manual reminders', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://authenticsmiles.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://authenticsmiles.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'shane@authenticsmiles.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/shanematt', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Dentist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(414, 60, '2026-03-25 13:52:19', 'Authentic Smiles', 'https://authenticsmiles.com', 'Kyanna Floyd', 'Registered Dental Hygienist', 'kyanna@authenticsmiles.com', '', 'YES', 32, 'Texas-based dental practice with strong industry match, but contact is clinical staff (hygienist) rather than decision-maker, limiting qualification tier despite good geographic and industry fit.', '', '', '', 'Generic dental practice likely struggles with manual patient communication and appointment management without automated systems in place', 'minimal practice information available, likely small practice without established communication automation', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With your hygienist-focused contact structure, you\'re likely handling recall scheduling manually instead of letting automated hygiene reminders maintain patient retention.', 'hygienist administrative burden reducing clinical productivity', 'hygiene recall schedules', 'Most dental practices have 30-40% of their hygiene patients overdue for their six month cleanings right now. The manual process of calling through recall lists means hundreds of patients slip through the cracks every quarter. When hygienists spend time between appointments making reminder calls instead of focusing on patient care, it creates a bottleneck that affects the entire practice flow. The patients who need you most end up being the hardest ones to reach.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We help dental practices automatically reach overdue hygiene patients through multiple channels so recall schedules stay full without manual calling. One practice saw their hygiene recall gap close by 70% in the first 90 days, with front desk teams reclaiming 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. You probably know which patients haven\'t been in for their cleaning, but reaching them consistently is the challenge.', 'Every month that overdue hygiene patients don\'t get scheduled costs the practice roughly $180 per empty appointment slot. Multiply that across 20-30 unfilled hygiene appointments and you\'re looking at $3,600+ in lost production monthly. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system and goes live in under a week with no IT setup required. Would it help to see how other practices are filling their hygiene schedules automatically?', 'Hey Kyanna, noticed you\'re at Authentic Smiles. Most hygienists tell me their biggest frustration is seeing the same overdue patients month after month on recall lists, but never having enough time to actually reach them all. How are you handling your six month recall scheduling right now?', 'cost of empty chairs', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://authenticsmiles.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://authenticsmiles.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'kyanna@authenticsmiles.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/kyanna-floyd-321107b5', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Registered Dental Hygienist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NU