(419, 60, '2026-03-25 13:57:25', 'Balcones Family Dental', 'https://balconesfamilydental.com', 'Megan Smith', 'Dental Assistant', 'megansmith@balconesfamilydental.com', '', 'YES', 47, 'Strong industry fit as dental practice in Texas with dental assistant contact, but limited by influencer-level persona and lack of pain/technology signals.', '', '', '', 'General dentistry practice likely struggling with manual patient communication, recall outreach, and front desk workflow inefficiencies without automated systems in place', 'general dentistry specialty, family practice patient mix, no visible communication automation, likely manual recall and reminder processes', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Family practices like Balcones typically see 20-30% hygiene recall drop-off when relying on manual phone outreach instead of multi-channel patient communication.', 'hygiene recall revenue leakage from manual-only patient outreach', 'recall patients going quiet', 'Most family practices see about 30% of their hygiene patients go quiet after their cleaning appointments. The front desk tries calling but reaches maybe half of them, and then those patients just drift away until they have a problem. Meanwhile those empty hygiene slots could be generating $200+ per visit. It\'s like watching revenue walk out the door in slow motion.', 'why I\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We help family practices like yours automatically stay connected with recall patients through text, email, and calls so they actually book their next cleaning. One practice in Austin saw no-shows dropped from 28% to under 12% in 90 days just by reaching patients the way they prefer to communicate. Would something like this help fill those hygiene gaps?', 'Every hygiene appointment that goes unscheduled is roughly $200 in lost revenue, and most practices have 15-20 overdue recall patients at any time. That\'s $3,000+ sitting on the table each month. Calyxr works with your existing practice ma