(425, 60, '2026-03-25 14:04:05', 'Beckett Dental Care', 'https://beckettdentalcare.com', 'Diana Hanes', 'Dental Assistant', 'appointments@beckettdentalcare.com', '', 'YES', 33, 'Strong industry match (dental practice) and EST geography (Ohio) but low persona fit as Dental Assistant is an influencer not decision-maker. No technology, pain, or intent signals present.', '', '', '', 'Small general dental practice likely struggles with manual patient communication and recall outreach leading to hygiene drop-off and no-shows', 'general dentistry practice, small practice size, no visible automated communication system', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With just a dental assistant handling front office duties, your hygiene recall calls are probably competing with chairside responsibilities.', 'dual-role staff bandwidth constraint affecting recall consistency', 'recall calls piling up', 'Diana, many small practices see the same pattern with recall outreach. Hygiene appointments get pushed out further and further because someone has to be chairside during procedures, and recall calls keep getting moved to tomorrow\'s to-do list. The six-month cleanings turn into eight months, then twelve. Patients assume you\'ll call when it\'s time, but they slip through the gaps when front desk duties compete with clinical responsibilities. Does this sound familiar at Beckett Dental Care?', 'why i\'m following up', 'Diana, I\'m writing because Calyxr handles the exact situation I mentioned yesterday. We take over all patient recall communications, so hygiene appointments book themselves without you having to choose between making calls and being chairside. One of our dental assistant clients told us their hygiene recall improved so much that no-shows dropped from 28% to under 12% in 90 days, just from consistent automated outreach. What does your current recall process look like?', 'Diana, every month without automated recall means more hygiene patients slip away quietly. The average practice loses $40,000+ annually in hygiene revenue from recall gaps alone. When you\'re covering both chairside and front desk, those recall calls will always come second to immediate patient needs. Calyxr lives in under a week and works with your existing practice management system. Would it help to see exactly how this works for practices your size?', 'Diana, noticed you handle both chairside and front desk at Beckett Dental Care. Most dental assistants in that role tell me hygiene recall calls keep falling behind when they\'re needed chairside. How are you managing that balance?', 'cost of waiting', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://beckettdentalcare.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://beckettdentalcare.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'appointments@beckettdentalcare.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/diana-hanes-64618257', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Dental Assistant', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(426, 61, '2026-03-25 14:39:35', 'South Florida Skin Center', 'https://theskincenter.com', '', '', '', '', 'YES', 13, 'South Florida Skin Center is in a good-fit specialty (dermatology) but lacks sufficient firmographic data to score well across most dimensions. Company name suggests dermatology focus which is ideal for Calyxr.', 'South Florida Skin Center is a dermatology practice serving the South Florida region, likely offering comprehensive skin care services including medical, surgical, and cosmetic dermatology treatments.', 'mid-size', 'high', 'High volume of cosmetic and surgical procedures requiring complex insurance verification and prior authorization workflows with frequent coverage denials', 'dermatology specialty, cosmetic procedures, surgical treatments, South Florida high-volume market, mixed insurance coverage complexity', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With cosmetic dermatology making up a significant portion of your case mix, your front desk likely spends hours daily fielding coverage questions for procedures with complex approval requirements.', 'staff time drain on insurance verification', 'coverage questions eating hours daily', 'Most dermatology practices with heavy cosmetic case loads report their front desk spends 3-4 hours daily just on coverage questions. The constant back and forth with insurance on procedure approvals creates a bottleneck that backs up scheduling and frustrates patients who just want to know if they\'re covered. When you\'re running both cosmetic and surgical cases, those approval workflows multiply fast.', 'why calyxr exists', 'The coverage question chaos is exactly why we built Calyxr for practices like South Florida Skin Center. Instead of your staff spending hours on phone calls and faxes for prior auths, our platform handles the entire verification and approval process in the background. One practice similar to yours cut their coverage-related admin time from 25 hours weekly to under 6 hours.', 'If your team spends 25 hours weekly on insurance verifications and prior auths, that\'s roughly $26,000 in staff time annually just for coverage questions. We can show you exactly how other dermatology practices handle high-volume approvals without the daily bottlenecks, and you can see it working with your actual cases in about a week. Would seeing how this works with a few of your trickiest procedures make sense?', 'Noticed South Florida Skin Center handles a lot of cosmetic and surgical cases. Most practices with that mix tell us insurance verifications become a daily headache. Worth a quick conversation about how others solve this?', '25 hours weekly adds up', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://theskincenter.com) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://theskincenter.com) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
