(428, 62, '2026-03-25 14:42:03', 'South Florida Skin Center', 'https://theskincenter.com', '', '', '', '', 'YES', 18, 'Dermatology practice with strong industry match (8 pts) but lacks all other qualifying data points including decision-maker contact, technology signals, and pain indicators.', 'South Florida Skin Center is a dermatology practice serving the South Florida market with comprehensive skin care services including medical, surgical, and cosmetic treatments.', 'mid-size', 'medium', 'High-volume cosmetic and surgical dermatology practice likely struggles with insurance pre-authorizations, eligibility verification, and managing mixed cash-pay and insurance workflows', 'dermatology specialty, surgical procedures requiring prior auth, cosmetic services (mixed billing), South Florida market (high patient volume)', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Running cosmetic procedures alongside surgical dermatology creates constant eligibility verification bottlenecks when staff can\'t quickly distinguish coverage tiers.', 'mixed workflow complexity', 'coverage verification chaos', 'Most dermatology practices running both cosmetic and surgical procedures hit the same bottleneck. Staff spend hours verifying what insurance covers versus what patients pay cash for. The constant back-and-forth creates scheduling delays and frustrated patients who thought their treatment was covered.', 'why calyxr reached out', 'Calyxr handles the insurance verification maze for dermatology practices like yours. Our platform instantly identifies coverage tiers and flags cash-pay procedures before scheduling. One practice in Tampa cut their pre-auth time by 75% and eliminated those awkward \"your insurance won\'t cover this\" conversations at checkout.', 'The average dermatology practice wastes 15 hours per week on insurance verification calls. At $25 per hour, that\'s $19,500 annually just in staff time, not counting rescheduled appointments. We can show you the coverage verification setup in 20 minutes, no contracts required. Worth a quick look at how this would work for your mixed procedures?', 'Noticed South Florida Skin Center handles both cosmetic and surgical dermatology. Most practices struggle with the insurance verification maze between coverage tiers. Mind if I share how similar practices are solving this bottleneck?', '15 hours weekly savings', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://theskincenter.com) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://theskincenter.com) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
