(431, 63, '2026-03-26 10:13:41', 'Abilene Family Dentistry North & South', 'https://abilenefamilydentistry.com', 'Tammy Nicolds', 'Associate Dentist', 'tnicolds@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'YES', 47, 'Strong industry match (dental practice) in Texas with multi-location structure indicated by \'North & South\' naming. Contact is clinical staff influencer rather than decision-maker, limiting immediate sales potential.', 'Abilene Family Dentistry is a multi-location general dental practice with two locations (North & South) serving Abilene, TX, offering comprehensive services from restorative to cosmetic dentistry with multiple dentists on staff.', 'mid-size', 'high', 'Multi-location practice likely struggling with fragmented patient communication and scheduling coordination between North and South offices without centralized automation', 'multi-location practice, general dentistry, comprehensive services, multiple dentists, likely high patient volume across two sites', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Running two Abilene locations means your front desk teams are probably handling double the VOB calls and appointment confirmations without shared communication workflows.', 'multi-location operational inefficiency and duplicated manual work', 'two offices, two headaches', 'Tammy, most multi-location dental practices end up with their North and South offices running completely different patient communication systems. One front desk confirms appointments by phone, the other sends text reminders, and nobody knows which patients are actually showing up until they walk through the door. The insurance verification calls alone probably eat up different amounts of time at each location, making it impossible to predict staffing needs or compare performance.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We help multi-location dental practices standardize their patient communication across all offices so your North and South locations operate with the same automated workflows. One of our dental groups saw front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone once they unified their patient outreach system. Instead of each office doing confirmations differently, both locations now follow identical automated sequences.', 'Running two different patient communication systems means you\'re probably losing 20+ hours of front desk productivity each week across both locations, plus the revenue from patients who slip through different reminder processes. Most practices don\'t realize how much coordination time gets wasted when offices operate independently. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and can be live in under a week. Would it make sense to see how other multi-location practices unified their patient outreach?', 'Tammy, noticed Abilene Family Dentistry has North and South locations. Most multi-location practices struggle with each office running different patient communication workflows, making it hard to maintain consistency. Are you seeing coordination challenges between your two offices?', 'cost of splitting workflows', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent