(432, 63, '2026-03-26 10:14:42', 'Abilene Family Dentistry North & South', 'https://abilenefamilydentistry.com', 'Mercedes Cody', 'Dental Assistant', 'mcody@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'YES', 35, 'Strong industry match with Texas location bonus, but contact is clinical staff influencer rather than decision-maker. Missing key data prevents higher scoring.', 'Multi-location general dentistry practice with two locations in Abilene, Texas, offering comprehensive services from preventive to complex restorative care including implants and Invisalign, with strong patient satisfaction ratings (4.9 stars, 850+ reviews).', 'mid-size', 'high', 'Multi-location practice likely struggling with centralized patient communication and scheduling coordination across two offices', 'multi-location practice, general dentistry with complex services, high patient volume indicated by 850+ reviews, comprehensive service mix from preventive to implants', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With two Abilene locations, coordinating hygiene recalls and appointment reminders across both offices likely creates patient confusion and scheduling gaps.', 'multi-location patient communication coordination burden', 'two locations, different systems', 'Mercedes, many multi-location practices like Abilene Family Dentistry run into the same challenge. Patients get confused about which office they\'re supposed to visit for their hygiene recall, or they miss appointment reminders entirely because each location handles outreach differently. The front desk teams end up playing phone tag trying to coordinate schedules between North and South, and patients slip through the cracks. Have you noticed this happening with your recall patients?', 'why i\'m following up', 'Mercedes, I\'m following up because Calyxr helps multi-location practices like yours coordinate patient communication from one central system. Instead of each office running separate reminder processes, both your North and South locations can send consistent, branded messages that clearly tell patients which office to visit and when. One practice saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone after switching to centralized outreach. Does this sound like something that could help coordinate things better between your locations?', 'Mercedes, staying with separate communication systems at each location typically costs practices about 12-15 hours of front desk time per week in coordination calls, plus the revenue from patients who get confused and simply don\'t reschedule. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system and goes live in under a week with no IT setup required. Would it make sense to see how this could work specifically for your North and South locations?', 'Hi Mercedes, noticed Abilene Family Dentistry has two locations. Most multi-location practices struggle with patients getting confused about which office to visit for recalls. Are you seeing this with your North and South coordination?', 'cost of the current approach', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'mcody@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/mercedes-cody-308bb6324', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Dental Assistant', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(433, 63, '2026-03-26 10:15:42', 'Abilene Family Dentistry North & South', 'https://abilenefamilydentistry.com', 'Kali Beauchamp', 'Dental Office Manager', 'kbeauchamp@abilenefamilydentistry.com', '', 'YES', 65, 'Strong fit dental practice in Texas with practice manager contact. Family dentistry indicates established patient base likely needing recall automation and front office workflow optimization.', 'Abilene Family Dentistry is a multi-location general dentistry practice with two locations (North & South) in Abilene, TX, led by Dr. Adam Awtrey and Dr. Jeff Webb. They offer comprehensive services including advanced procedures like dental implants and Invisalign, positioning themselves as a technology-forward family dental group.', 'mid-size', 'high', 'Multi-location practice likely struggling with inconsistent patient communication and scheduling coordination between North and South locations without centralized automation.', 'multi-location practice, general dentistry with advanced services, technology-forward positioning suggests current tech stack may have gaps, family dentistry implies high recall volume needs', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'Managing appointment coordination between your North and South locations likely creates scheduling conflicts when patients call the wrong office.', 'multi-location scheduling confusion and patient friction', 'two location coordination headache', 'Managing patient communication across multiple locations creates constant friction. Patients call the wrong office, appointments get double-booked between North and South, and your team spends time transferring calls and checking schedules at both locations. The manual coordination between offices means someone is always playing catch-up on patient status, and scheduling conflicts slip through when both locations aren\'t synced in real-time.', 'why i\'m following up', 'I\'m writing because Calyxr solves the multi-location coordination problem that\'s eating up your team\'s time. Instead of managing separate communication systems, you get unified patient outreach that works across both your North and South locations automatically. One practice we work with saw a 70% reduction in manual front office tasks without adding headcount once they centralized their patient communication. Does this sound like something worth exploring for Abilene Family Dentistry?', 'Every week your team spends coordinating between locations manually costs you productive hours that could go toward patient care. Those scheduling mix-ups and transferred calls add up to lost revenue when patients get frustrated and go elsewhere. The good news is Calyxr works with your existing PMS and requires no IT setup, so you could have both locations running unified communication within days. Would it make sense to see how this looks for your specific setup?', 'Hi Kali, I imagine coordinating patient communication between your North and South locations keeps your team busy with manual coordination tasks. Most multi-location practices we talk to struggle with this same challenge. Are you finding the same thing at Abilene Family Dentistry?', 'cost of staying manual', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://abilenefamilydentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-2