(435, 63, '2026-03-26 10:17:52', 'Aduddell Dentistry', 'https://aduddelldentistry.com', 'Scott Aduddell', 'General Dentist', 'scott@aduddelldentistry.com', '', 'YES', 38, 'Texas-based dental practice with General Dentist contact shows industry fit, but clinical staff persona has limited decision-making authority and lack of company size/operational signals limits qualification.', 'Aduddell Dentistry is a family-owned comprehensive general dentistry practice in Plano, TX, emphasizing patient comfort and relationship-based care with advanced technology investments. The practice markets itself as a high-touch, non-rushed alternative to corporate dentistry.', 'small', 'medium', 'Small family practice likely struggling with manual patient communication and recall management while trying to maintain high-touch service without adequate automation', 'family-owned practice, general dentistry, emphasizes relationship-based care, non-rushed service model, Plano TX location', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'Family practices like yours often lose hygiene recall revenue when patients slip through manual tracking systems despite your high-touch approach.', 'hygiene recall drop-off revenue loss from manual systems', 'hygiene recall gaps', 'Scott, many family practices track thousands in hygiene revenue sitting with overdue patients who never got a systematic recall outreach. The manual tracking works until it doesn\'t, and patients who haven\'t been in for 8+ months often assume you don\'t want them back. It\'s not a reflection of your clinical care, it\'s just the reality of manual systems in small practices. The revenue gap grows quietly while you\'re focused on the patients who do show up.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Scott, following up because Aduddell Dentistry likely has hygiene revenue sitting with overdue patients, and that\'s exactly what Calyxr was built to recover for family practices. Instead of your team manually tracking recall lists, the system identifies overdue patients and reaches them through multiple touchpoints until they reschedule. One similar family practice saw no-shows dropped from 28% to under 12% in 90 days while filling their hygiene schedule consistently. Would this type of recall recovery make sense for your practice?', 'Scott, staying with manual recall tracking typically costs family practices $15,000-25,000 annually in hygiene revenue that never gets recovered from overdue patients. The longer patients stay away, the more likely they are to find care elsewhere or delay treatment entirely. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and requires no IT setup on your end. If you had a way to automatically recover that sitting hygiene revenue without adding work for your team, would that be worth exploring?', 'Scott, noticed family practices often lose hygiene revenue when patients slip through manual recall tracking, even with great clinical care. Does this sound familiar at Aduddell Dentistry?', 'cost of manual tracking', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://aduddelldentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://aduddelldentistry.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 