(436, 63, '2026-03-26 10:18:55', 'Advanced DDS', 'https://advanceddds.com', 'Wendy Miller', 'Lead Dental Hygienist', 'wmiller@advanceddds.com', '', 'YES', 47, 'Dental practice in New York with clinical staff contact suggesting operational need, but limited decision-making authority and missing key firmographic data reduce overall fit.', 'Advanced DDS is an established multi-specialty dental practice in Garden City, NY operating for 35+ years with general dentistry, cosmetic, implants, sedation services, and an in-house lab offering same-day dentistry.', 'mid-size', 'high', 'Multi-specialty practice with 35+ years of legacy systems likely struggles with fragmented patient communication across different service lines and manual scheduling coordination between general, cosmetic, and implant departments', 'multi-specialty practice, 35+ years established (legacy systems), in-house lab coordination, same-day dentistry scheduling complexity, sedation services requiring specialized follow-up', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With general, cosmetic, and implant departments plus same-day lab work, your hygiene recall likely gets complicated when patients need cross-department coordination.', 'multi-specialty recall coordination complexity and revenue leakage', 'cross department scheduling chaos', 'Wendy, many multi-specialty practices with general, cosmetic, and implant departments face the same challenge. Patients need hygiene recalls, but then also have pending cosmetic consultations or implant follow-ups. Each department tends to manage their own scheduling and reminders separately. The result is patients getting multiple calls about different appointments, or worse, falling through the cracks entirely when they need coordinated care across departments. Does this sound familiar with your recall patients who also have treatment pending in other departments?', 'why im following up', 'Wendy, I\'m following up because Calyxr helps multi-specialty practices coordinate patient communication across all departments from one system. Instead of general, cosmetic, and implant teams each managing their own reminders, everything runs through unified patient workflows. One practice with similar departments saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone once they stopped duplicating communication efforts. Your recall patients probably need this type of coordination, especially when they have treatment pending across multiple departments.', 'Wendy, when each department handles patient communication separately, practices typically lose 15-20% of potential recall revenue because patients don\'t understand their complete treatment timeline. Staff ends up making redundant calls, and patients get confused about which appointments to prioritize. The system works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week. Would it help to see how other multi-specialty practices coordinate their patient communication across departments like yours?', 'Hi Wendy, noticed Advanced DDS has general, cosmetic, and implant departments. Many multi-specialty practices struggle with patients getting mixed messages when they need care across different departments. How do you currently coordinate recall patients who also have pending treatment in cosmetic or implants?', 'cost of manual coordination', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://advanceddds.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://advanceddds.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) →