(437, 63, '2026-03-26 10:19:51', 'Advanced Dental Care of Richmond', 'https://richmondsmile.com', 'Thomas Han', 'Associate Dentist', 'dr.han@richmondsmile.com', '', 'YES', 37, 'Strong industry match (Advanced Dental Care) but limited by Associate Dentist contact who is an influencer not decision-maker. Missing firmographic data prevents higher scoring despite clear dental practice fit.', 'Advanced Dental Care of Richmond appears to be a general dental practice serving Richmond, Virginia. With an Associate Dentist as the primary contact, this suggests a multi-provider practice structure rather than a solo owner-operated clinic.', 'small', 'medium', 'Multi-provider general dental practice likely struggles with coordinating patient communication and scheduling across multiple dentists without centralized automation', 'multi-provider practice structure, associate dentist contact indicates non-owner management, general dentistry specialty with high patient volume needs, Richmond market suggests PPO insurance mix', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Multi-provider setup like yours typically sees scheduling conflicts and missed patient handoffs between associate dentists without centralized communication workflows.', 'multi-provider coordination breakdown and patient experience inconsistency', 'patient handoffs between providers', 'Thomas, most multi-provider practices have the same issue we\'re seeing everywhere. Patient calls one doctor\'s line, books with another associate, then shows up confused about who they\'re actually seeing. The front desk spends half their day sorting out scheduling conflicts between providers because each dentist is managing their own patient communication differently. Patients get mixed messages about their treatment plan when they bounce between associates.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Thomas, following up because Calyxr solves the exact coordination problem I mentioned yesterday. Instead of each provider running their own patient communication, everything flows through one centralized system that tracks which dentist the patient belongs to and when. One of our multi-provider practices saw front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone because the system handles all patient routing automatically. Does this sound familiar to what you\'re dealing with at Advanced Dental Care?', 'Thomas, staying with the current patchwork approach costs most multi-provider practices about $8,000 monthly in missed appointments and staff overtime just sorting out scheduling conflicts. That\'s $96K annually in revenue sitting on the table. Worth exploring if there\'s a better way that doesn\'t require overhauling your entire PMS, works with your existing setup, and goes live in under a week. What\'s the biggest scheduling headache you\'re seeing between the associates right now?', 'Thomas, noticed Advanced Dental Care has multiple providers. Most multi-doctor practices we talk to struggle with patients getting confused about which dentist they\'re seeing and mixed communication between associates. Is this something you\'re dealing with there?', 'cost of the current approach', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://richmondsmile.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://richmondsmile.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website,