(438, 63, '2026-03-26 10:20:48', 'Advanced Dental Care of Round Rock', 'https://adcroundrock.com', 'Joe Widdison', 'Doctor of Dental Medicine', 'adcrr@mb2dental.com', '', 'YES', 48, 'Strong industry match for dental practice in high-value Texas market, but contact is clinical staff (DDS) rather than practice owner/decision-maker, limiting immediate buying power.', 'Advanced Dental Care of Round Rock is a small general dentistry practice in Texas with a bilingual focus, serving families with comprehensive care and accepting uninsured patients with budget-friendly pricing packages.', 'small', 'medium', 'Small bilingual general dental practice serving uninsured patients likely struggles with manual patient communication, recall outreach, and verification processes without staff to handle administrative burden', 'small practice size, general dentistry, accepts uninsured patients, bilingual patient base, family-focused care, budget pricing packages', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'Bilingual patient base in Round Rock likely creates double the recall workload when hygiene reminders need manual translation across two languages.', 'bilingual communication overhead multiplying administrative burden', 'bilingual hygiene recall challenge', 'Joe,\n\nMany dental practices serving bilingual communities in Round Rock notice their hygiene recall rates start slipping when patients miss their 6-month cleanings. The manual outreach gets complicated when half your patient base needs reminders in Spanish, and the other half in English. Front desk teams end up spending double the time on recall calls, and patients who don\'t get reached in their preferred language often just don\'t reschedule. The revenue from those overdue hygiene appointments starts adding up quickly.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Joe,\n\nFollowing up because I wanted to mention Calyxr. We help dental practices automate their hygiene recall outreach in both English and Spanish, so your patients get reached in their preferred language without your front desk having to manually translate and make separate calls. One practice in Austin saw their hygiene recall rate jump from 64% to 81% within 60 days once their bilingual patients started getting consistent outreach in the right language. Worth exploring for Advanced Dental Care?', 'Joe,\n\nIf 100 patients are overdue for hygiene cleanings at $200 average per visit, that\'s $20,000 sitting in your schedule gaps. For bilingual practices, the manual recall process often means patients slip through the cracks when language barriers make follow-up inconsistent. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system and goes live in under a week. Could I show you how the bilingual recall automation looks for a practice like yours?', 'Joe, noticed Advanced Dental Care serves a bilingual patient base in Round Rock. Many practices struggle with hygiene recall when half the outreach needs Spanish translation and the other half English. How are you handling recall reminders across both languages currently?', 'cost of missed cleanings', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://adcroundrock.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://adcroundrock.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export