(439, 64, '2026-03-30 13:00:04', 'Comprehensive Family Dental', 'https://victoriatxdentist.com', 'Tim Rainey', 'General Dentist', 'raineydds@victoriatxdentist.com', '', 'YES', 73, 'Strong dental practice fit with established 45-year family practice in Texas serving general and pediatric dentistry, though contact is clinical staff rather than owner/decision-maker which limits persona scoring.', 'Comprehensive Family Dental is an established 8-employee general and pediatric dental practice in Victoria, TX operating for 45+ years with $4.5M revenue, offering specialized TMJ treatment, orthodontics, and sleep apnea services alongside traditional family dentistry.', 'small', 'high', 'Front desk staff overwhelmed managing recall outreach, appointment scheduling, and insurance verification for dual patient populations (general and pediatric) with limited team bandwidth at $562K revenue per employee', '8 employees managing $4.5M revenue, dual specialty practice (general + pediatric), 45+ years established with likely legacy systems, multi-service offerings requiring complex scheduling coordination, high patient volume per staff ratio', 'high', 'Champion / Economic Buyer', 'high', 'With dual general and pediatric patient populations, your front desk is likely juggling different recall schedules and parent communication preferences manually.', 'dual population recall management complexity and parent communication burden', 'dual recall schedules', 'Most practices serving both general and pediatric patients find their front desk teams drowning in different recall timelines. Six-month cleanings for adults, three-month fluoride visits for kids, parent permission calls, and insurance verification for two age groups. The manual coordination alone can consume 20+ hours per week. When you\'re generating $562K per team member, that administrative time has serious opportunity cost.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Following up because Calyxr handles the exact recall complexity you\'re deali