(449, 64, '2026-03-30 13:10:07', 'Curtis A. Crandall, D.D.S.', 'https://drcurtiscrandall.com', 'Lisa Chapman', 'Dental Hygienist', 'lisa@drcurtiscrandall.com', '', 'YES', 47, 'Strong dental industry match with family/cosmetic dentistry focus and 5 employees in Texas, but contact is a hygienist (influencer only, not decision-maker). Established practice since 1989 with personalized patient experience focus suggests good fit for workflow automation.', 'Curtis A. Crandall, D.D.S. is a small family-oriented general dentistry practice in Plano, TX, established in 1989 with 5 employees. They focus on cosmetic and family dentistry with personalized patient experiences and state-of-the-art technology, serving patients for over 20+ years with high patient satisfaction.', 'small', 'medium', 'Small team of 5 employees handling front desk, scheduling, recalls, and billing manually without automation, creating operational bottlenecks and staff overload', '5-employee practice, established 1989 likely legacy systems, family dentistry high recall volume, cosmetic dentistry treatment plan follow-up needs, 35+ years in practice with aging patient communication methods', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With just 5 staff managing 35+ years of patient relationships, your hygienist is probably drowning in manual recall calls.', 'hygienist overwhelm from manual recall workload in long-established practice', 'recall calls eating your day', 'Most hygienists at smaller practices spend half their non-clinical time chasing down overdue patients for recall appointments. The phone calls pile up, especially when you\'re managing 35+ years worth of patient relationships with just a few hands on deck. Meanwhile, patients who genuinely want to come back slip through the cracks because there\'s simply no bandwidth to stay on top of everyone. Does this sound familiar?', 'why I\'m following up', 'I\'m reaching back out because Calyxr specifically handles recall outreach so hygienists like you don\'t