(450, 64, '2026-03-30 13:11:03', 'Custer Star Dental Group and Orthodontics', 'https://custerstardentalgroup.com', 'Lisa Smithyman', 'Registered Dental Hygienist', 'lisa@custerstardentalgroup.com', '', 'YES', 47, 'Small Texas dental practice with good geographic fit and clear dental industry match, but limited by clinical staff contact (influencer not buyer) and very small team size of 3 employees.', 'Custer Star Dental Group and Orthodontics is a small multi-specialty practice in Frisco, Texas with 3 employees offering both general dentistry and orthodontics under one roof, indicating complex scheduling and dual-workflow management needs.', 'small', 'high', '3-person team managing dual workflows for general dentistry and orthodontics creates scheduling conflicts and overwhelms staff with manual coordination between specialties', '3 employees total, multi-specialty practice, dual workflows for general dentistry and orthodontics, small team handling complex scheduling needs', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With only 3 staff juggling both general dentistry and orthodontics patients, your team likely spends significant time manually coordinating different appointment types and recall schedules.', 'dual-specialty scheduling complexity overwhelming small team', 'general plus ortho scheduling', 'Lisa, most dual-specialty practices with small teams face the same challenge. General dentistry patients need their standard cleanings and checkups while orthodontics patients follow completely different visit patterns and timing. Three people trying to juggle both workflows usually means someone is constantly playing catch-up on scheduling, recalls get mixed up between specialties, and patient communication becomes a daily puzzle of who needs what type of follow-up when.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Lisa, I\'m following up because Calyxr handles dual-specialty patient communication automatically. Instead of your team manually tracking different recall schedules for general vs. ortho patients, our system manages both workflows simultaneously. One practice similar to Custer Star saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone after switching from manual coordination to automated specialty-specific messaging.', 'Lisa, practices with dual workflows like yours typically lose 20-25 hours weekly on manual scheduling coordination between specialties. That\'s essentially one full-time employee\'s worth of productivity going toward administrative tasks instead of patient care. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and lives in under a week. Quick question, how much time does your team currently spend each day just coordinating between general and orthodontics schedules?', 'Lisa, noticed Custer Star handles both general dentistry and orthodontics with a 3-person team. Most dual-specialty practices struggle with keeping different patient workflows organized without constant manual coordination. Does your team find themselves juggling two completely different recall and scheduling systems daily?', 'cost of manual coordination', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://custerstardentalgroup.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Custer Star Dental Group and Orthodontics', '', '3', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://custerstardentalgroup.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Ag