(452, 64, '2026-03-30 13:13:04', 'D2 Dental Associates', 'https://themaldendentist.com', 'David Hornung', 'Dentist', 'david@themaldendentist.com', '', 'YES', 64, 'Strong industry match as multi-specialty dental practice with digital focus, but contact is clinical staff rather than owner/decision-maker. Good firmographic fit with 5 employees and Massachusetts location.', 'D2 Dental Associates is a 9-year-old multi-specialty family practice in Malden, MA with 5 employees offering comprehensive dental services from general to cosmetic dentistry. Despite being \'fully digital,\' they likely have typical small practice pain points around patient communication and workflow automation.', 'small', 'medium', 'Multi-specialty 5-person team likely overwhelmed with manual patient communication and recall coordination across general, pediatric, cosmetic, and periodontal workflows', '5 employees for multi-specialty practice, general dentistry + pediatric + cosmetic + perio services, family practice with diverse age groups, 9-year established practice likely has large recall base, claims to be \'fully digital\' but no advanced patient communication platform mentioned', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 5 staff handling general, pediatric, cosmetic, and periodontal patients, your recall coordination across specialties is probably consuming significant front desk bandwidth daily.', 'multi-specialty recall coordination burden overwhelming small team', 'recall coordination across specialties', 'David, multi-specialty practices like D2 Dental face a unique challenge most single-discipline offices never see. When your front desk is juggling recall schedules for general, pediatric, cosmetic, and perio patients, each specialty has different timing requirements and patient communication needs. Many 5-person teams find themselves spending hours daily just coordinating who needs what type of follow-up and when. The manual tracking across different patient populations often means someone falls through the cracks.', 'why i\'m following up', 'David, I\'m writing because Calyxr handles exactly what I mentioned yesterday about multi-specialty recall coordination. Instead of your team manually tracking different recall schedules across general, pediatric, cosmetic, and perio patients, everything runs automatically based on each specialty\'s specific requirements. One of our multi-specialty practices saw front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. Does this sound like something that could help D2 Dental\'s daily workflow?', 'David, quick math on what manual specialty coordination typically costs practices like yours. If your 5-person team spends even 2 hours daily on recall coordination across specialties, that\'s 520 hours annually at $25/hour, or roughly $13,000 in labor costs. Plus the revenue lost when patients slip through specialty-specific recall gaps. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week. Worth exploring how this applies to D2 Dental\'s specific workflow?', 'David, noticed D2 Dental handles multiple specialties with a 5-person team. Most practices that size find recall coordination across general, pediatric, cosmetic, and perio workflows consumes significant daily bandwidth. How are you currently managing the different timing requirements for each specialty\'s patient follow-up?', 'cost of manual coordination', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://themaldendentist.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'D2 Dental Associates', '', '5', '', '', 'Massachusetts', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://themaldendentist.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/d2-dental-associates', '+1 781-397-9229', 'david@themaldendentist.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/david-hornung-579b8b63', 'themaldendentist.com', 'hospital & health care', 'general dentistry, pedodontist, cosmetic dentistry, periodontis, hospitals & health care, medical practice, hospital & health care, cosmetics, beauty, apparel & fashion, barbers, beauty & spas', 'Our modern, multi-specialty dental practice is conveniently located in Malden Square and has easy access to public transit. The team of D2 Dental Associates is passionate about providing only the highest level of dental care for all ages. We use the latest techniques and only the best dental materials to care for our patients\' smiles and oral health.  Our office is fully digital, enabling a faster and a more comfortable way to identify and treat dental conditions. D2 Dental is a family practice,', 'Malden', '2015', '', 'Dentist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(453, 64, '2026-03-30 13:14:02', 'Dallas Functional Dentistry', 'https://dallasfunctionaldentistry.com', 'Sarah Tevis', 'Dentist', 'sarah@dallasfunctionaldentistry.com', '', 'YES', 48, 'Strong dental industry match in ideal Texas location with 5 employees, but limited by clinical staff contact rather than owner/decision-maker. Functional dentistry focus suggests holistic patient care approach that could benefit from automated communication workflows.', 'Dallas Functional Dentistry is a small 5-employee holistic dental practice in Dallas, TX focusing on complete-health dentistry and systemic health connections. This appears to be a boutique practice with an integrative medicine approach rather than traditional volume-based dentistry.', 'small', 'medium', '5-person boutique practice likely struggling with manual patient communication and recall management while trying to maintain personalized holistic care approach', '5-employee small team, holistic/functional specialty requiring patient education, boutique practice model, complete-health focus needs extensive patient communication', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', '5-person holistic practice balancing personalized complete-health consultations with manual recall follow-ups limits time for comprehensive systemic health discussions.', 'boutique practice administrative burden reducing patient consultation depth', 'recall systems in boutique practices', 'Many functional dentistry practices find themselves caught between two competing priorities. On one side, patients need those deeper systemic health conversations that set holistic practices apart. On the other side, recall lists keep growing with patients who\'ve gone 8, 10, even 12 months without their preventive visits. The manual phone calls and reminder systems that worked at 200 active patients start eating into chair time when the practice grows. It\'s frustrating because those overdue recall patients represent both missed revenue and missed opportunities to catch health issues before they become systemic problems.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is because of Calyxr. We specifically help boutique practices like Dallas Functional Dentistry solve the recall gap without losing that personal touch your patients expect. Instead of your team spending hours calling overdue patients, Calyxr handles the outreach automatically while you focus on comprehensive consultations. One holistic practice we work with saw no-shows dropped from 28% to under 12% in 90 days while their dentist gained back 6 hours a week previously spent on scheduling coordination. Would something like that make sense for a 5-person practice?', 'Quick math on what delayed recall patients cost a functional practice. If 40 overdue patients represent $120 each in preventive revenue, that\'s $4,800 sitting idle this month. More importantly, those are patients who trust your holistic approach but aren\'t getting the regular monitoring that catches issues early. The longer the gap, the more likely they drift to conventional practices for convenience. Calyxr works with your existing PMS, no long-term contracts, and most practices see results within the first week. Worth exploring what this would look like for Dallas Functional Dentistry?', 'Sarah, noticed Dallas Functional Dentistry focuses on systemic health approaches. Many boutique practices tell us their biggest challenge is balancing time for comprehensive consultations with manual recall follow-up. Curious if this resonates with your experience running a 5-person holistic practice?', 'cost of waiting', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dallasfunctionaldentistry.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Dallas Functional Dentistry', '', '5', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dallasfunctionaldentistry.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/dallas-functional-dentistry', '+1 214-363-4414', 'sarah@dallasfunctionaldentistry.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/dallasfunctionaldentistry', 'dallasfunctionaldentistry.com', 'medical practice', 'medical practices, hospital & health care', 'As a complete-health focused dental practice in Dallas, we strive to create healthy and beautiful smiles that match your individuality while achieving exceptional oral and systemic health.', 'Dallas', '', '', 'Dentist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(454, 64, '2026-03-30 13:15:04', 'Dallas Prosthodontics', 'https://dallasprosthodontics.com', 'Amanda Prosth', 'Dental Assistant', 'amanda@dallasprosthodontics.com', '', 'YES', 61, 'Strong specialty dental practice fit with prosthodontics focus and solid size/revenue, but contact is clinical staff influencer rather than decision-maker. High-value specialty procedures suggest good automation ROI potential.', 'Dallas Prosthodontics is a specialized prosthodontic practice with two board-certified specialists focusing on complex restorative cases including dental implants, All-on-Four treatments, and full-mouth reconstructions. With 7 employees and $26.5M revenue, this is a high-volume specialty practice handling complex treatment coordination.', 'small', 'high', 'Complex treatment coordination across multiple specialists with patients requiring extensive insurance pre-authorization and eligibility verification for high-value prosthodontic procedures', 'high-revenue specialty practice, complex restorative cases, All-on-Four treatments, implant procedures, multiple specialists, treatment coordination needs, high-value procedures requiring pre-authorization', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With $26.5M in complex prosthodontic cases, your front desk is likely drowning in All-on-Four and full-mouth reconstruction insurance verifications.', 'high-value prosthodontic procedure VOB burden crushing small front desk team', 'all-on-four insurance nightmares', 'Most prosthodontic practices with complex cases like full-mouth reconstructions and All-on-Four spend 3-5 hours per patient just on insurance verification calls. The pre-auth paperwork alone for a $40K treatment plan can take your front desk team two full days, and that\'s before the insurance company requests additional documentation or changes their coverage requirements mid-treatment. When you\'re coordinating between multiple specialists and managing high-value cases, the manual verification process becomes a bottleneck that delays patient care and ties up your entire administrative workflow.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We built something specifically for practices handling complex treatment coordination and high-value insurance verifications. Instead of your team spending hours on hold with insurance companies for each prosthodontic case, Calyxr confirms insurance eligibility in 12 seconds before every appointment, including coverage limits and pre-auth requirements. One prosthodontic practice saw their front desk reclaim 15+ hours a week on verification calls alone, which meant more time helping patients understand their treatment options instead of being stuck on administrative tasks.', 'Every hour your team spends on manual insurance verification is an hour not spent on patient care coordination or treatment planning support. At 15-20 hours per week on verification calls, that\'s roughly $18,000 in lost productivity annually, not counting the treatment delays when insurance requirements change mid-case. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system and requires no IT setup. Would it make sense to see how this handles your All-on-Four and full-mouth reconstruction verifications specifically?', 'Noticed Dallas Prosthodontics handles a lot of complex cases. Your front desk is probably spending hours daily on insurance verifications for those All-on-Four and full-mouth reconstructions. How are you managing the pre-auth workload with such high-value treatments?', 'cost of manual verification', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dallasprosthodontics.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Dallas Prosthodontics', '26.5M', '7', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichmen