(461, 64, '2026-03-30 13:21:53', 'DD Family Dentistry', 'https://ddfamilydentistrytx.com', 'Durga Devarakonda', 'Family Dentist', 'durga@ddfamilydentistrytx.com', '', 'YES', 42, 'Small Texas dental practice with clinical owner who likely makes all decisions, but limited scale with only 3 employees suggests minimal automation needs and budget constraints.', 'DD Family Dentistry is a small solo practice in Carrollton, TX with 3 employees, serving patients of all ages including special needs patients. Dr. Durga Devarakonda operates a patient-centric general dentistry practice with Saturday hours and emphasis on preventive care.', 'small', 'medium', 'With only 3 employees total including the doctor, the front desk is overwhelmed handling patient communication, appointment reminders, and insurance verification manually', 'solo practice, 3 total employees, special needs patients requiring extra communication, Saturday hours extending operational burden, preventive care emphasis requiring consistent recall outreach', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'With just 3 employees handling both special needs patients and Saturday hours, your front desk is likely drowning in manual insurance verifications.', 'front desk overwhelm from manual VOB burden in understaffed solo practice', 'insurance checks eating time', 'Many small dental practices with Saturday hours find their front desk drowning in manual insurance verifications. Three-person teams especially feel this, spending hours each week calling carriers to confirm benefits before appointments. The special needs patients require extra attention, but half the front desk time goes to insurance calls that could happen automatically. It leaves little bandwidth for the patient experience work that actually matters.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The insurance verification bottleneck is exactly why I\'m writing about Calyxr. It handles all your eligibility checks automatically, confirming benefits in 12 seconds before every appointment witho