(464, 64, '2026-03-30 13:23:58', 'DelliGatti and Milewski Orthodontic Group', 'https://dmorthogroup.com', 'Michael Milewski', 'Orthodontist', 'milewski@dmorthogroup.com', '', 'YES', 67, 'Strong orthodontic specialty fit with multi-location practice established since 1975, though contact is clinical staff rather than owner/decision-maker, limiting persona score.', 'DelliGatti and Milewski Orthodontic Group is an established 2-location orthodontic practice founded in 1975 with 7 employees, serving Montgomery County, Bucks County, and Northeast Philadelphia with comprehensive orthodontic care for adults and teens.', 'small', 'medium', 'Multi-location orthodontic practice with 7 staff needs automated patient communication to manage high-volume appointment scheduling, treatment plan check-ins, and recall coordination across two offices without overwhelming their small team', 'multi-location practice, orthodontic specialty, 7 employees, established since 1975, comprehensive adult and teen care, likely high appointment volume', 'medium', 'Economic Buyer', 'high', 'Two-location orthodontic group with just 7 staff handling Invisalign and traditional braces likely drowns in appointment coordination and phase treatment check-ins.', 'small team overwhelmed by multi-location orthodontic scheduling complexity', 'two locations seven staff', 'Most orthodontic groups with multiple locations hit the same wall around 7-8 staff members. The appointment coordination alone becomes unmanageable when you\'re tracking Invisalign check-ins, adjustment appointments, and phase progressions across two offices. Add in the constant patient questions about next steps and treatment timelines, and your team spends more time on phones than with patients. Many practices this size find their staff drowning in the coordination rather than focusing on treatment quality.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We handle all the appointment coordination and treatment phase communication for multi-location orthodontic practices like yours. Instead of your 7 staff members juggling two offices worth of Invisalign check-ins and adjustment scheduling, patients get automated updates about their next phase, appointment reminders, and treatment progress check-ins. One orthodontic group saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. Curious how this would change things for DelliGatti and Milewski?', 'Every week your team spends coordinating appointments across two locations is revenue opportunity lost. With 7 staff handling treatment phases manually, that\'s roughly $3,200 monthly in labor costs just on patient communication tasks. Meanwhile, patients fall behind on Invisalign compliance or miss adjustment windows because follow-up gets lost in the shuffle. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system and goes live in under a week. Worth exploring what automated treatment coordination would mean for your team\'s bandwidth?', 'Most orthodontic groups hit a coordination wall around 7 staff when managing two locations. The Invisalign check-ins and phase tracking alone probably consume half your team\'s day. How are you handling treatment progression communication across both offices right now?', 'cost of manual coordination', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dmorthogroup.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'DelliGatti and Milewski Orthodontic Group', '', '7', '', '', 'Pennsylvania', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dmorthogroup.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/cichetti-and-delligatti-orthodontics-p-c-', '', 'milewski@dmorthogroup.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-milewski-4a6462117', 'dmorthogroup.com', 'health, wellness & fitness', 'pediatric orthodontics, invisalign for teens, orthodontics, braces, invisalign, adult invisalign, wellness & fitness services, orthodontic treatment, orthodontic consultation, orthodontic specialists, digital orthodontics, phase i treatment', 'Our doctors have been providing the utmost orthodontic care since 1975. Our doctors are board certified or board qualified in orthodontics, having graduated from orthodontic specialty schools at the University of Pennsylvania, University of North Carolina and Temple University. As strong believers in continuing education, our orthodontists strictly adhere to Pennsylvania requirements for ongoing education after graduation.\n\nThe DelliGatti and Milewski Orthodontic Group has two offices and they a', 'Ambler', '1975', '', 'Orthodontist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(465, 64, '2026-03-30 13:24:55', 'Dennis E. Stansbury DDS', 'https://stansburydental.com', 'Karen Stansbury', 'Dental Office Manager', 'smiles@stansburydental.com', '', 'YES', 72, 'Strong dental practice fit in Texas with 4 employees and $17.5M revenue, led by dental office manager. High revenue suggests multi-location or high-volume operation that would benefit from workflow automation.', 'Dennis E. Stansbury DDS is a long-established general dentistry practice in Tyler, Texas that was acquired by Heaton Dental group in January 2024, transitioning from a solo practice to part of a multi-location dental organization.', 'small', 'medium', 'Recent acquisition by Heaton Dental group creates urgent need to standardize patient communication and operational workflows across multiple locations while maintaining existing patient relationships', 'recent DSO acquisition, transitioning from solo to multi-location, 4-person team managing general dentistry, legacy solo practice systems likely incompatible with group standards', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'Heaton\'s recent acquisition of your Tyler location likely means standardizing patient communication protocols across their growing network without losing your established patient relationships.', 'post-acquisition communication standardization challenge while preserving patient retention', 'heaton acquisition changes', 'Karen, noticed Heaton recently brought your Tyler location into their network. Most dental groups face the same challenge after acquisitions, trying to get all locations speaking the same language to patients while keeping the personal touch each practice built over years. The front desk teams often end up juggling different reminder systems, confirmation processes, and patient communication styles across locations. Patients start noticing inconsistencies pretty quickly.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Karen, following up because Calyxr specifically helps dental groups like Heaton standardize patient communication after acquisitions without losing what made each location special. Instead of forcing every practice to change how they talk to patients, we create consistent automated touchpoints that feel personal to each location. One group saw 70% reduction in manual front office tasks without adding headcount when they unified their patient communication across 8 newly acquired practices. Does Heaton have a plan for standardizing communication across all locations yet?', 'Karen, most groups that wait to standardize communication post-acquisition end up losing 15-20% of established patients within the first year. Each location doing things differently creates confusion, and patients start questioning if they\'re getting the same quality care. The front desk teams burn out trying to manage multiple systems and processes. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week with no IT setup required. Would it be worth seeing how other dental groups handled this same transition?', 'Karen, saw Heaton acquired your Tyler practice recently. Most groups struggle with keeping patient communication consistent across locations after acquisitions without losing the personal relationships each practice built. How is Heaton planning to handle patient communication standardization?', 'cost of waiting', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://stansburydental.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Dennis E. Stansbury DDS', '17.5M', '4', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://stansburydental.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (