 different communication styles, every provider uses the same patient engagement system. Implant recalls, Invisalign check-ins, and sleep apnea follow-ups all run automatically with consistent messaging. One practice with three oral surgeons saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. Does this sound like something worth exploring at Dentistry by RSE?', 'When each provider handles patient communication differently, you lose patients in the handoff. A $4.5M practice typically loses $50K annually just from specialty patients who don\'t complete treatment because follow-up wasn\'t consistent. The front desk spends hours daily trying to coordinate between providers instead of focusing on patient experience. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week. Would you be open to seeing how this looks for a multi-provider practice like yours?', 'Most multi-provider practices struggle with coordinating patient communication across specialties. Implant patients get handled differently than Invisalign patients, and the front desk becomes the coordination hub for everything. Does this ring true at Dentistry by RSE?', 'cost of coordination chaos', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dentistrybyrse.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Dentistry by RSE', '4.5M', '10', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dentistrybyrse.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI 