(470, 64, '2026-03-30 13:28:08', 'Dentistry For Health New York', 'https://dentistryforhealthny.com', 'Reid Winick', 'Holistic Dentist', 'reid@dfhny.com', '', 'YES', 58, 'Dental practice in high-value NY market with 6 employees fits size profile, but contact is clinical staff rather than decision-maker. Holistic dentistry angle suggests premium patient base that values communication.', '6-employee holistic dental practice in NYC specializing in mercury-free, sustainable dentistry with complex biological treatments. Uses Birdeye for reviews but likely has manual patient communication workflows for their specialized patient population requiring extensive education and follow-up.', 'small', 'high', 'Manual patient education and follow-up for complex biological treatments requiring extensive communication that a 6-person team cannot scale effectively', '6 employees, holistic/biological specialty, NYC location, Birdeye competitor detected, complex treatment education needs, sustainable/mercury-free positioning requires patient education', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'Your biological treatment protocols likely require 3-4 patient touchpoints per case, but manual follow-up is eating into clinical time for complex mercury-free procedures.', 'holistic treatment complexity requiring extensive patient education overwhelming small team capacity', 'biological protocol follow-up', 'Most biological dental practices find themselves caught between two problems. Complex mercury-free procedures and biocompatible protocols require multiple patient touchpoints per case, but clinical time gets consumed by manual education follow-up instead of chair time. A 6-person team can only stretch so far when each biological treatment needs 3-4 separate communications to ensure proper healing protocols are followed.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We help biological practices handle patient education sequences automatically so your clinical time stays focused on complex procedures instead of follow-up communications. One holistic practice saw their front desk team reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone, letting them focus on biocompatible treatment coordination instead. Does this sound like something worth exploring for your biological protocols?', 'Manual patient education follow-up for biological treatments typically costs practices 2-3 hours of clinical team time per complex case. That\'s chair time that could be spent on mercury-free procedures instead of explaining detox protocols over the phone. Calyxr works with your existing systems and goes live in under a week with no IT setup required. Would it make sense to see how this applies to your biological practice workflows?', 'Most biological practices struggle with the same thing - complex mercury-free cases need multiple patient touchpoints, but manual follow-up eats into clinical time. How are you handling patient education sequences for your biocompatible protocols at Dentistry For Health?', 'cost of manual follow-up', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dentistryforhealthny.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Dentistry For Health New York', '', '6', '', '', 'New York', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dentistryforhealthny.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (cl