(473, 64, '2026-03-30 13:31:14', 'Denville Dental Group', 'https://denvilledentalgroup.com', 'Aaliyah Elliott', 'Registered Dental Hygienist', 'aaliyah@denvilledentalgroup.com', '', 'YES', 45, 'Small dental practice (6 employees) with good geographic fit in New Jersey, but primary contact is a dental hygienist rather than owner/decision-maker. Practice appears patient-focused but lacks clear operational pain signals or technology stack visibility.', 'Denville Dental Group is a small general dental practice in Denville with 6 employees, led by Dr. Matarazzo, positioning itself as affordable modern dentistry in a caring environment with a hygienist as the primary contact.', 'small', 'medium', 'Six-employee general dental practice likely struggles with high administrative burden on small front desk team managing patient communication, recalls, and scheduling manually', 'small team size (6 employees), general dentistry specialty, hygienist as primary patient contact, affordable positioning suggests high patient volume relative to staff', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With only 6 employees, your hygienist is likely juggling patient care with recall coordination instead of maximizing chair time.', 'small team operational efficiency and hygienist productivity optimization', 'hygiene recall coordination burden', 'Most hygienists in smaller practices end up wearing two hats, bouncing between patient care and chasing down overdue recall appointments. It\'s tough when you\'re trying to focus on preventive care but also tracking who\'s due for cleanings, making reminder calls, and coordinating with the front desk. The recall coordination piece can easily eat up time that should be spent with patients in the chair.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr handles all the recall coordination automatically so you can stay focused on patient care instead of administrative tasks. The system reaches out to overdue patients, manages the entire recall process,