(477, 64, '2026-03-30 13:35:10', 'Dr. Alyssa Orthodontics', 'https://dralyssaortho.com', 'Alyssa Emory-Carter', 'Owner/Orthodontist', 'dralyssa@alyssaortho.com', '', 'YES', 78, 'Perfect industry match with orthodontics practice in Texas, clinical owner decision-maker, and 4-year established practice showing growth potential. Strong fit despite smaller size due to specialty focus and geographic location.', 'Dr. Alyssa Orthodontics is a 5-person orthodontic practice in Fort Worth, founded in 2020, serving the Texoma region with specialty focus on clear aligners, sleep-disordered breathing, and TMJ treatment for both pediatric and adult patients.', 'small', 'medium', '5-person orthodontic practice likely struggling with manual appointment scheduling, recall coordination for long-term ortho patients, and high patient communication volume across pediatric and adult populations without automation', 'small 5-person team, orthodontics specialty with long treatment cycles, pediatric and adult mix requiring different communication approaches, founded 2020 so likely still scaling operations, clear aligner patients need frequent check-ins', 'medium', 'Champion / Economic Buyer', 'high', 'Five-person ortho practice managing 18+ month treatment cycles likely has recall coordination gaps between adjustment appointments.', 'orthodontic recall coordination complexity with long treatment cycles', '18 month treatment cycles', 'Most orthodontic practices I see are great at getting patients started but struggle with something that happens around month 8-12. Patients start missing their adjustment appointments more frequently. The gaps between visits stretch from 6 weeks to 8, then 10, sometimes longer. Treatment timelines extend, retention compliance drops, and case completion gets pushed out by months. It\'s not that patients don\'t care about their results, they just fall out of the routine without consistent touchpoints between visits.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Following up because of Calyxr. We help orthodontic practices maintain consistent patient engagement throughout those long treatment cycles. Instead of your team manually tracking who\'s overdue for adjustments, Calyxr automatically reaches patients across multiple channels when appointments are missed. One practice similar to yours saw no-shows dropped from 28% to under 12% in 90 days. Curious if maintaining appointment consistency has been a challenge at Dr. Alyssa Orthodontics?', 'Each missed adjustment appointment typically extends treatment by 2-4 weeks. For a 5-person practice seeing 100 active ortho cases, even a 15% miss rate means 45 extra months of treatment time across your patient base annually. That\'s capacity you could use for new starts instead of extended cases. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system, no IT setup required. Worth exploring how this might help your case completion timeline?', 'Hey Alyssa, I work with orthodontic practices dealing with appointment gaps during those long treatment cycles. Patients tend to fall off routine around month 8-12, extending case timelines. Is maintaining consistent adjustment schedules something your practice navigates?', 'cost of gaps', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dralyssaortho.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Dr. Alyssa Orthodontics', '', '5', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://dralyssaortho.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → C