(478, 64, '2026-03-30 13:36:13', 'Dr. Doug Smith, Orthodontist', 'https://meadvilleorthodontics.com', 'Doug Smith', 'Orthodontist', 'drdoug@meadvilleorthodontics.com', '', 'YES', 71, 'Strong orthodontic practice fit with excellent revenue ($17.3M) and established operations since 1993. Dr. Smith as orthodontist-owner is ideal decision-maker persona, though practice size (7 employees) suggests limited operational complexity.', 'Douglas N. Smith Orthodontics is a 30-year-old dual-location orthodontic practice serving Meadville and Hermitage, PA with 7 employees generating $17.3M revenue. They offer traditional braces, clear aligners, and early treatment with advanced technology focus.', 'small', 'high', 'Two-location orthodontic practice with 7 staff managing $17.3M revenue likely overwhelmed by recall management for multi-phase treatment plans and appointment scheduling across locations', 'dual-location practice, orthodontic specialty requiring long-term patient relationships, high revenue-to-staff ratio indicating operational efficiency needs, multi-phase treatment planning requiring systematic follow-up', 'medium', 'Champion / Economic Buyer', 'high', 'With 7 staff managing $17.3M across two locations, your team likely spends hours manually coordinating recall timing for multi-phase ortho cases.', 'dual-location orthodontic recall coordination burden with small staff', 'ortho recall coordination nightmare', 'Most two-location orthodontic practices with high revenue volume hit the same wall around recall management. Multi-phase treatment plans mean dozens of patients need perfectly timed follow-ups, but staff at location A doesn\'t know what happened at location B yesterday. The manual coordination between sites eats up hours daily, and patients slip through cracks between adjustment appointments. With 7 team members managing complex case schedules across locations, someone\'s always chasing down where each patient stands in their treatment timeline.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We handle orthodontic recall coordination across multiple locations automatically, so your staff stops playing phone tag about which patient needs what when. One practice saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone because the system tracks every phase of treatment and reaches patients at exactly the right intervals. Your team can focus on patient care instead of manually coordinating recall schedules between Meadville locations.', 'Every week your team spends manually coordinating ortho recalls across locations costs roughly $2,400 in staff time, plus whatever revenue walks out the door when patients miss their adjustment windows. At $17.3M revenue with complex multi-phase cases, even a 3% improvement in recall consistency could mean $500K+ annually. The system works with your existing practice management software, no long-term contracts. Would it make sense to see how this handles your specific recall coordination challenges?', 'Doug, noticed you\'re managing orthodontic recalls across two locations with a smaller team. Most practices your size struggle with the manual coordination between sites for multi-phase treatment timing. How are you handling recall scheduling consistency between locations currently?', 'cost of manual coordination', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://meadvilleorthodontics.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Dr. Doug Smith, Orthodontist', '17.3M', '7', '', '', 'Pennsylvania', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://meadvilleorthodontics.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/dr-doug-smith-orthodontist', '+1 724-981-8421', 'drdoug@meadvilleorthodontics.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/doug-smith-91972741', 'meadvilleorthodontics.com', 'medical practice', 'orthodontics & braces, orthodontics, braces, medical practices, oral care, dental website compliance, patient experience, email communication, alternative communication methods, treatment planning, dental practice, accessible dental website', 'At the office of Dr. Douglas N. Smith, he and his qualified team understand what patients expect from their orthodontic treatment – genuine results from an experienced orthodontist they can trust! Patients working with Dr. Smith can count on receiving quality orthodontic care from a dedicated, hardworking staff who takes time to know and understand the needs of their patients. Dr. Smith specializes in adult and child orthodontics, including braces, SmartClip™ self-ligating braces, ClearCorrect™', 'Meadville', '1993', '', 'Orthodontist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
