(486, 64, '2026-03-30 13:43:24', 'Elara Orthodontics', 'https://elaraorthodontics.com', 'Sam Elkenawy', 'Orthodontist', 'drsam@elaraorthodontics.com', '', 'YES', 67, 'Strong dental specialty match (orthodontics) in high-value Texas market with 3-person team size ideal for automation, but contact is clinical staff rather than owner/decision-maker which limits immediate buying power.', 'Elara Orthodontics is a specialized orthodontic practice with two Texas locations (Richmond and Houston) founded in 2019, led by two board-certified orthodontists serving families with braces and Invisalign treatments.', 'small', 'medium', 'Small 3-person team managing complex orthodontic scheduling across two locations with lengthy treatment plans and frequent appointment adjustments without automation', '2 locations with only 3 total staff, orthodontic specialty with complex multi-visit treatment plans, Invisalign coordination requiring frequent check-ins, family-focused practice likely high appointment volume', 'high', 'Economic Buyer', 'high', 'Managing 18-24 month orthodontic treatment plans across Richmond and Houston with just three staff creates constant appointment juggling and missed adjustment reminders.', 'multi-location orthodontic scheduling complexity with minimal staffing', '18-month treatment plans, 3 people', 'Most orthodontic practices with multiple locations face the same challenge: small teams trying to coordinate complex treatment schedules across different sites. When you\'re managing 18-24 month patient journeys with just a few staff members, appointment adjustments become a constant juggling act. The manual coordination between locations eats up clinical time, and patients miss adjustment appointments when reminders fall through the cracks. Many practices find their three-person teams spending more time on scheduling logistics than patient care.', 'why i\'m following up', 'I\'m writing because Calyxr specifically handles multi-location orthodontic scheduling complexity. Instead of your team manually coordinating treatment plans across Richmond and Houston, the system automatically manages appointment sequences, adjustment reminders, and cross-location scheduling conflicts. One practice with similar dual-location challenges saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. The system understands orthodontic treatment phases and keeps patients on track without your staff constantly monitoring schedules.', 'When small teams manually manage complex orthodontic schedules across multiple locations, practices typically lose 20-30 hours weekly to coordination tasks alone. That\'s nearly a full-time employee worth of productivity going to administrative work instead of patient care. Each missed adjustment appointment extends treatment timelines and impacts case flow. Would it make sense to see how other orthodontic practices eliminated this scheduling burden? The system works with your existing software and lives in under a week.', 'Managing 18-month treatment plans across two locations with a three-person team sounds like constant appointment juggling. Most orthodontic practices face similar scheduling complexity when treatment spans multiple locations. How are you currently handling the coordination between Richmond and Houston?', 'cost of manual coordination', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://elaraorthodontics.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Elara Orthodontics', '', '3', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://elaraorthodontics.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/elara-orthodontics', '+1 713-999-1099', 'drsam@elaraorthodontics.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/sam-elkenawy-829867a1', 'elaraorthodontics.com', 'medical practice', 'orthodontics orthodontist dentistry dental braces invisalign retainers, medical practices, hospital & health care', 'A state-of-the-art dental specialty practice providing leading-edge orthodontics for all ages in a warm, welcoming, and family-friendly environment', 'Richmond', '2019', '', 'Orthodontist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(487, 64, '2026-03-30 13:44:19', 'Elden Family Dental', 'https://eldenfamilydental.com', 'Bob Meer', 'General Dentist Related to Search Terms in Your Query', 'bmeer@alban.org', '', 'YES', 47, 'Dental practice with strong industry match and US location, but limited by General Dentist contact who is an influencer rather than decision-maker. Missing firmographic data prevents higher scoring.', 'Elden Family Dental is a Virginia-based general dentistry practice serving families, likely operating as a small to mid-size practice with typical family dental services and mixed insurance patient base.', 'small', 'medium', 'Small family dental practice likely struggling with manual patient recall and appointment reminders, leading to scheduling gaps and revenue loss from missed hygiene appointments', 'family dental practice, Virginia-based general dentistry, mixed insurance patient base, small to mid-size practice', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Small family practices like yours typically lose 15-20% of hygiene recall revenue to manual phone outreach that never connects with busy parents.', 'hygiene recall revenue leakage from manual outreach inefficiency', 'hygiene recall gaps', 'Bob, most family practices see 40% of their hygiene patients go overdue without consistent recall follow-up. The front desk makes a few calls, maybe sends some postcards, but busy parents miss the voicemails or forget to call back. Meanwhile, those empty hygiene slots represent predictable revenue that just sits there. It\'s especially tough in smaller practices where the team is already stretched thin handling everything else.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Bob, following up because we built Calyxr specifically for family practices dealing with recall gaps. Instead of your team spending hours on manual calls, patients get reached through their preferred channel (text, email, voice) until they respond. One of our family practices saw their hygiene recall revenue recover by 18% in the first quarter alone because patients actually got the message and booked. Worth a quick look?', 'Bob, if 40% of your hygiene patients stay overdue for months, that\'s roughly $8,000-12,000 in lost production per month for most family practices. The longer patients go without cleanings, the more likely they drift to competitors or need more complex treatment. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week. Curious how many of your hygiene patients are currently overdue?', 'Hi Bob, noticed Elden Family Dental likely deals with the same recall challenge most family practices face - patients going months overdue because manual follow-up just doesn\'t connect with busy parents. How many of your hygiene slots typically sit empty each week?', 'cost of empty chairs', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://eldenfamilydental.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://eldenfamilydental.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'bmeer@alban.org', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/eldenfamilydental', '', '', '',