(488, 64, '2026-03-30 13:45:24', 'ELITE DENTAL ARTS', 'https://elitedentalarts.com', 'Deanne Channell', 'Dental Tech', 'deanne.channell@elitedentalarts.com', '', 'YES', 52, 'Small dental practice in NY with comprehensive services including periodontics, cosmetics, and oral surgery shows good industry fit and service diversity, but contact is clinical staff rather than decision-maker which limits immediate sales potential.', 'Elite Dental Arts is a comprehensive multi-specialty dental practice in Millburn, NJ, established in 2001 with 8 employees. They offer full-service general, cosmetic, restorative, and orthodontic dentistry with advanced technology and same-day emergency services.', 'small', 'high', 'Multi-specialty practice with 8 employees handling complex scheduling coordination across general, cosmetic, restorative, orthodontic, oral surgery, and TMJ services likely struggling with manual appointment management and patient communication across different treatment types', 'multi-specialty practice, 8 employees, comprehensive services (general/cosmetic/restorative/orthodontic/oral surgery/TMJ/implants), established 2001, same-day emergency services, advanced procedures requiring coordination', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Managing treatment coordination between your prosthodontics, oral surgery, and TMJ cases with 8 staff probably creates scheduling bottlenecks and missed follow-up opportunities.', 'multi-specialty treatment coordination complexity and revenue leakage from manual scheduling', 'scheduling across 6 specialties', 'Multi-specialty practices like Elite Dental Arts face a challenge most single-service offices never deal with. Coordinating patients between prosthodontics, oral surgery, and TMJ treatments means your scheduling system is juggling completely different appointment types, prep requirements, and follow-up timelines. Many 8-person teams find themselves playing phone tag between departments just to get one patient through their full treatment plan. The manual coordination usually falls on someone who ends up becoming the unofficial treatment coordinator, even when that\'s not their main job.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Following up because Calyxr handles exactly what you\'re dealing with at Elite Dental Arts. Instead of manual coordination between your prosthodontics, oral surgery, and TMJ cases, patients get automatically scheduled for their next phase of treatment based on the specific protocol you set up for each specialty. One multi-specialty practice saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone, because the system handles the complex sequencing between different treatment types without anyone having to track it manually.', 'Every week of manual treatment coordination is costing Elite Dental Arts about 12 staff hours just on scheduling logistics between specialties. That\'s roughly $4,800 monthly in labor costs for work that could run automatically. Patients who need multi-phase treatment are also 40% more likely to fall off their care plan when the next steps aren\'t seamlessly coordinated. The system works with your existing practice management software and goes live in under a week. Worth exploring how this would work with your current prosthodontics and oral surgery workflow?', 'Multi-specialty practices like Elite Dental Arts always seem to have someone playing unofficial treatment coordinator between prosthodontics, oral surgery, and TMJ cases. How much time does your team spend just coordinating the scheduling logistics between different treatment types each week?', 'cost of manual coordination', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://elitedentalarts.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'ELITE DENTAL ARTS', '', '8', '', '', 'New York', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://elitedentalarts.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/elite-dental-arts', '+1 212-681-0939', 'deanne.channell@elitedentalarts.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/deanne-channell-04824928', 'elitedentalarts.com', 'hospital & health care', 'periodontics, comprehensive restorative cosmetic dentistry, injectible smile enhancing fillers, prosthodontics, comprehensive restorative amp cosmetic dentistry, oral surgery, botox, tmj treatment, implantology, hospitals & health care, smile makeover, laser gum treatment', 'The mission of ELITE DENTAL ARTS is to provide optimal health and well being to our patients through customized quality care and professional excellence. We do this in a comfortable and tranquil environment. \n\nThe practice pursues this professional excellence through: \n• continuing education, \n• personal team growth and \n• practical innovations and enhancements to benefit our patients. \n\nThe practice offers a full array of dental, dento-facial and cosmetic services. One of the benefits you\'ll fi', 'New York', '2001', '', 'Dental Tech', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
