(490, 65, '2026-03-30 14:05:36', 'ELLYSSE CANALES DDS PC', 'https://san-antonio-dentist.net', 'Ellysse Canales', 'General Dentist', 'canales@san-antonio-dentist.net', '', 'YES', 42, 'Solo dental practice in Texas with General Dentist contact shows basic industry fit but limited scale and decision-maker access. Small practice may benefit from patient communication automation but contact is influencer-level, not owner.', '24th Street Dental Care is a solo general dentistry practice in San Antonio, Texas, founded in 2010 and led by Dr. Ellysse Canales. The practice operates with minimal staff (likely 1-2 employees) and focuses on restorative, cosmetic, and preventative dentistry in an underserved area.', 'small', 'medium', 'Solo dentist with minimal staff handling all front desk duties manually including appointment scheduling, insurance verification, and patient follow-up calls', '1 employee count, solo practice, general dentistry in underserved area, manual operations burden on doctor/minimal staff', 'high', 'Champion / Economic Buyer', 'high', 'Solo practice with one employee means Dr. Canales is likely handling insurance verification calls herself instead of seeing patients.', 'solo dentist clinical time displacement by administrative burden', 'insurance calls eating chair time', 'Solo practices face an impossible choice every day. Spend 20 minutes calling insurance companies to verify benefits, or risk treating a patient whose coverage lapsed last month. Most solo dentists end up making these calls themselves between patients, which means fewer appointment slots and longer days. The front desk person is already juggling scheduling and checkout, so insurance verification falls to the doctor. It\'s backwards, but it\'s reality for most single-doctor practices.', 'why i\'m following up', 'I\'m writing because Calyxr handles insurance eligibility verification automatically, so you never have to make those calls again. Every patient gets their benefits confirmed before they walk in, without any manual work from your team. One solo practice in Texas saw their insurance eligibility confirmed in 12 seconds before every appointment, which freed up 8 hours a week of doctor time that went straight back to patient care. Worth a look?', 'A solo dentist making insurance calls personally costs about $180 per hour in lost production time. If you\'re spending even 30 minutes a day on verification calls, that\'s $22,500 in missed revenue annually. Meanwhile, patients with expired benefits create write-offs and collection headaches. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system and goes live in under a week. What would an extra 8 hours of chair time be worth to your practice?', 'Solo practices get stuck with an impossible choice - make insurance calls yourself or risk treating patients with expired benefits. Most doctors end up doing verification calls between patients, which kills productivity. How are you handling insurance verification at your practice?', 'cost of those insurance calls', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://san-antonio-dentist.net) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'ELLYSSE CANALES DDS PC', '', '1', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://san-antonio-dentist.net) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-