(491, 65, '2026-03-30 14:06:43', 'Elmbrook General Dentistry SC', 'https://elmbrookgeneraldentistry.com', 'Rose Pham', 'Dentist', 'drpham@elmbrookgeneraldentistry.com', '', 'YES', 62, 'Strong dental industry match with good employee count (9) and Wisconsin location, but contact is clinical staff rather than decision-maker which limits immediate conversion potential.', 'Elmbrook General Dentistry SC is a 25-year established family dental practice in Brookfield, Wisconsin serving both adult and pediatric patients with comprehensive general dentistry services. With 9 employees and $25.9M revenue, they operate as a mid-size practice with extended hours 7am-6pm suggesting high patient volume.', 'mid-size', 'high', 'With $25.9M revenue and only 9 employees, this high-volume family practice likely has overwhelmed front desk staff struggling with manual appointment reminders, patient communication, and insurance verification across their large adult and pediatric patient base.', 'high revenue-to-employee ratio ($2.9M per employee), mixed adult/pediatric patient base, extended hours 7am-6pm indicating high volume, comprehensive services requiring complex scheduling, 25-year established practice with large recall database', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With 9 staff handling $25.9M revenue across adult and pediatric patients, your front desk is likely drowning in VOB calls during those 7am starts.', 'front desk VOB burden with early morning patient volume', 'those 7am vob calls', 'Rose,\n\nNoticed Elmbrook handles $25M+ with 9 staff members. That\'s impressive volume, but I imagine your front desk starts those early mornings with insurance verification calls.\n\nMost family practices this size tell me their teams spend the first 2 hours of every day manually checking eligibility before patients arrive. Adult and pediatric benefits work differently, so it\'s double the verification work.\n\nThe math never quite adds up when you\'re running this much revenue per person.', 'w