(495, 65, '2026-03-30 14:09:50', 'Exton Dental Health', 'https://extondental.com', 'Haiyi Xian', 'Dental Assistant, Registered Dental Assistant', 'haiyi.xian@extondental.com', '', 'YES', 42, 'Strong dental practice fit with solid revenue ($10.1M) and employee count (10), but contact is clinical staff influencer rather than decision-maker. Located in PA (EST state) with clear dental services including cosmetic and general dentistry.', 'Exton Dental Health Group is a high-end cosmetic and restorative dental practice in Exton, PA with two specialists (Dr. Scharf - cosmetic, Dr. Kopecki - prosthodontist) serving affluent Main Line patients with complex treatment plans and premium services.', 'small', 'high', 'High-value cosmetic and restorative treatment plans require extensive insurance pre-verification and patient financial coordination that\'s overwhelming their 10-person team with manual processes', '10.1M revenue with 10 employees, cosmetic/prosthodontic specialty requiring complex treatment planning, affluent patient base with premium insurance verification needs, multi-provider practice with specialists', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Your prosthodontist and cosmetic specialist setup generates complex insurance coverage scenarios that likely require 2-3 VOB calls per high-value case.', 'dual-specialty insurance pre-verification complexity and time burden', 'high value cases, endless calls', 'Most specialty practices with prosthodontics and cosmetic work end up with front office teams making 2-3 insurance verification calls per case. The crown and bridge work, veneers, and full mouth reconstructions require different coverage checks than routine cleanings. What should be a 5-minute process turns into hours of hold time with insurance companies, especially when benefits max out or coverage gets denied halfway through treatment. Are you seeing this pattern with your higher-value treatment plans?', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We built patient communication software specifically for practices handling complex treatment cases like yours at Exton Dental Health. Instead of your team making multiple VOB calls for prosthodontic and cosmetic cases, insurance eligibility gets confirmed in 12 seconds before every appointment. One practice similar to yours told us their front desk teams reclaimed 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. Does this sound like something worth exploring?', 'Every hour your team spends on hold with insurance companies is an hour not spent on patient experience or case coordination. At 15+ hours per week, that\'s roughly $12,000 in staff time annually just for verification calls. High-value cases get delayed when coverage questions arise mid-treatment. The system works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week. Would it make sense to see how this looks for your prosthodontic cases specifically?', 'Noticed Exton Dental handles a lot of cosmetic and restorative work. How much time does your team spend on insurance verification calls for the higher-value cases?', 'what manual vob costs', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://extondental.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Exton Dental Health', '10.1M', '10', '', '', 'Pennsylvania', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://extondental.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 To