(496, 65, '2026-03-30 14:10:54', 'Fairfax Dental Group', 'https://fairfaxdentalgroup.com', 'Brenda Young', 'Dentist', 'youngdds@fairfaxdentalgroup.com', '', 'YES', 69, 'Strong firmographic fit as US-based dental practice with solid revenue ($20M) and excellent dental specialties match (general, cosmetic, restorative, implants), but limited by dentist contact who is likely an influencer rather than decision-maker. Established practice since 1992 with comprehensive services indicates operational maturity.', 'Fairfax Dental Group is a well-established 30+ year general and cosmetic dental practice with 6 employees serving the Fairfax, VA market. The practice offers high-end services including Invisalign, implants, and cosmetic dentistry with strong patient loyalty but likely faces scheduling and insurance coordination challenges typical of smaller multi-service practices.', 'small', 'medium', 'High-end cosmetic practice with complex treatment planning and scheduling coordination across multiple specialties is likely struggling with manual insurance verification for expensive procedures and missed revenue from poor recall automation', '6 employees handling $20M revenue, high-end services (Invisalign, implants, veneers), multi-specialty offerings, 30+ year established practice with likely legacy systems, cosmetic procedures requiring pre-verification', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'With your high-end cosmetic cases like veneers and Invisalign, manual insurance pre-verification is probably eating up front desk time on complex coverage questions.', 'front desk burden from manual VOB on expensive cosmetic procedures', 'veneer pre-auths taking forever', 'Most cosmetic practices see their front desk teams spending 2-3 hours daily just on insurance pre-verification calls for veneers, Invisalign, and crown cases. The carriers put these high-dollar procedures through extra scrutiny, so your team ends up playing phone tag with benefits departments while patients wait weeks to start