(500, 65, '2026-03-30 14:14:48', 'Fioritto Dental Assoc', 'https://fiorittodental.com', 'Andrew Ricci', 'General Dentist', 'a.ricci@fiorittodental.com', '', 'YES', 81, 'Strong fit - 17-employee multi-location dental group in Ohio with $18.9M revenue, full-service practice since 1970. Contact is clinical staff (influencer role) but practice shows ideal size and operational complexity.', 'Fioritto Dental Associates is a 54-year-old family dental practice operating two locations (Mentor and Concord, Ohio) with 17 employees and comprehensive general/specialty services including pediatric dentistry, orthodontics, and advanced procedures.', 'mid-size', 'high', 'With 17 employees and $18.9M revenue across two locations, front desk staff are likely overwhelmed managing high-volume recall outreach, appointment confirmations, and insurance verification manually for comprehensive services including pediatric and specialty care', '17 employees handling $18.9M revenue, two locations, comprehensive services including pediatric dentistry and orthodontics, advanced procedures requiring pre-verification, specialty mix creating complex scheduling needs', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Managing recall coordination for pediatric through geriatric patients across Mentor and Concord with 17 staff creates scheduling bottlenecks during seasonal rushes.', 'multi-location age-diverse patient base scheduling complexity', '17 staff, endless phone tags', 'Andrew, most multi-location practices with comprehensive services see their front desk teams buried in recall calls during seasonal rushes. When you\'re managing pediatric through geriatric patients across locations, staff end up playing phone tag for hours instead of focusing on the patients walking through your doors. The coordination load gets especially heavy when families need different appointment types scheduled across age groups.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr handles the recall coordination that\'s eating up your team\'s time across Mentor and Concord. Instead of manual outreach, patients get reached through their preferred channel automatically. Front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. Your staff can focus on patient experience rather than chasing down overdue hygiene appointments for 17 different provider schedules.', 'Every week your team spends 20+ hours on manual recall means 20+ hours not spent on treatment coordination and patient care. That\'s roughly $800 in labor costs just for basic outreach that could run itself. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week. Would it make sense to see how other practices with your patient volume handle recall without the phone marathon?', 'Andrew, noticed Fioritto has comprehensive services across two locations. Most practices your size see front desk teams spending hours daily on recall coordination instead of patient experience. How are you handling the seasonal appointment rushes with pediatric through geriatric scheduling?', 'what staying manual costs', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://fiorittodental.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Fioritto Family Dental', '18.9M', '17', '', '', 'Ohio', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://fiorittodental.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Clau