(501, 65, '2026-03-30 14:15:53', 'Firouzian Dentistry', 'https://columbuscosmeticdental.com', 'Michael Firouzian', 'Dentist', 'drmike@eid-dentistry.com', '', 'YES', 72, 'Strong dental practice fit with cosmetic focus, good revenue and Ohio location, but contact is clinical staff rather than owner/decision-maker which limits immediate buying authority.', 'Firouzian Dentistry is a high-end cosmetic and holistic dental practice in Columbus, Ohio with 5 employees generating $13.3M revenue, indicating premium pricing and complex treatment coordination needs.', 'small', 'high', 'High-revenue complex cosmetic cases requiring extensive treatment plan coordination and patient communication across multiple appointment sequences with only 5 staff members', '$13.3M revenue with only 5 employees, complex multi-appointment cosmetic procedures (veneers, implants, FOY dentures), premium pricing requiring extensive consultation coordination, sedation dentistry scheduling complexity, TMJ treatment follow-ups', 'high', 'Champion / Economic Buyer', 'high', 'With $13.3M revenue from just 5 staff, your complex veneers and implant cases likely create communication bottlenecks during multi-visit treatment sequences.', 'high-revenue cosmetic practice staff bottleneck during complex treatment coordination', 'multi-visit cases gone quiet', 'Most high-end cosmetic practices see this pattern. Patient approves a $40K full mouth reconstruction or implant case, completes visit one, then radio silence for weeks. The front desk gets busy with daily operations, complex treatment plans sit in charts without follow-up, and patients drift into analysis paralysis. With 5 staff managing $13M in revenue, staying on top of every multi-visit sequence manually becomes nearly impossible.', 'following up on treatment gaps', 'That\'s exactly why I\'m writing about Calyxr. It handles the treatment plan follow-up that gets lost between appointments for complex cases. When a veneer patient or implant case goes quie