(505, 65, '2026-03-30 14:20:28', 'Foundation Endodontics', 'https://foundationendo.com', 'Amber Flannigan', 'Dental Assistant', 'amber@foundationendo.com', '', 'YES', 68, 'Strong dental specialty fit (endodontics) in high-value Texas market with 10 employees, but contact is clinical staff influencer rather than decision-maker. Founded 2018 suggests growth stage with automation needs.', 'Foundation Endodontics is a specialized endodontic practice founded in 2018 in Richmond, TX, serving the Greater Houston area with 10 employees. They focus exclusively on root canal treatments, retreatments, and surgical endodontics with state-of-the-art technology and luxury patient amenities.', 'small', 'high', 'Specialist practice with complex referral coordination and high-value procedures needs automated insurance pre-verification and recall management for multi-visit endodontic treatments', 'endodontic specialty practice, high-value procedures requiring pre-auth, multi-visit treatment protocols, referral-based patient flow, 10-employee practice size suggests manual processes', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With 10-person endodontic practice handling multi-visit root canal cases, referral coordination breakdowns likely cost you completed treatments.', 'specialist referral coordination revenue leakage from incomplete multi-visit endodontic sequences', 'referral coordination breakdowns', 'Many endodontic practices see the same pattern with multi-visit cases. A referring dentist sends a patient for root canal treatment, but somewhere between the referral and completion, things fall through the cracks. Maybe insurance wasn\'t pre-verified properly, or the patient didn\'t schedule their follow-up crown prep back with the referring office. The referring dentist assumes treatment is complete, the patient thinks they\'re done after the endo work, and suddenly a $1,500 case turns into an incomplete treatment and an unhappy referral relationship.', 'why i\'m following up', 'I\'m reachi