(506, 65, '2026-03-30 14:21:30', 'Frazer Dental Care', 'https://frazerdentalcare.com', 'Preetha Kesari', 'Dentist', 'pkesari@frazerdentalcare.com', '', 'YES', 72, 'Strong firmographic fit with 7-person PA dental practice at $14.3M revenue, but contact is clinical staff (Dentist) rather than owner/operations decision-maker. High revenue suggests multi-provider group with automation needs.', 'Frazer Dental Care is a family-oriented general dentistry practice in the Chester County area serving Frazer and Malvern communities. With 7 employees and extended hours (7am-7pm), they focus on accessible dental care through in-house financing and dental plans for uninsured patients.', 'small', 'medium', 'Small 7-person team managing high patient volume with extended hours (7am-7pm) likely struggles with phone coverage, appointment scheduling, and insurance verification workload', '7 employees with $14.3M revenue indicates high revenue per employee, extended 12-hour daily operations, general dentistry with in-house financing suggests complex billing needs, serving multiple communities increases patient communication volume', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 7 staff covering 12-hour days, your front desk is probably drowning in insurance verification calls between patient appointments.', 'small team extended hours operational strain on front desk insurance workload', 'insurance verification bottleneck', 'Running 12-hour days with a lean team creates an interesting challenge. Many dental practices with your patient volume find their front desk caught in endless insurance verification calls between appointments. Seven staff covering that schedule means someone is always on hold with Aetna or Delta while patients are waiting. The math gets brutal when you calculate how many chair-side hours get lost to eligibility checks that should take seconds, not minutes.', 'why i mentioned verification', 'Following up because Frazer Dental Care\'s setup reminded me why we built Calyxr in the f