(508, 65, '2026-03-30 14:23:31', 'Frisco Pediatric Dentistry', 'https://friscopediatricdentistry.com', 'Diane Lide', 'Pediatric Dentist', 'diane@drlide.com', '', 'YES', 54, 'Strong dental industry match in EST state with 4 employees, but contact is clinical staff rather than owner/decision-maker. Pediatric dental specialty indicates good patient volume potential.', 'Frisco Pediatric Dentistry is a small solo practice run by board-certified pediatric dentist Dr. Diane Lide with 4 employees serving infants through teens in Frisco, TX. Practice focuses on creating positive dental experiences for children with parent-friendly policies and entertainment amenities.', 'small', 'medium', 'Small pediatric team handling high-volume appointment scheduling, frequent no-shows from kids, and manual parent communication through phone calls only', '4-person team, pediatric specialty with parent coordination needs, no digital communication platform mentioned, open-door parent policy requiring coordination, focus on positive experiences suggests no-show management critical', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'With 4-person team managing high-volume pediatric scheduling, parents likely aren\'t getting timely appointment confirmations, driving up your no-show rate.', 'small pediatric team overwhelmed by manual parent communication leading to no-show revenue loss', 'pediatric no show patterns', 'Most pediatric practices see no-show rates climb when parents only get phone call reminders.\n\nKids get sick, schedules change last minute, and when there\'s no easy way for parents to confirm or reschedule, appointments just get missed.\n\nWith a 4-person team handling high-volume scheduling, there\'s rarely time to call every parent 48 hours out, then again the day before.\n\nSo slots go unfilled and the schedule stays unpredictable.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Following up because we built Calyxr specifically to solve the parent communication gap in pediatric practices.\n\nInstead of your team making confirmation calls, parents get automated texts they can respond to instantly. They can confirm, reschedule, or cancel with one tap.\n\nOne pediatric practice in Dallas saw no-shows dropped from 28% to under 12% in 90 days after switching from phone-only reminders.\n\nWorth exploring for Frisco Pediatric Dentistry?', 'If 20% of your pediatric appointments no-show, that\'s roughly $40,000+ in lost production annually for a practice your size.\n\nMeanwhile, your 4-person team spends hours each week on confirmation calls that half the parents don\'t answer anyway.\n\nCalyxr works with your existing scheduling system, no IT setup required, and you\'re live in under a week.\n\nShould I send over what the setup looks like for pediatric practices?', 'Noticed Frisco Pediatric has a small team handling high-volume scheduling. Most pediatric practices struggle with no-shows when parents only get phone reminders. Are you seeing missed appointments climb when your team can\'t reach every parent for confirmations?', 'cost of missed slots', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://friscopediatricdentistry.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Frisco Pediatric Dentistry', '', '4', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://friscopediatricdentistry.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/frisco-pediatric-dentistry', '+1 972-377-8444', 'diane@drlide.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/diane-lide-b05a009', 'friscopediatricdentistry.com', 'medical practice', 'medical practices, hospital & health care', 'This is where your child learns to love coming to the dentist! Dr. Diane Lide always wants to provide great experiences for your kids because she wants to raise \'happy dental adults.\' Dr. Lide is a board certified Pediatric Dentist who loves engaging with kids, and kids love engaging with her! Parents are always welcome to stay with their children throughout their visit since we have a unique open-door policy. Kids love the atmosphere at our dental office from the friendly staff to the video gam', 'Frisco', '', '', 'Pediatric Dentist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(509, 65, '2026-03-30 14:23:39', 'Frisco Smile Solutions', 'https://friscodds.com', 'Amber Sallee', 'Dental Assistant', 'asallee@friscodds.com', '', 'Skipped', 30, 'ICP score 30 is below the threshold of 35. Perfect dental industry match in high-value Texas market, but contact is a dental assistant (influencer, not decision-maker) which severely limits sales potential.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(510, 65, '2026-03-30 14:24:45', 'Full Implant Choice', 'https://fullimplantchoice.com', 'Wanda Conway', 'Registered Dental Hygienist', 'wconway@fullimplantchoice.com', '', 'YES', 66, 'Strong dental implant specialty fit with 6-person team in Virginia, but primary contact is clinical staff (hygienist) rather than decision-maker. High-value implant practice likely has significant patient follow-up needs.', 'Full Implant Choice is a specialized implant-only practice led by Dr. Adam Hogan in Virginia Beach, focusing exclusively on full-mouth reconstruction with 10,000+ implant cases completed. With 6 employees and an on-site dental lab, they offer premium single-day implant procedures like All-on-4 and Teeth-in-a-Day.', 'small', 'high', 'High-value implant cases ($20K-40K per patient) require extensive insurance pre-verification and treatment plan coordination across multiple appointments with premium patient communication expectations', 'implant specialty, premium procedures, multi-visit treatment plans, small team of 6 employees, high-value cases requiring pre-authorization, on-site lab coordination', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With $30K+ full-arch cases, your front desk probably spends hours on multi-carrier VOBs since implant coverage varies wildly between medical and dental plans.', 'high-value implant case insurance verification burden', 'full arch vob nightmare', 'Hi Wanda,\n\nMost implant practices with full-arch cases are drowning in insurance pre-verification work. When you\'re dealing with $30K treatments, the front desk ends up calling multiple carriers per patient because implant coverage splits between medical and dental plans.\n\nThe verification process that should take 10 minutes stretches into hours, and you\'re still not sure if the patient\'s portion is accurate until after treatment planning appointments.\n\nSeeing this pattern everywhere in implant-focused practices lately.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Hi Wanda,\n\nFollowing up because Calyxr handles the exact VOB complexity you\'re probably dealing with at Full Implant Choice.\n\nInstead of your team calling multiple carriers for each full-arch case, Calyxr confirms insurance eligibility in 12 seconds before every appointment, including the medical/dental plan coordination that implant cases require.\n\nOne practice doing similar work saw their front desk reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone.\n\nDoes the multi-carrier verification process sound familiar for your higher-value cases?', 'Hi Wanda,\n\nWhen your front desk spends 2-3 hours per full-arch case on insurance verification, that\'s roughly $150 in labor costs before the patient even sits down. Multiply that across your monthly implant volume and the numbers add up quickly.\n\nPlus there\'s the risk of incorrect benefits information derailing a $30K treatment plan.\n\nWorth exploring how this could work with your existing setup, no IT changes required on your end.\n\nWhat does your current VOB process look like for the complex implant cases?', 'Hi Wanda, noticed Full Implant Choice focuses on full-arch cases. Most implant practices I talk to are spending hours on insurance pre-verification since coverage splits between medical and dental plans. How are you handling the VOB complexity with your higher-value treatments?', 'cost of manual vob', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://fullimplantchoice.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Full Implant Choice', '', '6', '', '', 'Virginia', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://fullimplantchoice.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/full-implant-choice', '+1 757-629-4259', 'wconway@fullimplantchoice.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/wanda-conway-62b1b7158', 'fullimplantchoice.com', 'medical practice', 'all on 4, veneers, implants, smiles, self esteem, cosmetic dentistry, replacement of missing teeth, dental implants, confidence, teeth in a day, crowns, dentures', 'At Full Implant Choice, we focus exclusively on full-mouth dental implant solutions, replacing missing or failing teeth with efficient, life-changing care. Led by Dr. Adam Hogan, we offer advanced procedures like Teeth-in-a-Day, All-on-4®, and AOX full-arch restorations.\n\nAll diagnostics, surgery, and restorations are completed under one roof, including our on-site dental lab. This in-house approach means fewer visits, faster turnaround times, and greater precision throughout the entire process.', 'Virginia Beach', '2007', '', 'Registered Dental Hygienist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(511, 65, '2026-03-30 14:25:51', 'Fun Kids Dentistry', 'https://funkidsdentistry.com', 'Brielle Kiffa', 'Dental Assistant', 'brielle.kiffa@funkidsdentistry.com', '', 'YES', 52, 'Small pediatric dental practice in Texas with strong industry match and cutting-edge technology focus, but limited by clinical staff contact and very small team size requiring nurture approach.', 'Fun Kids Dentistry is a small pediatric dental practice in Prosper, TX with only 2 employees, offering full-service pediatric care including sedation dentistry and special needs patients. The practice accepts most major insurances and serves children from infancy through adolescence.', 'small', 'medium', 'With only 2 employees handling pediatric patients who require extensive parent communication and frequent recall scheduling, this practice likely struggles with manual appointment reminders and missed calls leading to no-shows', '2-person team, pediatric specialty requiring parent communication, sedation dentistry needing pre/post-procedure follow-up, special needs patients requiring additional coordination, accepts most major insurances creating verification burden', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With sedation cases and special needs pediatric patients, your 2-person team likely spends significant time on pre-appointment parent calls that could be automated.', 'sedation dentistry pre-appointment communication burden on minimal staff', 'sedation appointments and parent calls', 'Many pediatric practices with sedation cases find their small teams spending hours each day on pre-appointment parent calls. Between explaining procedures, confirming sedation protocols, and handling anxious parent questions, the manual reminder process can eat up half the day. When you\'re already juggling chairside duties with front desk coverage, those confirmation calls become overwhelming fast. The missed appointments from parents who didn\'t get proper reminders just make the revenue gaps worse.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We handle all the pre-appointment parent communication for pediatric practices, including sedation protocol confirmations and appointment reminders. Your team stays chairside while parents get the detailed information they need automatically. One practice similar to Fun Kids Dentistry saw no-shows dropped from 28% to under 12% in 90 days. Would something like this help with your current parent communication load?', 'Every missed sedation appointment costs about $400 in lost chairtime, and manual parent calls take roughly 2 hours daily for a 2-person team. That\'s 10 hours weekly that could go toward patient care instead of phone tag with anxious parents. We work with your existing practice management system and go live in under a week with no IT setup required. Would you be curious to see how this looks for a practice your size?', 'Noticed Fun Kids Dentistry handles sedation cases with just 2 team members. That probably means lots of pre-appointment parent calls eating into your chairside time. Are you finding the manual reminder process manageable, or is it becoming a daily challenge?', 'cost of manual reminders', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://funkidsdentistry.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Fun Kids Dentistry', '', '2', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://funkidsdentistry.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/fun-kids-dentistry', '+1 469-519-9951', 'brielle.kiffa@funkidsdentistry.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/brielle-kiffa-a8627825a', 'funkidsdentistry.com', 'medical practice', 'medical practices, hospital & health care', 'All Kids Dentistry is a full-service pediatric dental office, offering a wide range of preventive and restorative procedures. Whether your child needs a simple exam and cleaning, a filling, crown, or extraction, or even in-hospital sedation, we are here to help. We are committed to utilizing cutting-technology and proven techniques to ensure that your child receives the best possible treatment outcomes.', 'Prosper', '', '', 'Dental Assistant', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(512, 65, '2026-03-30 14:26:50', 'Fusion Orthodontics and Children\'s Dentistry', 'https://fusiondentalclinic.com', 'Fusion Orthodontics', 'Pediatric Dentist', 'garland@fusionorthodontics.com', '', 'YES', 74, 'Strong pediatric dentistry and orthodontics practice in Texas with 6 employees and $24.2M revenue, but contact is clinical staff rather than owner/decision-maker. Family-run practice suggests decision-maker accessibility.', 'Fusion Orthodontics and Children\'s Dentistry is a Harvard-trained, family-run dual-specialty practice serving North Dallas with 6 employees and $24.2M revenue. They offer both pediatric dentistry and orthodontics including Invisalign and lingual braces.', 'small', 'high', 'High-volume dual-specialty practice with only 6 employees likely drowning in manual appointment coordination, recall management for both pediatric and ortho patients, and insurance verification across multiple treatment types', 'dual-specialty practice, pediatric + orthodontics, 6 employees managing $24.2M revenue, North Dallas multi-location coverage, Invisalign treatment coordination, family-run practice, premium care positioning', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'Six-person team handling $24M dual-specialty revenue likely burns hours daily coordinating pediatric recall cycles with active ortho adjustment schedules.', 'dual-specialty appointment coordination chaos with minimal staffing', 'six people, two specialties', 'Most dual-specialty practices with pediatric and ortho under one roof hit the same wall around your size. Six team members trying to juggle recall schedules for cleaning patients while coordinating adjustment appointments creates this constant coordination dance. The pediatric side needs different reminder timing than ortho, insurance pre-auths vary by treatment type, and someone is always playing phone tag between the specialties. Have you noticed your team spending more time coordinating schedules than they probably should?', 'why i\'m following up', 'I\'m reaching out because Calyxr handles exactly what I described yesterday, the dual-specialty coordination challenge. We set up separate communication flows for pediatric recall versus ortho adjustments, handle insurance verification automatically across both treatment types, and eliminate the manual back-and-forth between specialties. One practice similar to yours saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone once both specialties were running on the same system. Does this sound like something worth looking into for Fusion?', 'Running two specialties with manual coordination is probably costing your practice more than you realize. If your six-person team is spending even 2 hours daily on appointment coordination and recall management, that\'s 500+ hours annually at clinical wages. Plus every missed pediatric recall or delayed ortho adjustment compounds into real revenue leakage. The system works with your existing practice management software and goes live in under a week. Would it make sense to see exactly how this would work for both your pediatric and ortho patient flows?', 'Running pediatric and ortho with six people has to create some interesting coordination challenges between the different appointment types and recall schedules. How are you currently handling the dual-specialty patient communication flow?', 'what this is costing', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://fusiondentalclinic.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Fusion Orthodontics and Children\'s Dentistry', '24.2M', '6', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://fusiondentalclinic.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/fusion-orthodontics-and-children\'s-dentistry', '+1 972-666-4949', 'garland@fusionorthodontics.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/fusion-orthodontics-8b3a16ab', 'fusiondentalclinic.com', 'medical practice', 'adult braces, pediatric dentistry, orthodontics, invisible braces, medical practices, hospital & health care, dentists, general dentistry, health & medical, orthodontists, pediatric dentists', 'Welcome to Fusion Orthodontics and Children\'s Dentistry, one of the top dental and orthodontic practices of north Dallas, Plano and Richardson neighborhoods. We are a family-run practice providing specialized premium care to children and families of North Dallas, Far north Dallas, Richardson and Plano using state of the art technology backed by more than a decade of dental experience. Dr. Rahimi, our Harvard-trained Board Certified Orthodontist provides Mechanodontics, Invisalign, Lingual (Incog', 'Dallas', '2014', '', 'Pediatric Dentist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(513, 65, '2026-03-30 14:27:51', 'Gallery57Dental', 'https://gallery57dental.com', 'Roseanna Torres', 'Registered Dental Hygienist', 'roseannardh@gallery57dental.com', '', 'YES', 68, 'Strong dental practice fit with advanced technology (CAD/CAM leader, on-site ceramics lab) and specialty services, but contact is clinical staff influencer rather than decision-maker, limiting immediate sales potential.', 'Gallery57Dental is a high-end 11-person cosmetic and restorative dental practice in NYC, operating an innovative same-day CAD/CAM ceramic lab since 2006. They pioneered single-visit crown technology with advanced digital scanning and in-house milling capabilities.', 'small', 'high', 'High-end cosmetic practice with complex treatment plans and premium clientele likely struggles with insurance verification delays and manual coordination between multiple specialists for implant/cosmetic cases', '11-person team, cosmetic dentistry, implant dentistry, same-day CAD/CAM, premium NYC location, multi-specialty services, sleep apnea treatment, on-site lab coordination', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With same-day CAD/CAM ceramics and complex implant cases, your front desk likely spends hours on insurance pre-verification calls for premium treatments.', 'complex premium treatment insurance verification burden', 'premium treatment pre auths', 'Most high-end cosmetic practices see the same pattern with complex cases. When patients need full mouth reconstruction or implant work, the insurance pre-verification process becomes a nightmare. Front desk teams spend entire mornings on hold with carriers, trying to get coverage details for premium treatments that might not even be covered. Meanwhile, patients are waiting weeks to know if they can move forward, and treatment coordinators are juggling multiple specialists for single cases.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We built something specifically for practices like Gallery57Dental that handle complex cosmetic and implant cases. Instead of your team spending hours on verification calls, our system confirms insurance eligibility in 12 seconds before every appointment, including detailed breakdowns for premium treatments and specialist referrals. One practice similar to yours told us their treatment coordinators went from 4 hours daily on insurance calls to under 30 minutes.', 'Every day your team spends on manual insurance verification is costing the practice. If treatment coordinators are spending 20+ hours weekly on pre-auth calls, that\'s nearly $2,400 monthly in staff time alone. Plus patients delay starting treatment when they can\'t get quick coverage answers. Calyxr works with your existing PMS, no long-term contracts, and most practices see the time savings within the first week. Would it help to see how this looks for a practice handling your volume of complex cases?', 'Hey Roseanna, noticed Gallery57Dental handles complex implant and cosmetic cases. Your treatment coordinators probably spend hours daily on insurance pre-verification calls for premium treatments. How much time does your team typically spend getting coverage details for full mouth cases?', 'cost of verification delays', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://gallery57dental.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Gallery57Dental', '', '11', '', '', 'New York', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://gallery57dental.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/gallery57dental', '+1 212-246-8700', 'roseannardh@gallery57dental.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/roseanna-torres-b84310194', 'gallery57dental.com', 'hospital & health care', 'implant dentistry, somnomed sleep appliance, cadcam dentistry, cosmetic dentistry, same day ceramics, hospitals & health care, d2c, dental services, digital smile design, laser dentistry, on-site dental lab, sleep apnea treatment', 'Gallery57Dental is a group dental practice offering general and specialty dental services. Gallery57Dental was the first integrated CAD/CAM office in the world and remains a leader in single visit ceramic dentistry. Thanks to our in-office ceramics lab, we provide highly aesthetic, porcelain crowns and veneers in a single visit. These restorations require less drilling and eliminate metal in the mouth as well as additional visits and injections. Gallery57Dental is also a leader in the all-cerami', 'New York', '2006', '', 'Registered Dental Hygienist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(514, 65, '2026-03-30 14:28:55', 'Garden Oaks Family & Cosmetic Dentistry', 'https://gardenoaksfamilydental.com', 'Kaitlyn Middlebrooks', 'Registered Dental Assistant', 'middlebrooksk@gardenoaksfamilydental.com', '', 'YES', 67, 'Strong industry match with dental practice keywords and Texas location, but limited by small team size (4 employees) and contact being clinical staff rather than decision-maker. Revenue appears inflated for practice size.', 'Garden Oaks Family & Cosmetic Dentistry is a privately-owned, multi-specialty dental practice in Denton, TX with 4 employees serving multi-generational families with comprehensive services including laser dentistry, clear aligners, and implants.', 'small', 'high', '4-person team managing comprehensive multi-specialty services including implants and cosmetic procedures likely struggling with manual patient communication, appointment reminders, and treatment plan follow-up across diverse service lines', '4 employees total, multi-specialty practice, comprehensive services including laser dentistry and implants, multi-generational patient base requiring different communication preferences, cosmetic and restorative treatment plans needing follow-up', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'Four-person team handling implants, cosmetic cases, and family dentistry likely spending significant chair time on treatment plan follow-up calls instead of clinical production.', 'treatment plan follow-up burden reducing clinical productivity', 'treatment plans sitting idle', 'Many dental practices find themselves with thousands of dollars worth of approved treatment plans sitting in patient charts. Patients say yes to the cosmetic work or implant, then life gets busy and they never reschedule. With a small team juggling family dentistry, cosmetics, and implants, there\'s rarely time to circle back and check on these cases. The treatment sits there while the practice moves on to the next patient.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is because of Calyxr, a system that automatically follows up on unscheduled treatment plans without your team lifting a finger. Instead of hoping patients will call back about their cosmetic work or implant treatment, it reaches out at the right intervals to get them back on the schedule. One practice saw 70% reduction in manual front office tasks without adding headcount. Worth exploring for a busy multi-specialty practice like Garden Oaks?', 'Each month that approved treatment sits unscheduled, the practice typically loses $15,000 to $30,000 in revenue that patients already said yes to. Meanwhile, your clinical team spends valuable chair time making follow-up calls instead of focusing on production. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week. Would it make sense to see how many unscheduled treatment plans are currently sitting in your system?', 'Hi Kaitlyn, noticed Garden Oaks handles everything from family care to implants with just four people. Bet you have treatment plans sitting in charts that patients never rescheduled. How do you currently follow up on approved but unscheduled cases?', 'sitting on approved treatment', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://gardenoaksfamilydental.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Garden Oaks Family & Cosmetic Dentistry', '36.6M', '4', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://gardenoaksfamilydental.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/garden-oaks-family-&-cosmetic-dentistry', '+1 940-566-4888', 'middlebrooksk@gardenoaksfamilydental.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/kaitlyn-middlebrooks1998', 'gardenoaksfamilydental.com', 'health, wellness & fitness', 'dental, medical, health care, health, wellness & fitness, hospital & health care', 'Garden Oaks Family & Cosmetic Dentistry is a company based out of DENTON, TX, United States.', 'Denton', '', '', 'Registered Dental Assistant', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(515, 65, '2026-03-30 14:29:52', 'Garden Valley Family & Cosmetic Dentistry', 'https://gardenvalleydentistry.com', 'Rhea Antolin', 'General Dentist', 'drantolin@gardenvalleydentistry.com', '', 'YES', 72, 'Strong dental practice fit with comprehensive service offering in Texas sweet spot market. General Dentist contact is influencer-level but may be owner at 1-employee practice, suggesting good conversion potential.', 'Garden Valley Family & Cosmetic Dentistry is a small solo practice in Roanoke, TX run by Dr. Antolin with 3-4 staff members offering comprehensive family and cosmetic dentistry services. The practice appears to be a newer, smaller operation with the dentist\'s husband as business manager, indicating a family-run structure with limited administrative resources.', 'small', 'medium', 'Small family-run practice with husband as business manager and only 1 employee on record needs to maximize productivity without adding overhead staff for patient communication and administrative tasks', 'solo practice, family-run business structure, husband as business manager, 1 employee count, comprehensive service mix including cosmetic and surgical procedures, newer practice with limited administrative resources', 'high', 'Champion', 'high', 'With just one employee on record and your husband managing the business side, you\'re likely handling patient calls and appointment confirmations manually instead of seeing patients.', 'solo practice productivity loss from administrative burden', 'time in chair vs phone', 'Many small dental practices see the same pattern. With minimal front desk support, the dentist ends up handling confirmation calls, appointment reminders, and patient follow-ups between procedures. What should be 8 hours of clinical time becomes 6 hours of dentistry plus 2 hours of phone work. The math doesn\'t work when your revenue comes from being in the chair, not on the phone with insurance companies or chasing no-shows.', 'why I\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We handle all the patient communication your practice needs without adding staff overhead. Automated appointment confirmations, insurance verification, recall reminders, and missed call follow-up. One of our family practices saw their front desk time drop by 15+ hours a week while maintaining the same patient experience. Would this type of setup make sense for Garden Valley Family & Cosmetic Dentistry?', 'Quick math on staying manual: if you\'re spending 10 hours weekly on calls and admin tasks instead of clinical work, that\'s roughly $800-1200 in lost production per week. Over a year, those manual processes cost most practices $40,000+ in opportunity cost. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system and goes live in under a week. Curious if you\'ve calculated what those phone hours are costing your practice?', 'Noticed Garden Valley Family & Cosmetic Dentistry has a lean team. Most small practices end up with the dentist handling patient calls between procedures instead of focusing on clinical work. Have you found a way to handle appointment confirmations without pulling you away from the chair?', 'cost of manual calls', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://gardenvalleydentistry.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Garden Valley Family & Cosmetic Dentistry', '', '1', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://gardenvalleydentistry.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/garden-valley-family-cosmetic-dentistry', '+1 682-237-2353', 'drantolin@gardenvalleydentistry.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/rhea-theresa-antolin-75890523a', 'gardenvalleydentistry.com', 'medical practice', 'dental implants, invisalign, pediatric dentistry, extractions oral surgery, root canal therapy, laser dentistry, exams cleanings, toothcolored fillings & crowns, zoom teeth whitening, veneers, gum therapy, bridges dentures', 'A dental office that cares about it\'s patients and their oral health.  Research shows that more than 90 percent of all systemic diseases have oral manifestations, including swollen gums, mouth ulcers, dry mouth, and excessive gum problems.  We strive to make each patient as comfortable as possible and our priority is your oral health.\n\nIt is Our Mission to provide the people of this community with the most advanced dental care possible. We pride ourselves on treating each dental patient with res', 'Roanoke', '', '', 'General Dentist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(516, 65, '2026-03-30 14:31:21', 'Gemma Tanglao Dalton, DDS', 'https://gemmadds.com', 'Gemma Dalton', 'Dentist', 'gemma@drdaltondds.com', '', 'YES', 67, 'Strong dental practice match with clinical owner persona in Texas, but very small team size (3 employees) and unusually high revenue figure suggests data quality issues. Bedford location and modern dentistry focus indicate growth potential.', 'Dr. Gemma Tanglao Dalton operates a small general dentistry practice in Bedford, Texas with only 3 employees, creating significant front desk operational strain despite generating high revenue per employee.', 'small', 'medium', '3-person team generating $26.5M revenue creates extreme front desk overload with patient communication, scheduling, and insurance verification handled manually', '3 employees, $26.5M revenue ($8.8M per employee), general dentistry high patient volume, small team relative to revenue scale, Bedford Texas location', 'high', 'Champion / Economic Buyer', 'high', 'With 3 employees generating $26.5M, your Bedford practice likely has one person juggling phones, scheduling, and insurance verification simultaneously.', 'extreme operational efficiency bottleneck at ultra-high-revenue micro practice', '3 people, 26m revenue', 'Most dental practices generating $26M+ have 15-20 team members handling patient communication, scheduling, and insurance verification. When a 3-person team tries to manage that same volume, someone is always drowning in phone calls and manual tasks. The math just doesn\'t work. One person can\'t juggle live calls, appointment confirmations, and insurance eligibility checks without something falling through the cracks.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We handle patient communication, appointment confirmations, and insurance verification so your small team can focus on what matters most, patient care and treatment delivery. One of our Bedford-area practices saw their front desk team reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. Does your current setup give your team breathing room, or are they constantly putting out fires?', 'Every week your 3-person team spends on manual patient communication and insurance verification is costing you roughly $2,400 in lost productivity, plus whatever revenue walks out the door from missed calls and scheduling gaps. At $26M revenue, that adds up fast. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week. Would it make sense to see how this looks for your Bedford practice specifically?', 'Noticed your Bedford practice generates $26M with just 3 employees. That\'s impressive, but someone on your team is probably drowning in patient calls and insurance verification. How does your front desk keep up with that volume?', 'cost of doing nothing', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://gemmadds.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Gemma Tanglao Dalton, DDS', '26.5M', '3', '', '', 'Texas', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://gemmadds.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/gemma-tanglao-dalton-dds', '', 'gemma@drdaltondds.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/gemma-dalton-30b4883b', 'gemmadds.com', 'medical practice', 'medical practices, hospital & health care', 'Get a healthy gorgeous smile at Gemma Tanglao Dalton, DDS from leading Bedford dentist Dr. Gemma Dalton. Modern dentistry that is affordable in a caring, fun environment', 'Bedford', '', '', 'Dentist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(517, 65, '2026-03-30 14:32:29', 'Georgetown Pediatric Dentistry & Orthodontics', 'https://gtownkids.com', 'Travis Hildebrand', 'Pediatric Dentist', 'drtravis@gtownkids.com', '', 'YES', 62, 'Strong industry match with pediatric dentistry specialty in Texas, but limited by clinical staff persona rather than owner/decision-maker contact. Pediatric practices have high recall complexity making automation valuable.', 'Georgetown Pediatric Dentistry & Orthodontics is a specialized pediatric dental practice serving Georgetown, Texas and surrounding areas including Round Rock, Cedar Park, and Leander. They offer both pediatric dentistry and orthodontics with multiple sedation options and advanced diagnostic technology.', 'small', 'high', 'High no-show rates and appointment management complexity with pediatric patients requiring frequent recalls and orthodontic follow-ups across multiple treatment modalities', 'pediatric specialty, orthodontics dual-specialty, multi-location coverage area, sedation appointments requiring confirmation, advanced diagnostic technology suggesting high patient volume', 'medium', 'Champion / Economic Buyer', 'high', 'Managing dual-specialty recalls for both pediatric preventive visits and active ortho adjustments creates scheduling gaps that hurt production.', 'dual-specialty recall coordination complexity impacting revenue consistency', 'dual specialty scheduling gaps', 'Travis, most pediatric practices running both preventive and ortho see appointment slots going unfilled when kids miss their scheduled visits. The complexity gets worse when you\'re managing different recall intervals, some patients need routine cleanings every six months while active ortho cases need adjustments every 4-6 weeks. When a 10-year-old no-shows for their adjustment, that\'s not just a missed appointment, it\'s a gap in their treatment timeline. The manual reminder process most practices rely on doesn\'t account for the different urgency levels between a routine cleaning and an active orthodontic case.', 'why i\'m following up', 'Travis, I\'m following up because of Calyxr. We help pediatric and orthodontic practices solve the exact scheduling gap issue I mentioned yesterday. Instead of your team manually calling families for different types of appointments, Calyxr automatically sequences reminders based on treatment type and sends them through the channels each family actually responds to. One of our pediatric practices saw no-shows dropped from 28% to under 12% in 90 days, specifically because parents were getting ortho adjustment reminders differently than routine visit reminders.', 'Travis, staying with manual reminders for dual-specialty scheduling typically costs practices 15-20 unfilled chair hours per month. For active ortho cases, each missed adjustment can extend treatment time by 2-4 weeks, which means delayed case completion and reduced annual production per patient. The families get frustrated with longer treatment timelines, and your schedule stays inconsistent. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system and requires no IT setup. Would it make sense to see how this would look for Georgetown Pediatric specifically?', 'Travis, noticed Georgetown handles both pediatric preventive and orthodontics. Most dual-specialty practices struggle with no-shows because kids missing routine cleanings vs. ortho adjustments require different reminder approaches. Are you seeing scheduling gaps affect your ortho treatment timelines?', 'cost of empty chairs', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://gtownkids.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://gtownkids.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 5 Personalisation Insight + Agent 3 Top Pain + CSV (company, contact, specialty) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', 'drtravis@gtownkids.com', '', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/travis-hildebrand-342a3a89', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Pediatric Dentist', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
