(518, 65, '2026-03-30 14:33:30', 'Ghosh Orthodontics', 'https://ghoshortho.com', 'Sam Ghosh', 'Orthodontist', 'smile@ghoshortho.com', '', 'YES', 68, 'Strong fit as an established orthodontic practice with clinical owner contact, good revenue size, and clear dental specialty focus. Pennsylvania location and 3-person team size are workable but not optimal.', 'Ghosh Orthodontics is a 27-year-old, dual-location orthodontic practice in Pennsylvania with 3 employees serving adults and teens. With $2.8M revenue and Dr. Ghosh\'s perfectionist approach, they offer comprehensive treatment from traditional braces to Invisalign across Allentown and Pottsville locations.', 'small', 'high', 'Multi-location orthodontic practice with only 3 employees handling $2.8M revenue needs automated patient communication and recall to prevent treatment plan delays and no-shows across Allentown and Pottsville locations', 'multi-location practice, orthodontic specialty with long treatment cycles, small team (3 employees) for $2.8M revenue, adult and teen patient mix requiring different communication preferences, 27-year established practice likely using legacy systems', 'medium', 'Champion / Economic Buyer', 'high', 'With only 3 staff managing $2.8M across Allentown and Pottsville, your adjustment appointment no-shows likely create scheduling gaps that extend treatment duration.', 'orthodontic treatment timeline extension due to missed adjustments at lean-staffed multi-location practice', 'treatment delays costing months', 'Many orthodontic practices with multiple locations see the same pattern playing out. When adjustment appointments get missed, treatment timelines stretch from 18 months to 24+ months. Patients reschedule once, then life gets in the way again. What started as routine progress checks become scheduling gaps that delay case completion by months. The smaller the team, the harder it becomes to stay on top of every patient across every location, especially when you\'re managing $2.8M in revenue with just 3 staff members.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We help orthodontic practices eliminate the adjustment appointment no-shows that stretch treatment timelines. Instead of hoping patients remember their appointments, we ensure they show up through automated outreach that actually works. One of our orthodontic practices saw no-shows dropped from 28% to under 12% in 90 days, which cut their average treatment time by 3.2 months. Worth exploring how this could work across your Allentown and Pottsville locations?', 'Every missed adjustment appointment doesn\'t just delay that patient\'s treatment, it creates a domino effect across your schedule. When cases stretch from 18 months to 24+ months, you\'re looking at fewer new starts per year and frustrated families. With your current patient volume, that\'s potentially $200K+ in delayed revenue annually. Calyxr works with your existing practice management system and goes live in under a week, no long-term contracts. What if your treatment timelines could be consistently shorter starting next month?', 'Noticed you\'re managing $2.8M across two orthodontic locations with just 3 staff. The adjustment appointment no-shows must create real scheduling headaches that extend treatment times. How are you currently handling appointment confirmations across Allentown and Pottsville?', 'cost of delayed cases', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://ghoshortho.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Ghosh Orthodontics', '2.8M', '3', '', '', 'Pennsylvania', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://ghoshortho.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)