(523, 65, '2026-03-30 14:38:45', 'Greene Street Dental', 'https://greenestreetdental.com', 'Jill Hotchkiss', 'Dental Assistant', 'jill.hotchkiss@greenestreetdental.com', '', 'YES', 42, 'Strong dental industry match with US location, but contact is clinical staff influencer rather than decision-maker. Missing key data on practice size and technology stack limits scoring potential.', 'Greene Street Dental appears to be a small general dentistry practice in Pennsylvania with a lean front office structure, evidenced by the dental assistant serving as the primary contact rather than dedicated administrative staff.', 'small', 'medium', 'Small general dentistry practice with lean front office structure likely struggles with front desk staff wearing multiple hats and handling patient communication manually', 'dental assistant as primary contact, small practice size, general dentistry, lean front office structure, no dedicated administrative staff', 'medium', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With your dental assistant handling front desk duties, patient recall calls and appointment confirmations are probably competing with chairside responsibilities.', 'clinical staff pulled away from production for administrative tasks', 'front desk plus chairside', 'Many dental assistants at smaller practices find themselves juggling chairside responsibilities with front desk duties like appointment confirmations and recall calls. The constant interruptions between patient care and phone work make it tough to focus on either task properly. When you\'re trying to assist with procedures but also fielding calls about scheduling, both patients in the chair and on the phone end up waiting longer than they should.', 'why i\'m following up', 'I\'m following up because of Calyxr. We handle all the patient communication that pulls you away from chairside work, confirmation calls, recall outreach, and appointment scheduling. One of our general practices saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone, which meant their dental assistant could focus on what she was hired to do instead of constantly switching between the phone and the treatment room. Does this sound like what\'s happening at Greene Street?', 'When dental assistants spend half their day on phone duties, procedures take longer and patient care suffers. Every hour spent on manual recall calls is an hour not spent helping with treatment that actually generates revenue for the practice. The real cost isn\'t just your time, it\'s the appointments that don\'t get scheduled because patients couldn\'t reach anyone, and the procedures that take longer because you\'re not fully focused chairside. We can have you set up with no IT hassle required. What\'s your current biggest challenge with balancing front desk and chairside work?', 'Hi Jill, noticed you\'re handling both dental assisting and front desk at Greene Street. That split focus between chairside work and patient calls is exhausting. How are you managing the constant switching between treatment room and phone duties?', 'cost of splitting focus', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://greenestreetdental.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://greenestreetdental.com) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (partial Apollo export) → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (company, website, specialty) + Agent 2 Summary + Agent 3 Top