(525, 65, '2026-03-30 14:40:47', 'Greentree Dental Group', 'https://greentreedentalgroup.com', 'Jody Kear', 'Dentist', 'drkear@greentreedentalgroup.com', '', 'YES', 74, 'Strong dental practice fit with good revenue ($4.7M) and established Ohio presence since 1984, but primary contact is clinical staff rather than decision-maker, limiting immediate conversion potential.', 'Greentree Dental Group is a 40-year-established, dual-doctor general dentistry practice in Columbus, Ohio serving families with advanced services like same-day crowns, Invisalign, and sedation dentistry. At 10 employees with $4.7M revenue, they\'re expanding their facility to serve more patients but likely face scaling challenges with manual patient communication and scheduling coordination.', 'small', 'medium', 'Dual-doctor practice with $4.7M revenue and 10 employees likely struggling with manual scheduling coordination between two providers and limited patient communication automation during facility expansion', 'dual-doctor practice, 40-year established practice, facility expansion, 10 employees for $4.7M revenue, advanced services requiring complex scheduling, family dentistry with recall needs', 'medium', 'Champion', 'high', 'Dual-doctor scheduling between Drs. Kear and Ferguson with same-day CEREC crowns creates complex coordination that manual systems can\'t handle efficiently.', 'dual-provider scheduling complexity with same-day procedures', 'dual doctor scheduling chaos', 'Most dual-doctor practices hit the same wall around the $4-5M mark. Two providers, same-day CEREC work, emergency slots, hygiene recalls. The manual coordination between schedules becomes impossible when you\'re trying to expand. One doctor\'s running behind, the other has gaps, patients get shuffled around, and your front desk spends half their day playing schedule Tetris instead of focusing on patient experience. The bigger the practice gets, the messier it becomes.', 'why i\'m following up', 'The reason I\'m writing is Calyxr. We handle the dual-provider coordination automatically, so your front desk isn\'t constantly juggling Dr. Kear and Dr. Ferguson\'s schedules by hand. The system knows each doctor\'s preferences, CEREC timing, and emergency availability. One practice with two prosthodontists saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. Would automated schedule coordination between your providers make sense for Greentree Dental Group?', 'Every week your team manually coordinates dual-doctor scheduling, that\'s 12-15 hours of front desk time that could go toward patient care instead of schedule management. At $4.7M revenue with expansion plans, those coordination gaps are costing you filled appointment slots. Calyxr works with your existing PMS and goes live in under a week. What if your providers\' schedules coordinated themselves while your team focused on patients?', 'Jody, most dual-doctor practices around the $4-5M mark hit the same scheduling coordination wall. Manual systems can\'t handle two providers plus CEREC timing during expansion. How are you handling the schedule coordination between you and Dr. Ferguson right now?', 'cost of manual coordination', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://greentreedentalgroup.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Greentree Dental Group', '4.7M', '10', '', '', 'Ohio', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://greentreedentalgroup.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Agent 2 Research Summary + CSV (specialty, employees) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'CSV (contact name, title) + Agent 2 Research Summary + Apollo.io Enrich