(527, 65, '2026-03-30 14:42:47', 'Guerrino Dentistry', 'https://guerrinodentistry.com', 'Christa Maria', 'Registered Dental Hygienist', 'cmaria@guerrinodentistry.com', '', 'YES', 62, 'Multi-location dental practice in NY with strong revenue fit ($3.1M) and dental service keywords, but primary contact is clinical staff rather than decision-maker. 3 locations suggest operational complexity that benefits from automation.', 'Guerrino Dentistry is an established multi-specialty practice serving Westchester County with 2 locations in Scarsdale and Mt Vernon since 1989, generating $3.1M revenue with 8 employees. The practice offers comprehensive services including oral surgery, orthodontics, and implant dentistry with a bilingual patient base.', 'small', 'high', 'Multi-location coordination with comprehensive specialty services requires significant front desk coordination across locations and treatment types, likely overwhelming current 8-person team', 'multi-location practice, comprehensive specialty mix, 8 employees managing $3.1M revenue, established since 1989 likely using legacy systems, bilingual patient base requiring diverse communication', 'high', 'Wrong Contact', 'low', 'With 8 staff coordinating specialty referrals across Scarsdale and Mt Vernon locations, your front desk likely spends hours daily on cross-location scheduling and treatment plan coordination.', 'multi-location specialty coordination burden overwhelming small team', 'cross location scheduling chaos', 'Many specialty dental practices with multiple locations see the same pattern. Front desk teams spend hours daily coordinating between sites, managing specialty referrals, and trying to keep treatment plans aligned across different locations. With comprehensive services spanning two locations, the coordination load usually falls heaviest on clinical staff who end up fielding calls meant for scheduling. The 8-person team structure works well clinically, but the administrative coordination between Scarsdale and Mt Vernon can pull hygienists away from patient care.', 'why im following up', 'The reason I\'m reaching out is Calyxr. We handle the cross-location coordination that typically overwhelms front desk teams at specialty practices like yours. Instead of your clinical staff managing scheduling calls between sites, our system routes patients to the right location automatically and keeps treatment plans synchronized. One practice similar to Guerrino Dentistry saw their front desk teams reclaim 15+ hours a week on reminder calls alone. Does the coordination load between your two locations sound familiar?', 'When hygienists spend time on scheduling coordination instead of patient care, it costs the practice roughly $45 per hour in clinical productivity. Across 8 staff members handling cross-location coordination, that adds up to significant revenue sitting on the table. The manual approach also means patients sometimes slip through cracks between locations. We can have you live in under a week with no IT setup required. Would it make sense to see how this works for multi-location specialty practices?', 'Noticed Guerrino Dentistry runs comprehensive specialty services across two locations. With an 8-person team, the cross-location coordination probably keeps everyone busy beyond just clinical work. How do you currently handle the scheduling coordination between Scarsdale and Mt Vernon?', 'cost of manual coordination', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://guerrinodentistry.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Guerrino Dentistry', '3.1M', '8', '', '', 'New York', 'United States', 'CSV (company, industry, employees, specialty, state, country, revenue, contact title) + Apollo.io Enrichment → Claude AI (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)', 'Website Scrape (https://guerrinodentistry.com) + Apollo.io Enrichment →